title: helen's oven roast
directions: Will also need 2 sheets of aluminum foil (enough to cover roast).
Crisscross the foil.
It should look like a plus sign.

title: simplified quiche
directions: Line bottom of pie shell with bacon, cheese, onion and bell pepper.
Blend other ingredients in blender on high for one minute.
Pour over bacon, cheese, etc.
Bake at 350° for approximately 55 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.

title: nutty cheese bites
directions: Mix cheeses together and refrigerate until easy to handle. Form into balls, should make about 43.
Roll in walnuts. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In top of double boiler, mix cornstarch, flour, sugar and salt.
Gradually stir in boiling water.
In small bowl, beat egg yolks into cornstarch mixture.
Place top of double boiler over boiling water and cook about 5 minutes until filling is thick, stirring occasionally.
Remove pot from boiling water.
Mix in margarine, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Cover in cooker and cool slightly.
Pour in crust.
Top with your favorite meringue.

title: pumpkin fudge
directions: Cook together sugar, pumpkin, cornstarch, spice and milk until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water or reaches 235°.
Do not stir while cooking; add vanilla.
Stir together and cool in ice water to 110°.
Beat until smooth or it loses its gloss.
Pour on buttered plates and cut into small squares when nearly cool.

title: raspberry lemonade
directions: In a blender, mix first 5 ingredients until smooth, stopping to scrape down sides. Pour fruit mixture through a wire-mesh strainer into a pitcher, discarding solids. Stir in 3 cups of water. Serve over ice.

title: black bean chili
directions: Note #1:
The best bet is to by London broil and grind it yourself.

title: western pepper steak
directions: Put peppercorns into plastic bag and crush gently with rolling pin.
Press crushed peppers into both sides of steaks.
Heat 3 tablespoons of butter and oil in a large, heavy skillet over high heat.
Brown steaks on both sides and cook to desired degree of doneness.
Season with salt.
Remove steaks to a warm serving platter.
Reduce heat and add beef broth.
Stir well to loosen crumbs from bottom.
Continue cooking until sauce has reduced slightly; stir in the 1 tablespoon butter.
Pour over steaks and serve.
Serves 4.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add raisins.
Combine beaten eggs, buttermilk and shortening.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Pour batter in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken-macaroni salad
directions: Cook elbows according to directions and drain. Combine elbows, chicken, cucumber, radishes, celery and green onion.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over salad mixture. Toss, cover and chill.

title: 1-2-3-4 coconut cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Pour into three 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Stir lemon juice and rind into Marshmallow Fluff.
Blend the cream cheese with 1/4 cup heavy cream.
Whip remaining cream until it thickens, then add cream cheese.
Mix well.
Combine with Marshmallow Fluff and lemons.

title: chicken crepes florentine
directions: With Mixer:
Measure all ingredients except flour into a large mixing bowl.
Gradually add flour, beating with mixer until smooth. Cover batter and let stand at room temperature 1 hour before baking.

title: duzma casserole
directions: Slice vegetables to round medallions.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix oil, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: ann's butternut squash casserole
directions: Combine ingredients by stirring with a spoon or blender.
Bake in a greased casserole dish.
Set in a pan of water at 350° for 45 minutes or until set. Before removing from the oven, cover with buttered cracker crumbs and bake until brown. Very good.

title: nut cake
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Pour melted butter over this.
Add flour at once.
Add flavoring and nuts last.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: dutch crumb cake
directions: Put flour, sugar and margarine in a bowl.
Cut together with 2 knives making crumbs.
Take out almost 1/2 cup crumbs and set aside.
To the rest of the flour mixture, add milk, baking powder and salt.
Mixture will be thick.
Put into a well-greased pan (8 x 8-inch).
Sprinkle 1/2 cup crumbs on top and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Flatten tenders between sheets of wax paper to 1/4-inch thickness.
Combine flour, salt, lemon pepper and garlic powder; dredge chicken in mixture.
Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook 3 to 4 minutes each side. Drain on paper towels and keep warm.
Add lemon juice, wine and slices to pan drippings; heat, stirring well.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: celery hot dish
directions: In saucepan, cook celery 8 minutes. Drain. Slice water chestnuts and add.
Stir in pimentos and chicken soup.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
In small bowl, blend together melted butter and bread crumbs. Sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: creamy strawberry punch
directions: Process strawberries through blender.
Combine strawberries, chunks of ice cream and the ginger ale in a punch bowl.
Stir and serve immediately.

title: frito chili pie
directions: Place Fritos, cheese and onions in baking dish.
Alternate layers, ending with Fritos.
Pour heated chili over ingredients in baking dish.
Cook at 350° until onions are done.

title: swedish krumkaka(cookies)
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar and beat.
Add melted butter, cream, nutmeg and flour.
Beat until smooth. Bake on krumkaka iron using about 1/2 teaspoon for each cake.
Roll while warm.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add vanilla, flour, salt and nuts.
Mix well.
Form into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar after cool.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches and granulated sugar in saucepan until coated. Add cornstarch, brown sugar and water.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick.
Add butter and lemon juice. Pour into oiled 12 x 7-inch baking dish.

title: pumpkin coffee cake
directions: Melt margarine, add sugar and brown sugar.
Mix in flour, pumpkin pie spice and salt until crumbly.
Remove 1 cup to small bowl; add nuts and cinnamon.
Mix well, set aside.
To remaining mixture, add rest of the ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes.

title: chow mein guyanese salad
directions: Boil noodles in a large pot with 2 teaspoons salt, water and 2 tablespoons oil (to prevent noodles from sticking).
Let cook for 10 minutes.
Place meat, sweet peas and cabbage in a pan with 2 tablespoons oil and add cooked noodles, soy sauce, black pepper and other seasonings to taste.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Combine flour, nuts and butter in a medium bowl.
Mix thoroughly and press into the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake in the oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove and cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well after cream cheese softens.
Roll in chopped pecans. Makes 3 balls.

title: my own thing cake
directions: Cut rhubarb into 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange in greased 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and gelatin.
Top with marshmallows. Prepare cake mix with eggs, oil and water as directed on package. Spread batter evenly over marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 50-55 minutes or until cake is done.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Turn out of pan upside down onto serving tray.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: layered salad
directions: Use a deep glass serving bowl.
Each ingredient will be 1 layer.
The bottom layer will be the first ingredient. Refrigerate for 8 hours before serving.

title: brandon's monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into golf ball size and bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes.
Makes 22 dozen.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown ground beef, green pepper and onion in large skillet. Add spices to this mixture as you brown.
Add rest of ingredients, except rice, and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add water and rice.
Put lid on skillet, turn off heat and let stand until rice is tender.

title: linguine and clam sauce
directions: Melt butter and olive oil in pan.
Saute garlic until soft and golden with 2 teaspoons of salt.
Add cloves and simmer 2 minutes. Toss with 1 pound of linguine and serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into walnut-sized balls.
Place on cookie sheet to freeze. When frozen, put into freezer bags.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add oatmeal and nuts. Mix well.
Shape in balls.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill thoroughly overnight.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in moderate oven for 10 minutes (350°).
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: pumpkin butter
directions: In blender container, combine all ingredients and blend until smooth.
Simmer in small saucepan until slightly thickened, stirring often.

title: cheese balls
directions: Cream the margarine and cheese.
Add flour, salt and pecans. Form into balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole(microwave)
directions: Crumble ground beef in colander. Set in bowl and cook in microwave for 6 minutes. Stir and break up beef once or twice during cooking period. Remove from microwave.
Put drained meat into a large bowl. Stir in onion, soups and enchilada sauce.
Cook 5 minutes. Add tortillas or taco chips, olives and chilies.
Stir to combine ingredients.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch glass dish and cook 5 minutes. Top with cheese and return to microwave to melt, about 1 to 2 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: strawberry rhubarb jam
directions: Mix together the rhubarb, pineapple and sugar; let stand for 30 minutes.
Bring mixture slowly to boil; cook for 12 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in strawberry jello (dry); mix until dissolved.
Pour into jelly jars.
Freezes well or keep in refrigerator.
Makes approximately 1 pint.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400° for shiny metal pan or to 375° for dark metal or glass baking pan.
Grease an 8 or 9-inch square pan. Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken.
Skin and debone.
Melt margarine and mix with Pepperidge Farm stuffing.
Sprinkle 1/3 of stuffing on the bottom of casserole dish.
Add a layer of chicken.
Add cream of mushroom soup (undiluted) on top of chicken, another layer of stuffing and add last of chicken.
Spread cream of mushroom soup over chicken and end with last of stuffing.
Pour 2 cans of broth over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: healthy nonalcoholic cocktail
directions: Fill glass with 2/5 cranberry juice and 2/5 orange juice and fill rest with ginger ale.
A resident favorite.

title: super quick appetizer
directions: Spread out crescent dough on cookie sheet, pressing together perforations. Cover with 1 layer of salami, then Provolone cheese. Roll up like a jelly roll, pinching ends together.
Cook according to directions on dough package.
Really good.
Very simple. Slice and serve.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Slice onion and pepper over cabbage; pour sugar over this.
Do not stir.
Heat rest of ingredients to boil. Pour over cabbage mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: easy chicken and dressing
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place prepared stuffing in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange chicken breasts on stuffing. Mix together soup and milk.
Pour over breasts.
Sprinkle grated cheese over breasts.
Bake 1 hour.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Note:
Use 12 ounces of orange juice if not adding rum and applejack.

title: roast beef
directions: In a large skillet or pot, season your roast with pepper, salt and oregano.
Let it set overnight in your refrigerator.
Put it in a pot and cut up your onion and green pepper over it.
Bring it to a boil.
Don't forget the 2 cups of water. Simmer, covered, 1 hour. Turn roast.
Brown flour in pan drippings in skillet. When brown, add water to liquid in pot roast.
Cook slowly until thick.

title: grilled beef with peppers
directions: Mix soy sauce, sugar and garlic together in a bowl. Add beef strips and toss to coat.
Marinate for 20 to 30 minutes.
Heat oil in a heavy skillet and saute beef and peppers over medium-high heat until the steak is done and the peppers are hot but still crisp.
It won't take long, 2 to 3 minutes at most.
Serve peppers and steak as desired over rice or use as teriyaki-style dish as well as main dish.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients with salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste. Shape in walnut size balls and brown these in skillet. (Reserve drippings to make sauce.) In skillet, add Heinz chili sauce, juice of 2 lemons and grape jelly. Stir until jelly is dissolved. Add meatballs. Simmer 30 minutes over low heat, then serve hot.

title: dumplings for sauerkraut
directions: Mix all together.
Drop in boiling broth about the size of egg.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes.
Add water to make broth come to top of sauerkraut.

title: blackened chicken breasts
directions: Mix together all spices.
Coat chicken with mix (1 tablespoon per piece) and baste with melted margarine.
Grill, basting with margarine after turning once or cook in skillet in hot oil. Excellent on a bun with mayo, lettuce and tomato!

title: chicken rolls
directions: Mix together chicken and cream cheese.
Separate and flatten rolls.
Fill each roll with 1/8 of the chicken mixture.
Roll dough around filling and seal edges.
Dip tops of rolls in melted margarine and then in crushed, seasoned bread crumbs or stuffing mix.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve with chicken gravy.

title: pink party punch
directions: Combine all juices and sugar, mixing well.
Freeze until slushy.
Add ginger ale right before serving.
Serves about 25 (5 ounce) servings.

title: platter cookies
directions: Melt butter; let cool.
Add sugars, vanilla and eggs to cooled butter; beat until creamy.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Add cereal and oatmeal; beat well.

title: egg and asparagus casserole
directions: Arrange asparagus
in a clockwise position in bottom of casserole dish.
Use
can of soup and spread over asparagus. Slice 3 boiled eggs and place over soup; spread with 1/2 cup cheese.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.	Cover top layer
with
buttered
bread
crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Garnish and serve.

title: moist buttery red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and cream until well blended. Mix food coloring and cocoa; add to creamed mixture.
Sift salt, soda and flour; add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Fold, do not beat.
Bake in three 9-inch cake pans or 9 x 13-inch pan lined with wax paper at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool, frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: spring break shrimp
directions: Cook shrimp in margarine; remove shrimp, but save shrimp broth. Add 1/4 cup of broth and reduce for 5 minutes.
Add wine and cook for several more minutes.
Add seasoning, mustard and 1 tablespoon flour.
Gradually thicken.
When mixture reaches thin paste texture, add green onions and shrimp.
Stir until coated.
Serve over precooked angel hair pasta.

title: chunky chili
directions: Cut steak into 1/2-inch cubes.
Coat meat with flour.
Heat oil in 3-quart pyro-ceramic casserole over medium-high heat.
Add meat and brown on all sides.
Add celery, onion, garlic and water. Cover with casserole lid.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes or until vegetables are just about tender, stirring once.
Add tomatoes (cut into pieces), tomato paste, chili powder, bouillon, sugar, cumin and pepper.
Cover.
Microwave on High 5 minutes. Stir and then microwave on Low (30%) 45 to 50 minutes or until meat is tender, stirring once.
Stir in beans; cover.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes or until heated through.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: pipinola narazuke
directions: Peel
pipinola	skin; cut into squares.
Soak in salted water for
day.
Pat dry the pipinola; soak into sake kasu sauce
for 4	to
5 days.
Rinse the sake kasu; cut into bite size pieces and serve.

title: norwegian cheese ball
directions: Put jar of English cheese in pan of hot water for 10 minutes to soften.
Cream together Philadelphia cheese and English cheese. Add 3 tablespoons pecans, onions and most of parsley.
Form into ball.
Sprinkle with remainder of nuts and parsley.
Put into the refrigerator and chill.
Serve on Ritz crackers.

title: chocolate kahlua cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Combine crushed cookies and butter.
Press into the bottom of spring-form pan.

title: pleasin cheese and herb dressing
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in a saucepan and boil 2 minutes (stirring constantly).
Remove from heat. Add the peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper. Cool.
Store in cookie jar.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear bread into small pieces.
Mix together all ingredients in oblong dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Chop onion and bell pepper.
Mix all ingredients together. Put in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: peanut pattie
directions: Mix ingredients; stir until sugar dissolves.
Cook to a firm (but not hard ball).
Remove from fire and add 1 teaspoon vanilla, 1/8 teaspoon salt and a few drops red coloring.
Beat until thick. Drop by spoonfuls on a buttered dish.
(Not waxed paper, it will stick.)
Or you can pour on a buttered plate and cut later.

title: raspberry wine vinegar
directions: Heat wine and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Add raspberries and stir.
Place in a quart jar and place lid on jar.
Put in a dark, cool place for 3 or 4 days.
Take from storage and strain through a coffee filter or muslin.
The raspberry wine vinegar can then be stored in bottles in a cool place or refrigerator.
Can be used as a salad dressing.
For those on a low-fat diet, this dressing has no fat.
Makes 26 fluid ounces.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together, add eggs and mix well. Add zucchini and vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Blend in dry ingredients gradually to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Grease loaf pan well (13 X 5 X 3).
Bake at 350 for 1 hour.
Cool on wire rack at least 10-15 minutes.

title: gram's molasses cookies
directions: Blend first four ingredients.
Add spices.
Add molasses, soda, sour milk and flour to make dough stiff enough to roll.
Mixture will be soft and gooey; roll in plenty of flour.
It will stick and be gooey.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into shapes and bake at 400° for about 12 minutes.
Frost with white frosting and top with coconut.

title: cream cheese and beef spread
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add onion, dried beef and olives.
Mix well.
Chill overnight.

title: chocolate chip dessert
directions: Dip cookies in milk and layer on bottom of container.
Spread layer of Cool Whip.
Repeat procedure, ending with Cool Whip on top.
Chill.

title: cake pan cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly in mixing bowl.
Pour into greased 8-inch round pans (2).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.
May also be used for cupcakes.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate dream pie
directions: Melt the butter.
Mix the flour, chopped pecans and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 10 or 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix the confectioners sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix the instant pudding as directed on box.
Add the Cool Whip.
Keep in fridge overnight and serve.

title: cornbread pielets
directions: Heat grease in deep fryer.
Add enough milk to remaining ingredients to blend.
Using a tablespoon (depending on the size you want), drop mixture into hot grease.
Be careful not to splash hot grease.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: baked pineapple salad
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and juice; pour over pineapple and cheese (9-inch glass dish).
Mix together margarine and cracker crumbs (enough crackers to make a thick oatmeal base) and spread on top of pineapple and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve hot!

title: crock-pot turkey breast
directions: Spray crock-pot with nonstick spray.
Place turkey breast inside and sprinkle on seasoning items.
Cover and cook on high for 4 hours.
For a prettier finish, brown under broiler when done.

title: baked popcorn
directions: Stir oleo, sugar, syrup and salt.
Boil without stirring for five minutes; remove from heat; add soda, vanilla and pour over 6 quarts popped corn.
Pour into at least two large cookie sheets and bake for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir each, every 15 minutes.
Break apart and store in air tight containers.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Combine raisins and water in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer until raisins are tender.
Mix sugar and cornstarch. Stir into raisin mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and lemon juice.
Serve over ham, lamb or pork.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs.
Beat in milk, baking powder and flour.
Spread mixture in 8-inch square pan.
Peel and slice apples very thin.
Spread over batter.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip to serve.

title: irish stew
directions: Chop vegetables and lamb.
Place them in stew pan in alternating layers of vegetables and meat.
Add salt, pepper and water.
Cover pan and cook slowly until the greater part of the gravy is absorbed and all ingredients are tender.

title: apple crumble
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a square 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish or rectangular dish, 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch.
Mix baking mix, sugar and egg until crumbly; sprinkle over apples.
Drizzle with margarine; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in shells.
Bake at 350° until middle doesn't wiggle.
You may have to cover these with foil towards the end of the baking, so they won't burn on top.
I always have to do that.

title: easy garlic biscuits
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well. Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: pan enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef.
Heat together enchilada sauce and tomato sauce.
Layer as follows:
6 corn tortillas dipped in enchilada sauce, ground beef, rice, half of the cheese, 6 corn tortillas not dipped.
Pour remaining enchilada sauce, then the remaining cheese.
Bake at 425° until cheese melts and browns, approximately 20 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In saucepan, mix together sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually add milk, then chipped chocolate.
Cook in double boiler, stirring constantly until thick.
Put a little of chocolate mixture into beaten yolks.
Then pour into hot mixture and cook two minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Pour into cold pie crust.
Chill in refrigerator. Decorate with Cool Whip.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions, green pepper and celery.
Add tomatoes, catsup, barbecue sauce, mustard and seasonings.
Simmer over low heat for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve over hamburger buns. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and sift together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in shallow buttered pan (8 x 8-inch) in a 425° oven for 20 minutes.

title: creamy chicken primavera(rush hour recipe)
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken in butter.
Add Pasta Accents and water.
Cover; simmer 7 to 9 minutes until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream. Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate dipped strawberries
directions: Melt chocolates, butter and syrup together on top of stove or on High in microwave.
Dip strawberries into chocolate and place on wax paper to cool.

title: squash patties
directions: Boil squash in water until tender.
Drain.
Mash and drain again.
Add other ingredients to mashed squash.
You may need to add more flour and meal if batter is not stiff enough.
Spoon into a hot frying pan and cook on medium heat until brown and crisp.

title: majarete(puerto rico)
directions: Mix rice meal, salt and sugar.
Add milk and lemon rind.
Cook at low heat, stirring constantly to prevent clumps.
When mixture thickens, pour in dishes.
Let cool and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Cut lettuce into small pieces into salad bowl.
Layer one or more of the next ingredients over the lettuce.
Crumble or cut bacon into small pieces and layer over salad.
Mix and beat salad dressing and Equal until dissolved (use like a frosting). Top with grated cheese and let set a few hours before serving.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in tepid water.
Beat egg.
Mix shortening, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Pour boiled water into mixture. Stir until sugar dissolves.
Let stand until tepid.
Pour in yeast, egg and mix.
Stir in flour and let rise in warm place for 1 hour. Stir down, cover and put in refrigerator.
The next day, take out and poke down and let rise again.
Poke down 2 or 3 times.
Divide in two hunks and knead.
Makes 1/4-inch rolls.
Dip rolls in melted butter.
Fold and put in pan.
Let rolls rise again, double in size.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix crab meat, mayonnaise, egg, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce; form into cakes.
The smaller you make the cakes, the better they hold together.
Dip both sides of each cake in bread crumbs.

title: toffee gram bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Line cookie sheet with graham crackers (may not use whole box). In small saucepan, boil butter, margarine and white sugar for 2 minutes. Pour over crackers. Sprinkle with almonds and bake for 15 minutes. Remove with spatula. Place on wax paper. Will harden in 5 minutes. Enjoy. Store in airtight container.

title: beef ragout(health conscious)
directions: Heat a skillet; saute ground beef.
Pour contents of pan into a colander lined with paper towels.
Drain fat; return meat to pan.
Add onion; saute for 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir in water, wine, hot pepper, garlic, tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili powder, cumin, oregano, salt and pepper.
Bring mixture to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add kidney beans; simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Coat chicken with flour, salt and pepper.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat (350°).
Brown chicken and cover.
Reduce heat and cook 20 minutes.
Turn occasionally.
Remove cover and cook 10 minutes.

title: farm house spiced tea
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Add hot water.
Mix well.
(The dry mixture may be stored in a tight container.)
Water may be added later by the gallon or cup.
For a cup, use 1 to 1 1/2 heaping tsp. dry mixture.

title: salmon loaf supreme
directions: Mix well all ingredients except salmon.
Add salmon gently last.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Loosen carefully from pan and place on platter.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese with butter.
Stir in flour, salt and paprika. Mix well (by hands works best).
Wrap 1 teaspoon of dough around an olive.
Place on cookie sheet.
Freeze firmly.
Place in plastic bag and store in freezer until needed.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chicken divan
directions: Remove skin from chicken breasts and bake or boil. Cut into pieces. Cook broccoli according to package directions, drain. Arrange broccoli in a greased 7 x 11 casserole dish, place chicken over broccoli. Combine mayonnaise, soup, lemon juice and curry powder, pour over chicken, sprinkle with cheese. Mix bread crumbs and butter, sprinkle over cheese. Bake 25 minutes in 350° oven. 8 servings.

title: chop suey
directions: Use wok or large cast-iron skillet.
Cut celery, sweet pepper and mushrooms into thin strips.
Cut beef into 2 inch thin strips. Mix cornstarch with water; set wok or skillet over high heat.
Add oil; add each ingredient separately.
Stir-fry each one minute before adding the next ingredients:
onion and garlic, celery, green pepper and bean sprouts.
Push vegetables to sides of wok or skillet.
Push mushrooms to one side.
Add beef and stir until warmed through.
Sprinkle soy sauce over ingredients.
Add cornstarch mixture.
Mix all ingredients until sauce is thick and clear.
Serve at once.
Yield:
6 servings.
Carbohydrate 13 g, protein 14 g, fat 16 g, calories 252.
One serving = 2 meat medium fat exchanges, 1 bread starch exchange, 1 fat exchange.

title: tin can casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and
pour in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches and juice in a 9-inch x 9-inch pan.
(I slice my peaches again if they are big).
In a bowl, place margarine, sugar, and flour.
Cut with a fork until crumbly.
Evenly spread this mixture over peaches.
Bake in a 400° oven about 40 to 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Beat cream until stiff and then add fruit cocktail, marshmallows and walnuts, then let chill.

title: play doh
directions: May substitute 1 package unsweetened Kool-Aid for coloring and fragrance.

title: johnnycake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
If no buttermilk, use 2 cups of milk with 1 teaspoon vinegar per cup.
Then must use baking powder instead of baking soda.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Can serve with butter and/or syrup.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Remove egg yolks; mash and combine with the remaining ingredients.
Stuff egg whites; chill and sprinkle with paprika.

title: pecan coffee cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan heavily.
Sprinkle pecans on bottom of pan. Layer rolls in pan.
Sprinkle with pudding.
Melt oleo with brown sugar; pour over rolls.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with damp towel and let rise overnight on counter.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°. Turn out of pan immediately.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix ingredients and let stand for 2 hours.
Make 1/2-inch balls and fry in hot oil until brown on both sides.
Drain and roll in powdered sugar.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute hamburger and drain off most of the fat.
Then add the rest of the ingredients.
Cover and cook on low heat for approximately 35 to 45 minutes.

title: no ka oi banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and egg.
Add mashed bananas.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix together soda and sour milk (it will foam up).
Add to banana mixture.
Add nuts and dry ingredients until blended.
Put in greased and floured pans.
Makes 1 large loaf or 2 small loaves or 4 soup cans.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes for large loaf, 30 to 35 minutes for small loaves.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sugar, oil and apricot nectar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Mix powdered sugar and lemon juice.
Spread on cake while cake is still warm.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Add taco seasoning and 1/2 cup water to ground chuck.
Cook rice according to directions on package.
Melt Velveeta cheese in microwave with Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Mix all together.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Serve with chips.

title: icebox banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions on box. Mix pudding and Cool Whip together. Add vanilla.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook and drain eggplant. Beat eggs and milk together.
Add eggplant, onion, salt, pepper and soup.
Mix this with half of the crackers, margarine and cheese.
Cook about 30 minutes at 350°. Add cheese and rest of crackers coated with margarine.
Cook until brown.

title: drunken wieners
directions: The night before:
Combine whiskey, chili sauce, brown sugar, onion and peppers.
Bring to a boil and let simmer for about 1 hour.
Refrigerate overnight.
About 3 hours prior to serving, put sausages in crock-pot and pour sauce over.
Heat until sauce cooks through meat (about 3 hours).

title: mexican pork chops
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper.
In skillet brown chops in oil over a medium heat.
In a 13x9 glass baking dish, combine rice, water, tomato sauce, and taco seasoning.
Place pork chops on top of rice mixture.
Top with pepper slices.
Cover and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350 degrees.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with the cheese.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.
Serve.

title: glazed cinnamon breakfast loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3). Mix brown sugar and cinnamon and set aside. Beat Bisquick, sugar, milk and eggs in large bowl on low speed for 30 seconds. Beat on medium speed for 3 minutes. Stir in raisins. Pour 1/3 of batter into mixture. Sprinkle about 3 tablespoons of brown sugar mixture. Repeat process 5 times. Bake until toothpick comes out clean (40 to 50 minutes). Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan. Cool completely. Drizzle with glaze.

title: chili con carne
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook beef and green pepper until beef is browned and pepper is tender, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix flour, oleo and powdered sugar together until crumbly.
Pat into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender, but firm.
Drain and cool.
Mince green pepper and slice onion.
Mix with cooled carrots.
Cover with remaining ingredients and marinate about 12 hours.
Keeps at least 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: eggplant with hot garlic sauce(based on honolulu's maple garden restaurant recipe)
directions: Blend ginger, garlic, sugar, shoyu, vinegar and hot pepper sauce in a bowl.
Mix cornstarch with water in a separate bowl. Blend into first mixture.
Heat the oil to 360° in a wok or deep-fryer.
Cook the eggplant and pork until eggplant is golden brown and pork is tender.
The pork will take much less time to cook.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Remove all but 1 teaspoon of oil from pan.
Add sauce mixture and heat until slightly thickened.
Place eggplant in serving container and pour sauce on top.
Cover and heat in oven or microwave oven before serving.
Do not try to mix or eggplant will break apart.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable sausage loaf
directions: Grind vegetables. Beat eggs and add other ingredients. Form loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesy spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a microwavable bowl.
Microwave on high, stirring frequently, until mixture is smooth.
Serve with raw vegetables, bread or chips.

title: coconut-oat waffles
directions: Blend cornmeal with milk and coconut.
Stir in remaining ingredients with spoon.
Let sit 1 hour or more in refrigerator. Bake on piping hot ungreased waffle iron until done.

title: golden salad
directions: Drain fruit, saving syrup.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water; cool, add juice from fruit.
Cool completely.
Add pineapple and marshmallows.
Push down into jello and place in refrigerator and congeal.
Mix Cool Whip and mayonnaise.
Spread on top of salad.
Grate cheese and scatter on top of salad.
This will keep in refrigerator several days.
Especially good with meats.

title: beef fajitas
directions: Cut beef into 4 pieces.
Put in plastic bag with lime juice, garlic, salt and pepper.
Close bag and marinate in refrigerator for 2 to 30 hours or overnight.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Chop nuts; cut cherries.
Crumble crackers and mix together. Melt marshmallows in Eagle Brand milk over low heat; stir constantly.
Pour over chopped ingredients and mix well.
Mold in well-buttered foil or container of your choice.

title: red pepper haste
directions: Cut up fine, or use food processor.
Cover with salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain well.
Add the vinegar.
Add the mustard seed.
Cook until well heated and the sugar is melted.
Do not boil.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel apples and core.
Slice very thin and put in pie shell. Mix water and flour together; put on apples.
Mix sugar and cinnamon, then sprinkle it on apples.
Cut butter up in small pieces and put on apples.
Take other pie shell; place on top of pie and press down edges with fork.
Sprinkle remaining sugar and cinnamon mixture on top.
Put butter on top of that.
Bake for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: play dough
directions: Stir last 3 ingredients into first 3 ingredients.
Cook over low heat until mixture appears slightly transparent.
Don't overcook.
Remove from heat, turn onto tabletop and knead until smooth. Store in covered container.

title: spinach fandango
directions: Brown meat in skillet with onion, garlic, mushrooms and oregano.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place frozen spinach on top and cover to steam until mixable.
Add celery soup and sour cream. Mix thoroughly.
Top with cheese.
Bake uncovered for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Put bread, cheese, ham and mushrooms into two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Beat eggs, milk, butter and mustard.
Pour over ham mixture. Let sit overnight.
Bake covered at 350° for one hour, uncover last 10 minutes.

title: polish misteaks
directions: Brown meats together and drain.
Mix oregano, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Melt cheese and spread on rye bread. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sea slaw
directions: Combine vegetables and add seafood.
Prepare dressing and add to salad.
Mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate.
Serve cold.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese soup
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomatoes and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Pour into soup bowls; top with tomatoes. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: corn light bread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 375° until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Slice about 1/2-inch thick and fry in shortening until lightly brown.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat
eggs
with
mixer.
Add
sugar gradually and beat until mixture
is thick and lemon colored.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Fold with vanilla into egg mixture.
Turn into shallow 15
x
10-inch pan lined with greased paper.
Bake at 400°
for about 13 minutes or until done.
Cut crisp edges off cake.
Turn pan
at
once
onto
a clean cloth sprinkled with powdered
sugar. Remove
paper
from
cake;
spread cake with softened
jelly or jam, then roll it up quickly, wrap in towel and cool on rack.

title: eggs rebel
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 1/2-inch casserole dish.
Cook sausage or ham in skillet and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Place cubed bread and sausage on bottom of casserole dish.
Mix the remaining ingredients with a mixer or in the blender.
Do not overbeat. Pour over the bread and sausage; cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with electric mixer 2 minutes or until creamy. Gradually add sugar, beating 5 to 7 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time beating just until yellow disappears. Stir in vanilla and lemon. Combine flour and next 3 ingredients, add to butter mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Beat at low speed just until blended after each addition. Pour into a greased and floured 12 cup Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan on a wire rack 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on rack. Pour buttermilk glaze on warm cake.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in graham cracker crumbs. Mix, then pat in bottom for crust.
Add nuts, chips and coconut and pour milk over all.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown on top.
Cool.

title: chicken or turkey tetrazzini
directions: In Dutch oven, melt butter.
Cook onion until tender. Dissolve bouillon cube in water.
Add bouillon to soup; stir until smooth.
Add turkey or chicken, parsley flakes, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook over slow heat.
Stir in noodles; heat through.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in a buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: lemon ricotta cheese cake
directions: Make cake mix batter according to directions on box.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend together Ricotta cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Spoon over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar after cooled.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Make a paste of vinegar and cocoa; add to mixture.
Sift salt and soda with flour.
Add to mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Blend well and add vanilla and coloring.
Mix well.
Pour into 3 (8-inch) greased cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
Use Red Velvet Cake Icing.

title: sweet and sour dressing for vegetable salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
This makes enough for several salads.

title: brown rice with black beans
directions: Cook brown rice in water as directed on package.
Meanwhile, saute onion, sweet red pepper and jalapeno peppers in olive oil until softened but not browned, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Add corn, chopped tomato and black beans with liquid from can.
Sprinkle with chili powder and balsamic vinegar and stir well.
Simmer, covered, 15 minutes.
Keep warm until rice is ready.

title: zucchini triangles
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Place in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool in pan. Cut in triangles. Freezes well.

title: black bean and corn salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except tomatoes.
Cover and chill.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Mix well. Add vanilla, salt and cocoa and mix.
In separate bowl, mix flour and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients and water, a little at a time, to the first bowl and mix.
Mix in the sauerkraut.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13 cake pan for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Use your favorite cream cheese frosting.

title: neiman's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and both sugars. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and soda. Add chips, candy and nuts. Mix well. Refrigerate for 1/2 hour. Roll into balls and place 2 inches apart on a cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Mix cheeses; fold in onion, green peppers and beef.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Oil 9-inch square pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine and chocolate in saucepan.
Remove from heat and add all the ingredients, except the eggs.
Mix and blend thoroughly.
Then add eggs and beat well.
Pour into prepared pan and bake 30 minutes or until crusty.
Cool in pan; cut before completely cool.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour 1/3 cup fresh squeezed carrot juice over all as needed to moisten.

title: barbecue franks
directions: In saucepan, add margarine, onions and celery; saute. Add water, ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Simmer 15 minutes. You can leave franks whole or cut in bite size pieces. Place franks in casserole dish; add sauce. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Great as an appetizer or main meat.

title: potato chip potatoes
directions: Melt 6 tablespoons of margarine in a two-quart Pyrex dish at 375°.
Add potatoes. Turn once in butter.
Mix next four ingredients and sprinkle over potatoes.
Drizzle with about 2 tablespoons melted margarine and bake at 375° for about 45 minutes until potatoes are tender and top is crisp.

title: good cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased Bundt cake pan.
Bake 55 minutes at 350°.

title: bean soup
directions: In large saucepan or Dutch oven, soak beans overnight in 6 cups of water (or bring to boil 2 minutes and let stand covered 1 hour). Add remaining 4 cups of water, the ham hock, bay leaf and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are almost tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, cover, cook 20 to 30 minutes more until beans are tender.
Discard bay leaf.
Cut meat from bones and return to soup.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix mushroom soup and milk in saucepan., Add cheese with onions.
Drain tuna and mix with the rest.
Boil noodles and drain. Mix together.

title: pancit(a dish from the philippines)
directions: Boil the diced chicken in a large pot, 3/4 filled with water. Put 2 dashes of Mrs. Dash or any herbs if you have and 1/2 tablespoon of soy sauce.
Drain the chicken and put aside the broth.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Blend cheese and mayonnaise with sugar.
Add fruit, nuts and cream (whipped).
Pour into 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Freeze for 6 hours or overnight.
Let stand for 15 minutes at room temperature before removing from pan.
Slice and serve on lettuce. Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken spaghetti or noodles
directions: Boil chicken with a little onion and bell pepper.
Save juice and add spaghetti or noodles and boil noodles or spaghetti until tender.

title: dr. e's fried rice
directions: Dice chicken nuggets and cooked sausage.
Boil one cup of rice and drain.
Put drained rice and soy sauce in wok or saute pan. Add chicken and sausage pieces.
Add onion powder and Mrs. Dash spice to taste.
Mix thoroughly, being careful not to burn rice. Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: creamy dark fudge
directions: Combine chocolate morsels and condensed milk in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat until chocolate melts, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Spread chocolate mixture in a lightly greased 8 inch square pan. Sprinkle with pecans.

title: easter bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix 1 cup flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Combine milk and margarine in pan and heat until warm.
Add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and 1/2 cup flour or enough to make a thick batter.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough. Knead 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn to grease top. Cover; let rise in warm place about 1 hour.
Add nuts and seed. Punch down; turn and knead in nuts and seed.
Divide in half; roll 24-inches long each.
Twist together and join ends to form a ring. Place on baking sheet.
Brush with margarine and tuck raw eggs into twist.
Cover.
Rise 1 hour.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: chicken and wild rice bake
directions: Combine rice mix, seasonings from packet, soup mix and celery in 4-quart casserole.
Arrange chicken over top of rice mix. Cook, covered, on Full power in microwave for 21 to 26 minutes or until chicken is done and rice is tender.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Keep liquid.
Mix bananas and marshmallows with half of fruit juices.
Mix rest of juices with pudding mix.
Combine fruit, marshmallows and nuts.
Pour mix over fruit and nuts.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: deep dish cheddar chicken
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Blend in flour and seasonings. Gradually add milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add chicken, cheese and broccoli.
Pour into an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Separate dough into 1 large and 2 small rectangles.
Press perforations together.
Cut into 12 strips and place on casserole in lattice form.
Brush with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fudge cookies
directions: Mix in large bowl the oatmeal, vanilla and pecans.
Bring to a boil in large saucepan the sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Pour second mixture over first; stir thoroughly and drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.
Cookies are ready to eat when cool.

title: white chip orange dream cookies
directions: Combine flour (I use self rising, don't use baking soda and salt), baking soda and salt in small bowl.
Beat butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar in large mixer bowl until creamy. Beat in egg and orange peel.
Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in morsels.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheets.

title: tex-mex popcorn
directions: Keep popcorn warm.
Mix seasonings together and toss with popcorn.
Add cheese and mix thoroughly.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Place 1/2 cup miniature marshmallows on a tray or in a shallow pan. Freeze until firm. Place semi-sweet chocolate and butter in large bowl. Set aside. In heavy saucepan, combine sugar, 1 cup miniature marshmallows and evaporated milk. Bring to a boil over medium heat, then boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour over chocolate mixture. Stir until well blended and mixture begins to thicken. Add walnuts, vanilla and frozen marshmallows. Pour into a lightly greased 8-inch square pan. Chill until firm. Cut into squares. Store, covered, in a cool place. Makes 2 pounds.

title: liver dish
directions: Brown liver.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Note:
I like to cut the apples so you can see them.

title: chop suey hot dish
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Mix all ingredients into large casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Take out and sprinkle with 1 can of chow mein noodles.
Return to oven for 1/2 hour.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Blend well.
Add salt and garlic to taste.

title: stuffed grouse
directions: Shell nuts.
Peel and dice apples.
Simmer apples until soft. Mix together apples, currants, nuts, salt, pepper and crumbled bread.
Stuff birds.
Brush with butter and wrap in foil or cook in cooking bags.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: toasted coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in unbaked shell.	Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: chocolate-nut candy
directions: Microwave:
In a 2-quart glass bowl, melt bark on 50% power for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring every 2 to 3 minutes.
Add cocoa and mix well. Stir in nuts.
Dip out on wax paper using 1 teaspoon dips.
Let cool until firm.
Store in covered container.

title: aunt lola's golden pound cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir the shortening to soften.
Gradually add sugar and cream together until light and fluffy.
Beat 3 minutes on medium speed.
Add lemon peel and juice.
Add milk and mix enough to break up creamed mixture. Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture and mix until smooth. Add eggs, one at a time; beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
When cooled, sift confectioners sugar over top.

title: salsa sauce
directions: Mix all in a bowl and refrigerate.
Let stand for at least 2 hours.
Serve with taco chips.

title: jalapeno cheese dip
directions: Remove stems and seeds from jalapeno peppers, saving the liquid.
Remove cheese from refrigerator and grate.
Let stand until room temperature.
Grind together the peppers, onion and garlic.
Place cheese in a mixing bowl and beat until smooth.
Add the pepper mixture and the liquid and blend for 5 minutes.
Add salad dressing, increase speed of mixer and let mix until smooth. Will keep indefinitely in the refrigerator.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except the cracker crumbs, melted oleo and almonds.
Place in casserole. Top with the mixture of the cracker crumbs, oleo and almonds. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbles up good.

title: macaroni and beef casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and place into greased casserole dish.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil hen until well done (about 3 hours).
It should be ready to fall off the bones.
Debone and use only the lean meat.

title: zucchini fries
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour and seasonings.
Add egg, milk and oil; mix until smooth.
Cut zucchini in halves crosswise; cut each half into 8 wedges to form fries.
Remove seeds.
Dip each fry into flour mixture; drain off excess, then roll in crumbs to coat all sides.
Crush more cereal if needed.
Fry in deep, hot fat (360°) for about 2 minutes, or until golden.
Drain on paper towel.
Best served hot.

title: danish apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into greased 9 or 10-inch pie pan.
Bake until golden brown at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can serve with vanilla ice cream on the side.

title: peanut butter thumbprints
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine shortening, peanut butter, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg.
Beat just until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown beef in a sautepan and drain; remove from heat.
Add next 4 ingredients to beef.
Combine sour cream and cottage cheese in a separate bowl.
Place 1/2 the crushed chips in the bottom of a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add enough meat mixture to cover the chips, then cover the meat with 1/2 the sour cream mixture. Sprinkle with 1/2 the grated cheese.
Repeat layers; bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: biscuit cups
directions: Grease muffin tins.
Flatten biscuits in muffin tins.
Add cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: crock-pot chicken and dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Spray PAM into crock-pot. Pour chicken and dressing mixture into the crock-pot. Cover and cook on low for 4 hours. Serve while hot. Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: italian squash
directions: In 1-quart casserole, combine all ingredients and stir.
Cover and vent.
Microwave on High 5 minutes; let stand, covered, 1 minute.
Serves 2.
Contains 28 calories, 0.3 gm fat and 238 mg sodium.

title: quick monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle pecans in bottom of well-greased Bundt pan.
Set aside.
Combine sugars and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits into quarters. Roll each piece in cinnamon and sugar mixture and layer in pan. Combine brown sugar and butter.
Pour over dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Cool 10 minutes in pan, then invert onto serving plate.
Makes one 10-inch coffee cake.

title: dump cake
directions: In well greased 9 x 13-inch pan dump pineapple and juice and cherry pie filling, then fork together butter and cake mix.
Pour mixture on top.
Sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage supper
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
Add broth, cut up sausage, vinegar, potatoes and sugar.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
Add flour to thicken.
Cook to desired consistency.

title: oven baked potatoes
directions: Wash and cube potatoes.
Leave skins on.
Mix potatoes, olive oil and onion soup mix together in a bowl.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves about 4 people.

title: ruthie's yummy cookies
directions: Melt oleo in 10 x 16-inch pan.
Lay graham crackers over entire bottom of pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, nuts and coconut over crackers.
Drizzle 1/2 can of Eagle Brand milk over all.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cut when cool. "Quick and good."

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric beater.
Great on pumpkin bars or spice cake.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onion, celery and garlic in oil until light and yellow. Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer 40 minutes.
Add shrimp. Cook 10 minutes longer. Serve on hot steamed rice.

title: rice pudding
directions: Melt margarine in a 2-quart casserole. Beat eggs and add sugar, milk, vanilla and rice. Put mixture in casserole. Bake, uncovered, about one hour at 350°. Recipe may be halved.

title: hot sausage rolls
directions: Cut butter into 1/2-inch pieces.
Cut into flour until mixture is in pea-sized pieces.
Stir in cottage cheese until a stiff dough forms.
Add 2 to 3 teaspoons ice water.
Divide into 6 parts.
Roll each part to make a rectangle 6 inches long and 3 inches wide.
Spread with 1 teaspoon mustard.
Top with a sausage. Roll pastry around sausage, encasing it completely.
Brush with water to seal.
Seal ends.
Place seam side down on cookie sheet. Prick once or twice with fork.
Repeat for remaining sausages. Mix egg and milk.
Brush on pastry.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until nicely browned.
Slice into 1-inch pieces. Arrange on serving tray.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients except chicken in a saucepan. Simmer 10 minutes. Place chicken in a large baking pan. Pour half of the barbecue sauce over chicken and bake, uncovered, for 50 minutes, basting with remaining sauce every 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
Contains 260 calories.

title: tex-mex casserole
directions: Soak sweetbreads in salt water for half an hour.
Boil until well done, then remove skins and small pipes and cut into small pieces.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add to oil mixture, beating well.
Stir in pineapple and vanilla.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until done.
Invert pan.
Cool completely.

title: creamed veal
directions: Take a deep frying pan, put in the lard and the onion which has been chopped fine and brown.
Take the meat which has been washed and put it in the pan with 3 cups of water, salt and pepper and cook until meat is tender.
Add ketchup and let simmer for 10 minutes.
Take the milk and flour and put in a bowl.
Beat until the flour is dissolved.
Add to the meat in the pan and keep stirring until it comes to a boil and add more pepper.

title: date nut cake for diabetics
directions: Cream shortening, eggs, sweetener and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and spices.
Mix well.
Fold in dates, applesauce and nuts.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter and peanut butter together.
Add sugars. Beat in egg.
Stir in flour mixture. Bake at 375° until almost done.
With 1 minute to go, take out and put on kiss.
Put back in oven for a minute or so.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix pudding and syrup.
Gradually add milk and egg; blend. Add nuts.
Pour in shell.
Bake until firm at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Drain shrimp.
Mix softened cream cheese, mayonnaise and onions.
Then mix in shrimp.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Stir until cheese melts.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheets to 375°.
Boil sweet potatoes in water until easily pierced by fork.
Cool slightly.
Place cooked, peeled potatoes in large mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in butter and sugar; beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in spices, salt and Pet milk.
Pour into unbaked pie crusts.
Bake on preheated cookie sheet near center of oven for 70 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on wire rack.
Garnish with marshmallows, if desired.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: five pound beef brisket
directions: First day and night:
Marinate brisket in vinegar, oil, garlic, salt and pepper.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: Combine flour and brown sugar.
Cut in margarine to make a crumb mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Set aside 3/4 cup mixture for topping.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of 8 x 8 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes; cool slightly.

title: the new famous cheese ring
directions: Combine all ingredients except preserves and mix well.
Mold into ring and chill.
Fill with preserves to serve.
Can be frozen after taking out of ring.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly; refrigerate until serving time.
Yields 1 cup.

title: meringue
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until frothy but not stiff.
Gradually beat in sugar, one teaspoon at a time.
Continue to beat until mixture is glossy and stands in soft peaks.
Pile meringue on cooled filling in pie.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 5 minutes or until delicate brown.
Let cool at room temperature away from drafts.

title: party potatoes
directions: Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: popcorn
directions: Cook oleo, brown sugar, Karo syrup and salt over low heat 5 minutes; stir often. Pour over popped corn and peanuts (if desired); place in oven for 1 hour at 200°. Stir every 20 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except chicken, in large, flat casserole pan.
Lay chicken pieces on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 2 hours at 325°.
Freezable.

title: baked sour cream tacos
directions: Fry tortillas in very hot oil, not long because you have to be able to roll them.
Set aside.
Wilt onion in oil.
Add tomatoes and salsa (and peppers if you like).
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes. Butter a baking dish.
Roll each tortilla with sauce and a piece of Jack cheese inside.
Pour remaining sauce over tacos.
Put more pieces of cheese on top.
Cover whole thing with sour cream and bake about 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: green bean casserole deluxe
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese in casserole; mix well. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients together except peaches. Pour into a buttered pan. Pour can of peaches on top. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Blend pudding and Cool Whip. Add pineapple, marshmallows and almonds.
Stir.
Fold in oranges. Chill 2 hours.

title: blade steak casserole
directions: Six ways to improve on perfection.
Make your plain everyday burger a Good Burger!!

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Mix with sour cream the spinach and onion soup.
Place in greased casserole.
Top with crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pepper relish
directions: Cover with boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Drain. Cover again. Let come to a boil.
Drain again.
Add 3 tablespoons salt, 1 quart vinegar and 2 cups sugar.
Cook 15 minutes.
Seal.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix on a sheet of wax paper the flour, salt, paprika and black pepper.
Tenderize steak and cut into serving portions, dredging well in seasoned flour.
Heat 1/2 cup oil in heavy skillet and brown meat over medium heat.
Remove meat to platter.
Add to the skillet the remainder of seasoned flour and stir until browned. Add 2 cups of water and cook until slightly thickened.
Return steak to skillet.
Add chopped onions, tomato juice or tomatoes as you like.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is fork-tender.

title: chicken curry
directions: Mix together first eight ingredients.
Marinate chicken in mixture for at least 30 minutes, but preferably a few hours. Refrigerate.
Cook onion in shortening until it begins to color. If using mushrooms, add at this time and tomato and bay leaves. Cook 5 minutes.
Add chicken and marinade and mix together.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: pan braised salmon with green sauce
directions: In a large skillet, bring chicken broth and garlic cloves to a boil over medium heat.
Wash and trim the scallions, spinach and fresh dill.
Add the whole scallions, spinach, dill, lemon juice and salmon steaks to a boiling broth temperature.
Reduce the heat to low, cover and simmer until the salmon just flakes when tested with a fork, 5 to 7 minutes.
Carefully remove the salmon to a plate and cover loose to keep warm.
Remove the garlic, scallions, spinach and dill.
Puree the cooked vegetables.
Add butter, mustard, lemon zest, salt and pepper.
Add sour cream.
Serve.

title: croutons
directions: Mix together all ingredients in microwave dish, stirring to coat bread cubes with other ingredients.
Heat on Full power for 3 to 4 minutes, or until croutons are dry.
Stir once during heating.
Croutons will become crispier as they cool.

title: sunday spice cake
directions: Measure into mixing bowl (all measurements level) the first 10 ingredients.
Beat vigorously by hand or mixer (medium speed) for 2 minutes.
Stir in baking powder and soda.
Add eggs and milk. Mix thoroughly by hand or mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into two deep 9-inch layer pans.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for about 35 minutes.
Top with your favorite icing.
Makes 2 deep 9-inch layers.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken and onion soup.
Pour into buttered 2 quart casserole dish.
Place chicken breasts over rice and sprinkle with dry onion soup.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: fudge sundae pie
directions: Combine 1/4 cup corn syrup, brown sugar and margarine in medium-sized saucepan.
Cook over low heat until mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies, stirring until well coated.
Press evenly in 9-inch pie pan to form crust.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat all ingredients well, adding coconut last.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325° until golden brown.

title: apricot salad
directions: Combine pineapple, jello and sugar and dissolve over low heat. Blend in cream cheese with fork.
(Do not use mixer.)
Add apricots and fold in Cool Whip and pecans.
Chill.

title: herbed beef stew
directions: Brown meat in oil in a Dutch oven.
Add water, onion, seasonings and tomato paste.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Stir in potatoes, carrots and green pepper; simmer 30 minutes.
Add additional water if necessary.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: my mother's mac and cheese
directions: Combine macaroni, tomatoes, onion salt, pepper and 1 1/2 cups of the Cheddar cheese.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish. Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves four.

title: heavenly hot fudge sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, combine sugar, heavy cream and corn syrup. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently with a wooden spoon, for about 3 minutes or until sugar is dissolved. Stir in chocolate and butter with a wire whisk until completely blended and smooth, Remove from heat and stir in vanilla extract. Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: easy chili
directions: Crumble beef into a 2-quart ovenware casserole dish.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook in microwave 5 to 6 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover loosely with wax paper.
Cook in microwave for 12 to 13 minutes.

title: festive pecan pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients except pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with pecan halves.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
May add whipped topping.

title: toffee diamonds
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk.
Sift flour and cinnamon; add to butter mixture.
Spread dough evenly over greased 10 x 15-inch pan (a pizza roller smooths dough quickly).

title: mini cream cheese cakes
directions: Place 1 vanilla wafer in muffin cup.
In large bowl, add cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice, vanilla and eggs and mix well.
Fill to 1/2 from top in muffin cup.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 325° oven.
Cool.
Add pie filling, chill and serve.

title: salad maison
directions: In a food processor, process the egg and set aside (use steel blade).
With machine running, drop the garlic and process until minced.
Add parsley and process until chopped.
Add all remaining ingredients except egg and lettuce.
Process until well blended.
Toss with lettuce and sprinkle with egg on top.

title: white butter icing
directions: Cream butter and add sugar.
Add milk.
Beat until spreading consistency.
Stir in flavorings.

title: vegetable chili
directions: In a large crock-pot, combine tomatoes, paste, water and jalapeno peppers.
Stir in cumin, chili powder and red pepper. Add vegetables and apple.
Cook 3 hours to 1 day.
The longer the better.
One hour before serving, add kidney beans, a bit more chili powder and red pepper.
Serve with taco shells and sour cream.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust.

title: 7 grain bread(or whole wheat bread for bread making machine)
directions: Put all ingredients in bread pan in order given.
Bake according to instructions of your bread machine.

title: fast grilled potatoes
directions: Lay potatoes on microwave-safe dish. Spray each potato with Pam spray. Sprinkle each potato with garlic salt, paprika, dill weed and Parmesan cheese. Cover potatoes with plastic, leaving a place for air to escape.
Cook on High for 10 to 15 minutes. Place on grill until browned on both sides of sliced potatoes, 10 minutes or so.
Very good when mashed with butter and sour cream topping it off.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Cream sugar with the shortening.
Add milk, egg and vanilla extract; beat well.

Add mixture of flour, baking powder and salt. Add orange extract and cinnamon. Stir in chopped cranberries. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Boil macaroni in salted water and drain.
Combine all ingredients and put in buttered casserole dish.
Top with crushed crackers and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: herbed green beans
directions: Cook beans in 2 cups boiling water for 10 to 15 minutes, covered, until tender-crisp.
Combine herbs in a small bowl.
Saute chopped onions and garlic in oil, adding herbs, then sunflower seeds.
Add to cooked beans.
Season to taste and toss lightly. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil, peel and dice potatoes.
Boil and chop eggs.
Dice cucumber, green pepper and onion.
Half and slice radishes and sweet pickles thin.
Toss all ingredients together; set covered in refrigerator.
Cream mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar and canned milk until smooth.
Add to vegetable mixture gradually.
Use amount needed to make potato salad preferred moisture.

title: red cabbage
directions: Slice cabbage like for cole slaw. Slice apples and onions. Put in kettle; add vinegar, sugar and water. Cover and cook about 1 hour. Season with salt, pepper and butter.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Save a little cheese to place on top.
Grease an iron skillet and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: catfish stew
directions: Heat oil and add onions. Cook until tender, then add soup. Use enough water to clean out soup cans, then add ketchup and use enough water to clean bottles. Add salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce. Bring to a slow boil. Stir bottom and turn down heat to simmer. Add fish and cook for 1 hour. Stir occasionally. This feeds approximately 62 people? This recipe can be shortened to 1/2 or 1/4, etc.

title: hot chips sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes and peppers and mix with chopped onions.
Mix all together.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Pack into hot sterilized jars and seal.
Yields 7 pints.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Mix all well and store in refrigerator.

title: texas style corn
directions: Mix ingredients in a saucepan and stir over low heat until cheese begins to melt.
Pour into a small casserole and bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Remove bread crust.
Roll each slice thin with rolling pin. Mix cheese, seasonings and sour cream; spread on slices.
Put asparagus spear on edge of bread and roll jelly roll style.
Put seam side down on cookie sheet; brush with melted butter.
Brown lightly on both sides under broiler.
Slice each roll into bite size pieces.
These can be frozen (don't thaw).

title: chicken marengo
directions: In large skillet, brown chicken in shortening; pour off fat. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Cook over low heat 45 minutes or until tender.
Stir now and then.
Uncover.
Cook until desired consistency.
Serves 6.

title: caramel delight
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
While cake is hot, punch holes with toothpick and pour a mixture of Eagle Brand milk and caramel topping over hot cake.
Let cool completely.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with Heath bar shavings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; strain off grease.
Combine cheese soup and milk.
Place vegetables, cheese soup mixture and hamburger in large casserole dish.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a greased casserole.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: bean sprout and sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine and boil for 3 minutes the first 8 ingredients.
Pour boiled liquid over onion, celery and pepper.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: shrimp linguine
directions: Prepare linguine according to package directions.
In large skillet over medium-high heat, cook shrimp, mushrooms and garlic in butter 5 minutes until shrimp turn opaque, stirring frequently. Drain linguine.
In large serving bowl, combine shrimp mixture, linguine, 3 tablespoons Romano cheese and salt.
Toss gently to coat well.
Top with remaining cheese and cracked pepper to taste. Garnish.

title: bananaberry pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Mix in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Stir in 3/4 cup of the strawberries.
Pour into pie crust; chill until firm, about 15 minutes.

title: chocolate lover's dessert
directions: Make brownie mix as directed in a high-sided pan; cool.
Do not cut the brownies.
Prepare instant pudding as directed, then add cream cheese and spread evenly over cooled brownies.
Spread cherry pie filling over the pudding; refrigerate until set.

title: corn pudding
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Mix well with all the other ingredients (except sour cream and Cheddar).
Place in casserole dish.
Cover with sour cream and Cheddar cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese. Add vanilla and mix well. Sift together sugar and cocoa. Mix well. Add nuts. Pour in buttered pan. Cool and store in refrigerator. Cut into squares.

title: pickled beets
directions: Boil corn ready to eat.
Cut corn off cob; fill dry canning jars 2/3 full.
In cooker, bring to a boil 1 cup salt and 1 gallon water.
Fill jars to ring, not to full seal.

title: elegant dessert
directions: Mix all and press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: sea island bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch square cake pan.
Melt butter in a 2-quart saucepan over very low heat.
Remove from heat.
Blend in sugars and water.
Stir in flour, then add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add nuts, coconut and chocolate pieces and stir to combine.
Pour into prepared pan and bake 30 minutes.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Mix all together; put in a graham cracker pie crust.
Freeze.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Place ingredients in order given in greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Salt and pepper each layer.
Bake 2 hours at 300° to 325°.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into shell.
Let chill for 3 hours.
Top with cherries.

title: nanaimo (3 layered) cookies
directions: Put 1/2 cup butter, granulated sugar, unsweetened chocolate and vanilla in top of double boiler.
Cook over boiling water until well blended.
Add egg; cook 5 minutes more, stirring.
Add crumbs, nuts and coconut.
Press into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (or 9 x 9 x 2-inch for thick cookies).
Cool.
Chill in fridge 15 minutes.
While 1st layer is in fridge, cream 1/2 cup butter until fluffy.
Beat in pudding mix and milk.
Add confectioners sugar gradually and beat until smooth.
Spread over 1st layer.
Chill 15 minutes.
While 2nd layer is in fridge, melt semi-sweet chocolate and 1 tablespoon butter over low heat.
Spread over 2nd layer. Chill until firm.
Cut in 1-inch squares.
Must be kept cold until ready to serve.

title: spoon bread
directions: Stir meal into rapidly boiling milk.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly; don't scorch.
Remove from heat and allow to cool.
Add well beaten eggs, salt, baking powder and butter; beat with electric mixer for 15 minutes.
You might be tempted to cut this step short, but don't; this is really a souffle and it won't rise as well.
Pour into well greased casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: milk punch
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat milk, sherbet and ice cream until frothy.
Pour into punch bowl.
Stir in soda.
Serve immediately. Serves 20.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes and put in a deep dish pie pan or quiche pan. Add chili peppers and spread mayonnaise over peppers.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: texas ranger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and blend.
Stir in corn flakes and oats.
Gradually add flour, soda, baking powder and salt, sifted together.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate-amaretto cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle chocolate wafer crumbs in bottom of a 7-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.
Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add cream cheese and next 7 ingredients, processing until smooth.
Add egg and blend.
Fold in chocolate morsels. Slowly pour mixture over crumbs in pan.
Bake at 300° for 65 to 70 minutes or until cheesecake is set.
Let cool in pan on wire rack. Cover and chill at least 8 hours.
Remove sides of pan, transfer cheesecake to a serving platter.
Yield:
12 servings (about 200 calories per serving.)

title: macaroni and meatballs
directions: Combine eggs, bread crumbs, onion, green pepper, parsley, 1/2 of the oregano, garlic salt and dash of pepper.
Add ground beef; mix well.
Shape into 24 meatballs.
Bake in shallow pan, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Combine dry cheese mix, sour cream, 1/2 oregano and milk.
Stir in cooked macaroni.
Turn into 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange meatballs atop.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: cheddar herb snack bread
directions: In a large bowl combine 2 cups flour, undissolved yeast, herbs, garlic and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt; stir in hot water.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed (scrape bowl occasionally).
Add eggs and 1/2 cup flour; beat 2 minutes with spoon.
Stir in 1 cup cheese and enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Cover and let rest 20 minutes.

title: jew bread
directions: Melt oleo on low heat, add sugar, let cool.
Add flour and eggs one at a time.
Add flavoring and nuts.
Mix well, pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
