In a saucepan, combine 1 cup butter, 1/4 cup cocoa, water, 1/2 cup buttermilk and eggs.
Stir constantly over low heat until mixture bubbles.
In a large bowl, mix sugar, flour and baking soda.
Stir hot mixture into dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla. Spread mixture evenly into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 25 minutes until firm to touch in center.
Cool.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients.
Put in a pan and cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Put ketchup on top and let cook for 1/2 hour.

title: healthy breakfast drink
directions: Mix orange juice and bananas in blender until thick.

title: gramp's chocolate fudge cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Alternate flour mixture and milk.
Put in vanilla.
Mix well.
Use 3 or 4 round pans.
Fill 1/2 full with batter in each pan to make several layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baker's boiled frosting
directions: Cook in saucepan the milk and flour; stir until it turns to a thick paste.
Then cool.
Put in mixer the shortening, sugar, butter and vanilla and beat until light and fluffy.
Add cooled paste to mixer and beat until consistency of whipped cream.

title: hearty lentil soup(yields 4 servings)
directions: Bring lentils to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for about 1 hour.
Add chopped onions, celery and carrots; stir while simmering 10 minutes.
Add chopped tomatoes and minced garlic; simmer 3 minutes.
Add parsley, tomato paste, thyme and salt, if desired.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Stir in olive oil and serve.

title: cheese scalloped corn casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir onion in 2 tablespoons margarine until onion is tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour and seasonings; cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in corn, egg and cheese.
Pour into ungreased 1-quart casserole. Combine cracker crumbs and 1 tablespoon melted margarine; sprinkle evenly over corn mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cranberry arctic freeze
directions: Cream softened	cream cheese and sugar; add mayonnaise. Fold in	mashed	cranberry
sauce,
drained pineapple, whipped cream and nuts.
Pour in 9 x 5
x
3-inch
loaf
pan
or Pyrex dish. Freeze until firm.	Cut in	squares
and
serve on lettuce. Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: green beans au gratin
directions: Melt butter; add onion, flour, liquids and seasonings to make sauce.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese.
Place beans in greased casserole; pour sauce over all.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and paprika.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat 4 eggs; add sugar gradually, then add 5 1/2 cups of half and half and 2 cups whipping cream.
Add 2 tablespoons vanilla and dash of salt for taste.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.
Makes one gallon.

title: calzone
directions: Brown sausage with sliced green pepper and onion.
Rinse and drain well.
Mix meat with cheese.
Chill.
Divide loaves into 4 pieces, total 8.
Roll each piece in a circle.
Put approximately 1/2 cup of meat mixture on one-half of circle.
Fold other half over the meat.
Pinch ends together well.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spanish pork chopsceres, california
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper.
Brown meat in hot shortening.
Drain.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Add egg and milk. Mix lightly. Stir in chopped onion. Drop batter by teaspoonfuls into deep hot oil. Cook until golden brown. Yield: 2 dozen.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Stir together milk, egg yolks and lemon juice and place in graham cracker crust.
You may top this with whip cream or Cool Whip or you may make a meringue out of the egg whites. Refrigerate.

title: chicken and brown rice
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry.
Saute rice in frying pan in 2 tablespoons of butter just until brown, along with the pepper and onion.
Place in baking dish.
Add consomme; mix.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Cover with can of golden mushroom soup. Bake, covered, at 350° to 400° for approximately 1 hour, until chicken is done and rice is tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: microwave raisin bread pudding
directions: In ungreased 2-quart round microproof dish, mix bread and raisins.
Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt until well blended. In 4-cup glass measure, heat milk and butter on High for 4 1/2 to 5 minutes or until steaming hot.
Gradually stir in egg mixture. Pour over bread and raisins.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with waxed paper.
Center may be slightly soft but will set as pudding cooks.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: rocky road
directions: Partially melt chocolate over hot water.
Remove from heat and beat until smooth.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Spread in buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill.
When firm, cut into squares.

title: chicken tremendous
directions: Combine rice and soup; add water.
Place mixture in 10 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle soup mix over chicken.
Cover with foil; do not open foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours and 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: cheese scalloped potatoes
directions: Oil large shallow baking dish.
Without peeling, thinly slice potatoes.
Place half of potatoes in dish.
Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese, 1 1/2 tablespoons margarine, half of sesame seed and paprika.
Repeat layers.
Pour milk over.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.
Cover the last 15 minutes.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan mix flour, granulated sugar, 1/4 cup cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Stir in milk and oil until well blended.
(Stir in nuts if using.)

title: hollyberry punch
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over ice in punch bowl. Float slices of lemon or orange for garnish. Makes about 2 3/4 quarts or 12 servings.

title: harriet's peach cobbler
directions: Put the sliced peaches in baking dish. Cover with 1 cup sugar. Dot with butter and put in a 375° oven until the batter is prepared.
Sift dry ingredients. Beat egg and add hot water, then dry mixture and vanilla.
Take peaches from oven, cover with batter and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat and bake for 30 minutes. Serve with cream or hard sauce.
It is very good with apples, too.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cut up tortillas.
Put 1/2 chicken on bottom of pan in layers. Add 1/3 of chicken, cheese and chilies.
Make 2 more layers. Pour diluted soup over this.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Cut baked potatoes in 1/2 lengthwise, without breaking skin. Scoop out inside and mash.
Season with salt, pepper, butter and chopped parsley.
Refill potato skins.
Moisten tops with a few drops of milk.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Brown in 400° oven.

title: light 'n' luscious chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9-inch square or round baking pan with cooking spray.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cocoa, cornstarch, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
In a medium bowl with a wire whisk or fork, stir water, egg, egg white, corn syrup and corn oil.
Gradually stir into dry ingredients until smooth.

title: make-believe marble
directions: Put water in a container.
Sprinkle plaster on water until a thick, creamy mixture forms.
Add glue to plaster mixture.
Drip some tempera over the plaster and stir until the mixture looks streaked.
Pour into a mold and let harden.

title: mediterranean skillet chicken
directions: Heat oil in 12 inch nonstick skillet over medium high heat. Cook chicken in oil 5 minutes, turning once, until brown. Stir in remaining ingredients. Heat to boiling; reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until juice of chicken is no longer pink when centers of thickest pieces are cut. This has 6 grams carbohydrates.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place in microwave oven and cook 7 to 8 minutes, stirring well after 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Blend well with syrup.
Return to microwave 1 to 2 minutes.
Add baking soda.
Stir until mixture is light and foamy.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
When cool, break into pieces.
Yields 1 pound.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Rub frozen dough with olive oil and let defrost.
When thawed roll out dough approximately 18 x 12-inches.
Sprinkle with cheese and pepperoni.
Roll tightly like a jelly roll to make an 18-inch loaf.
Pinch open ends well to close bread completely.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 350° approximate 40 minutes or until lightly browned.
Try other stuffings (broccoli, cheese and ham, sausage, herbs, etc.).

title: chocolate filled caramel buns
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 9-inch square pan.
Spread frosting over bottom of pan.
Press pecans into frosting.
Separate dough into 20 biscuits.
Wrap 1 biscuit around each candy Kiss; pinch edges to seal.
Arrange filled biscuits over frosting and pecans. Bake at 375° for 28 to 32 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Makes 20 buns.

title: 3-in-1 dinner
directions: In 3-quart casserole, arrange chicken breasts (skin removed) in center, green beans on one side, potatoes on the other.
Combine margarine and garlic cheese mix.
Pour over all.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: marshmallow no cook frosting
directions: Beat the egg whites in large bowl and add salt.
Gradually add sugar, beating after each addition, until smooth and glossy. Slowly add the Karo syrup and beat until it stands up firm in peaks.
Fold in vanilla last very slowly.
Frost cooled cake.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk with the lemon juice.
Blend well or stir well.
Add 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Place in crust.
Spread the other Cool Whip on top and chill.
(No eggs.)

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes and bacon.
Set aside. Fry onion in bacon drippings until light brown. Add flour and blend.
Add sugar, salt, vinegar and water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Mix in celery, parsley and frankfurters.
Pour mixture over potatoes and bacon.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Serve hot.

title: cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add sugar, vanilla and baking powder.
Mix gently.
Add chopped pecans and Ritz crackers.
Pour into a greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: pretzel salad
directions: First Layer:
Mix pretzels, butter and 3 teaspoons sugar in a bowl.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and spread completely over bottom in thin layer.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Set aside to cool.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar, then fold in other ingredients. Put into a mold and freeze for several hours.

title: chopped chicken liver
directions: Saute chicken livers in chicken fat after onions are completly sauted.
Add salt and pepper.
Additional fat may need to be added.
In food processor slice eggs.
Then put all ingredients together including liquid and blend.
Chill overnight.
Serve with triscuit crackers.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla and zucchini. Blend in dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or 2 bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and lard into crumbs, then add egg.
Mix in other ingredients.
This recipe is enough for 4 pies.

title: sunday brunch casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread, if desired.
Butter bread.
Cube and place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer cheese, sausage, red pepper and onion over the bread.
In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add soup, milk, mustard and pepper.
Pour over bread mixture. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Salt and pepper ground beef.
Press into a 9-inch square dish. Spread soup over and then place Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350°, uncovered for 1 hour.

title: tangy pea salad
directions: Thaw peas.
In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, yogurt, vinegar, pickle relish and mustard.
Shred lettuce.
Cut onion into half rounds by halving onion and slicing each half.

title: apple-oatmeal cookies
directions: In saucepan, combine fruits, nuts, granulated sugar and 2 tablespoons water.
Cook and stir until thick and apple is tender, about 10 minutes.
Cream butter and brown sugar until fluffy. Beat in eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients; add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats.
Reserve 3/4 cup dough. Drop remainder from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet; make depression in center and top with apple filling.
Top off with reserved dough.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 36.

title: strawberry cream squares
directions: Dissolve strawberry
flavored gelatin in boiling water. Add the frozen	strawberries
that are partially thawed;
stir occasionally until	thawed.
Add
the
crushed
pineapple
and bananas.
Pour half into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch casserole or baking pan; chill firm.
Spread
evenly
with
the
sour cream.
Pour remaining gelatin on top and chill until firm.

title: easy delight
directions: Measure cold milk.
Add instant pudding mix.
Put into a shaker and shake 1 to 2 minutes.
Place topping into a small pitcher, then fold in prepared pudding.
Chill thoroughly.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups or 5 servings.

title: chocolate amaretto cheesecake
directions: In a bowl, combine chocolate crumbs, almonds, sugar and softened butter.
Pat mixture onto bottom and sides of a buttered 9 1/2-inch spring-form pan.
Then cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add heavy cream, Amaretto and vanilla. Beat until light.
Pour batter into spring-form pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Combine sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Spread on cake and bake for 5 minutes more.
Cool on rack completely and chill overnight.
Remove sides of pan and transfer cake to a stand.
Press sliced blanched almonds, lightly toasted around top edge.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place thinly sliced apples in a bowl. Add 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon, cornstarch and lemon juice.
Mix lightly and pour into a buttered 9-inch pan.
Blend remaining sugar, flour, salt and butter to a crumbly consistency.
Add the nuts and blend.
Sprinkle over the apples.
Bake 45 minutes or until crust is brown.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream. Makes 6 servings.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Add more oatmeal if too soft. Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: potatoes royal(microwave)
directions: Crumble bacon and set aside.
Slice potatoes into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add onion and water.
Cover with lid and microwave on High 12 to 14 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking time. Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to potatoes; mix lightly to combine.
Sprinkle bacon over top.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes to heat through.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter and margarine.
Add white and brown sugar. Mix well; add eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in flour.
Drop by teaspoon. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: john's caramel cake
directions: Make cake as directed on box and bake.
After cake is done, poke holes in it with a wooden spoon while it's still hot.
Pour on sweetened milk and caramel topping.
Let cool and put Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate.

title: chuck wagon skillet dinner
directions: Put in a large covered skillet.
Cook onions until tender. Add meat, sprinkle over salt and pepper.
Brown slowly, turning often.
Put in layers and add cheese, celery and olives.
Add noodles.
Pour over tomatoes and water.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Do not remove cover.
Turn heat to low.
Simmer 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fudge nut pie
directions: Place all ingredients, except nuts, in bowl and mix well.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: grandma's squash pie
directions: Combine squash, sugar, butter, spices and salt.
Stir in eggs and milk.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes. Knife should come out clean when tested.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Chop vegetables and meat into bite-size pieces.
Combine all ingredients and pour into a Dutch oven, covering tightly.
Bake in 300° oven for six hours.
Shred with a fork and serve on hard rolls.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix oleo, Crisco, eggs, white sugar, brown sugar and vanilla. Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine the coconut, crushed corn flakes, oats and nuts into other ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi(microwave)
directions: Set power at High.
In round baking dish, heat butter and garlic 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until butter is melted.
Add lemon juice, parsley, salt and pepper; stir in shrimp.
Set power at Medium.
Heat, covered, 2 to 4 minutes, or until shrimp is done, stirring once.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes; sprinkle with paprika before serving (if desired).
Serves 4.

title: hamburger macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Brown the ground beef; drain.
Add soups, green pepper, pimiento, macaroni and the ground beef. Place half the mixture in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with half the cheese and onions.
Top with remaining macaroni mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining onions, bake 5 additional minutes.

title: chicken rice skillet
directions: Brown
chicken in margarine;
add water; cover.
Simmer for 25 minutes.
Take chicken out; add rice, soup and vegetables. Bring
to
boil.
Take
off
heat
and
let stand for 5 minutes. Serve on plate with chicken on top.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine margarine, oil and sugars; cream well.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix together.
Add dry ingredients.
Roll in balls; flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together flour, cream of tartar, baking soda, salt and nutmeg.
Use 1/2 cup of the flour mixture to coat the blueberries. In a mixing bowl, cream the sugar, margarine, egg and lemon together.
Alternate dry ingredients with milk into the mixing bowl.
Add the blueberries and fold into mixture.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: reuben dip
directions: Mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve on cocktail bread.

title: buttermilk fried fillets
directions: Cut fillets into serving size portions.
Place portions in a single layer in shallow dish.
Pour buttermilk over fish and let stand for 30 minutes, turning once.

Combine biscuit mix and salt. Remove fish from buttermilk and roll in biscuit mix. Fry in moderately hot cooking oil for 4 to 5 minutes or until brown. Turn carefully and fry 4 to 5 minutes longer or until fish is brown and flakes easily when tested with a fork. Drain on paper towel. Serve with lemon wedges or malt vinegar.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: christmas wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Remove and discard cinnamon sticks.
Serve hot.
Yields 14 cups.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle over it the graham cracker crumbs, then sprinkle chocolate chips, then coconut.
Drizzle sweetened condensed milk.
Put 1 cup nutmeats on top and bake at 350°.
Cool and cut.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Into top of a double boiler, over boiling water, add all ingredients.
Keep stirring constantly.
Begins to thicken in about 5 minutes.
Makes 1 cup.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Cook syrup and sugar to boiling; remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Pat into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips in double boiler and spread onto the Rice Krispies mixture.
Cut into squares.

title: warmed cranberry brie
directions: Combine cranberry sauce, brown sugar, rum extract or orange extract and nutmeg.
Peel off top rind of Brie round, leaving 1/4 inch rim.
Top Brie with cranberry mixture and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake in 500° oven for 4 to 5 minutes.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: cheese casserole
directions: Pam spray large baking dish.
Butter French bread and place buttered side down in dish.
Cut onion slices to cover bread. Saute onions in oil or butter but do not brown.
Add the egg mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: boursin cheese
directions: Crush garlic and add juice to all ingredients.
Mix well and place in a plastic wrap lined mold or dish.
Chill overnight. Remove when hard and coat with black pepper.
Very good served with Wheat Thins.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Peel and slice apples and place in baking dish.
In a small bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add unbeaten egg and mix until crumbly.
Pour over apple slices.
Melt butter and pour over top of crumb mixture slowly.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Making sure water has been drained from all, mix chopped spinach, sausage (or hamburg), cottage cheese, garlic, juice of 1/2 lemon, cheese, salt, pepper, oregano and egg.
Cook shells ahead of time and chill.

title: chicken soup
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Stir in celery, carrot and onion; coat with butter.
Add chicken.
Cook over low heat, covered, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove chicken, cut into small cubes and return to pan.
Add broth.
Bring to a boil and add noodles and corn.
Simmer for 15 minutes or until noodles are done.
Season with pepper and salt, if needed.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Mix together and place in greased muffin tins.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375 for 9 to 11 minutes, until golden brown. Yield: 12.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Cook beef and onion; drain. Stir in salt. Spread in greased 9-inch pie plate. Sprinkle with cheese. Stir remaining ingredients with fork until blended. Pour into plate. Bake 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: white mountain frosting
directions: In small saucepan combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cover. Heat to boiling (rolling) over medium heat.

Remove cover and boil rapidly without stirring to 242° on candy thermometer or until syrup spins a 6 to 8-inch thread when dropped from a spoon. As mixture boils, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Pour hot syrup very slowly in a thin stream into the beaten egg whites, beating constantly on medium speed.
Beat on high speed until stiff peaks form.
Add vanilla.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Melt margarine, sugar and cream cheese, then beat until smooth.
Add 1/2 cup sweet milk.
Beat Dream Whip with 1/2 cup of sweet milk until thick.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix in 3 tablespoons sugar and pretzels.
Bake for 8 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.

title: easy peanut butter chocolate fudge
directions: In a large pan, melt peanut butter chips and 1 cup condensed milk with 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanuts.
Spread mixture into waxed paper lined 8-inch square pan.
In small saucepan, melt chocolate morsels and remaining condensed milk with butter.
Spread mixture over top of peanut mixture.
Chill 2 hours, until firm.
Cut into squares. This is quite rich.
I recommend cutting it into small pieces.

title: cranberry corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Stir in egg, milk and oil.
Fold in cranberries and spoon into greased muffin tin.
Bake 20 minutes.
Yield:
12 muffins.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix together and bake in four layers (or two layers and slice them).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes for 4 layers, 20 to 30 minutes for 2 layers.

title: pork liver
directions: Fry liver in fat very slowly; add flour and onion and cook 20 to 30 minutes.
Add water, vinegar, salt and pepper and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Put pineapple in 9 x 13-inch pan; add blueberries.
Add the 3/4 cup sugar over
this.
Sprinkle
the dry cake mix over the blueberries.
Add 1
cup pecans, then sprinkle the 1/4 cup sugar over the pecans.
Bake
at
for
35 or 40 minutes. Serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Grease and flour muffin tins or use baking cups.
Mix all ingredients together, beat for 2 minutes.
Fill muffin into 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Can also be baked in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot shrimp canapes
directions: Mix Cheddar cheese with enough mayonnaise to insure clumpy consistency.
Fold in shrimp.
Season with garlic powder.
Spread on Triscuits, heaping helpings.
Broil until cheese melts and becomes bubbly.
Never fails to make a hit!

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and use as a dip for raw vegetables.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Use mixer; soften cream cheese with milk and some Worcestershire sauce.
Add lemon juice and onion.
When smooth, add chopped beef.

title: brown trout with oatmeal
directions: Season trout with lemon juice and salt and pepper to taste. Dip in flour, then egg.
Press lightly in oatmeal flakes.
Put in hot pan with melted butter and fry about 5 minutes per side. Garnish with lemon slices and pour melted butter over trout.

title: traveling cupcakes
directions: Mix well and spread over last layer of crackers.
Cut and serve.

title: rich and zesty mushroom soup
directions: Saute onions in 2 tablespoons butter for a few minutes.
Add mushrooms, dill, soy sauce and paprika.
Continue to saute until vegetables are barely tender, then add 1/2 cup of stock and reduce heat to simmer.
Melt remaining butter in saucepan.
Whisk in flour and cook 2 minutes or so.
Gradually add milk and cook over low heat until thick, stirring often.
Stir thickened mixture into mushroom mixture and add remaining stock.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add lemon pepper and cream or yogurt just before serving.

title: easy spaghetti bake
directions: Fry bacon; add onions, garlic and meat.
Cook.
Stir in tomato sauce, water, salt and chili powder; simmer, covered, 5 minutes. Stir in olives.
Break half the spaghetti into greased casserole dish and spread evenly.
Cover with half of sauce.
Sprinkle with half of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fruit-in-crust cheesecake pie
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Reserve 1 cup.
Pat remainder on bottom and sides of 9-inch pan.
Spread preserves over crust.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs over preserves.
Blend in small mixer bowl the next 4 ingredients.
Whipped cream is mixed in a small bowl after it has been whipped.
Spoon into cream mixture.
Crust should be baked at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Spoon creamed mixture into baked crust.
Refrigerate.

title: tuna-cream dip
directions: In medium bowl flake tuna; stir in all ingredients until mixed.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: kielbasa and sauerkraut
directions: Cut kielbasa into pieces.
Brown in 350° oven.
Add the sauerkraut, onion and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: garden fresh garlic pizza
directions: Coat both sides of pizza shell (lightly) with oil.
Spread on a thin layer of Ricotta cheese.
Evenly distribute garlic slices. Next, cover with zucchini slices, followed with tomato slices. Sprinkle with Italian seasoning and garlic salt; top with Romano cheese.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 18 minutes or until bottom of shell is light brown.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: almond joy bar
directions: Boil potatoes, mash and mix in powdered sugar and coconut. Refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Shape ball of mixture around an almond.
Melt chocolate chips.
Dip ball in chocolate.
Cool and enjoy.

title: jenny's green bean and potatoes
directions: Dice potatoes (squares).
Slice onion.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, add potatoes, green beans, onion and cream of mushroom soup.
Mix until potatoes and green beans are coated. Add 1/2 cup milk. Crunch French's onions over top and bake until potatoes are soft at 350°.

title: farmhouse ribs
directions: Trim off excess fat from ribs.
In a large skillet, brown ribs in oil.
Place in a roasting pan.
Place apple wedges and onion rings over ribs in pan.
Combine all ingredients for sauce.
Baste ribs with sauce.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Uncover.
Pour remaining sauce over ribs.
Bake at 350° for another 40 to 50 minutes or until ribs are no longer pink near the bones.

title: grandma nora's pineapple bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.	Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in pineapple and lemon juice.
Fold in the bread cubes.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish. Bake uncovered for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.	Sprinkle cinnamon over top.

title: pull taffy
directions: Combine ingredients; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to hard crack stage or until it will spin a thread (375°).
Pour out on cold buttered platter.
Pull edges to center and centers out. Pull until white; cut into portions.

title: jacki's cinnamon toast
directions: Put toast in the toaster for 2 minutes.
Take it out.
Put butter, then cinnamon.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers into salad bowl.
Cream mayonnaise and milk together, enough to coat cucumbers.
Add dash of salt and pepper to taste.
Onions may be added if you like.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Put hot carrots into blender or food processor.
While mixing, add margarine, eggs, flour, vanilla, cinnamon, sugar and baking powder.
Put into a 2-quart casserole dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler. While chocolate is melting, cream oleo and sugar; add eggs. Add flour and milk alternately. Then add 1/2 cup of the hot water to the melted chocolate. Bring the other 1/2 cup water to a boil and add soda. Stir in chocolate immediately. Slowly add the chocolate to the batter and add vanilla. Bake in greased and floured 9 x 12 pan about 1 hour at 325°. Pulls away from sides of pan when done. Cake is at its best the third day. Not necessary to ice (but much better).

title: okra creole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer over low heat 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Okra can be cut up if you prefer and onion can be sliced into half rings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix together.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with cheese or croutons, etc.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli (cooked) in the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Pull apart chicken and arrange on top of broccoli. Mix soup and mayonnaise together and spread over meat. Cover with cheese and seasoned croutons.
Bake approximately 45 minutes at 325°, until bubbly and hot.

title: chicken ravioli
directions: Cook onion, peppers and celery until tender in small amount of broth.
Salt and pepper to taste.

Put layers of noodles in baking dish, layer of chicken, then layer of mixed vegetables and pimento, then a thin layer of cheese, then layer of noodles. Continue until all is used with thick layer of cheese on top.
Put in medium hot (350°) oven until cheese is melted.
Serve warm.

title: "mounds" like candy
directions: Mix the mashed potatoes with the powdered sugar; roll into balls.
Dip into a mixture made by mixing the chocolate chips and milk chocolate in a double boiler.
Add a small amount of wax to keep thin.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels and Pet milk.
Put this caramel mixture over what you have just baked.
Toss chocolate chips on top with rest of dough and bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook the chicken breasts and broccoli.
Mix soup, sour cream, cheese, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Drain broccoli and arrange on the bottom of a 3-quart casserole dish sprayed with Pam. Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Skin and bone the chicken.
Pull into pieces and place over the broccoli.
Add more Parmesan cheese, then top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: velma's treats
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease pan.
Melt butter.
Add sugar and stir well.
Add egg and vanilla; stir well.
Sift flour and baking powder into egg mixture.
Mix well.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes in a square 8-inch pan.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Place layer of tortillas in shallow casserole dish.
Layer ingredients and top with another layer of tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes
or until tortillas brown.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain off grease.
Slice bread 1/2-inch thick.
Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish, greased.
Lay bread in dish and sprinkle sausage over top.
Reserve about 1/4 to sprinkle on top.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over sausage.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Lay cheese on top and rest of sausage and bake until cheese melts, about 5 minutes.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Cut celery, onions and peppers into small pieces.
Put celery and peppers in 6 quarts of water and boil 10 minutes.
Put flour and oil in skillet and brown until dark. (This will be called your rue.)
Add onions and garlic to taste.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add the flour mixture (rue), shrimp, crab meat, tomatoes and crab boil to the celery and pepper soup mix and cook for 30 minutes.

title: angel cornsticks
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder, yeast, salt and soda.
Then mix eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Add to dry ingredients. Stir well and spoon into well-greased cast-iron cornstick pan. Fill 1/2 full.
Bake at
450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: coon hunters cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 25 minutes.
While cake is hot, make holes in cake and pour frosting over cake.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain first four ingredients and add onion, celery and green pepper.
Marinate in vinegar, oil and sugar.
Add salt and pepper. Marinate overnight.

title: almond cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease two large baking sheets. In large bowl of electric mixer, combine eggs and almond paste.
At medium speed, beat 5 minutes or until mixture is light and creamy. Add cookie mix; at low speed, beat until mixture forms a dough. Roll rounded teaspoonful of dough into a ball.
On a sheet of waxed paper, place sugar.
Roll dough ball in sugar to coat.
Place ball on prepared baking sheet; flatten slightly with palm of hand. Gently press an almond into center of dough.
Repeat with remaining dough, placing cookies about 1 inch apart on prepared baking sheets.
Bake 12 minutes or until cookies are golden.
With metal spatula, transfer cookies to wire rack to cool.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: baked cheese grits
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking dish.
Slowly stir grits and salt into brisk boiling water. Reduce heat to medium-low and cover.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes or until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add small amount of grits to beaten egg.
Return grits to mixture in pan. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat an additional minute or until cheese is melted.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until top is set and lightly puffed.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: irish cream
directions: Thoroughly mix together.
After all ingredients are well blended, add 1 1/2 to 2 cups whiskey.
Refrigerate and serve.
May be stored in freezer for later use.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar with hand mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, salt and baking powder.
Add cocoa. (If making plain pound cake, omit cocoa and increase vanilla to 2 teaspoons.) Add flour and milk alternately, ending with milk. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: creamed corn
directions: Melt butter and cream cheese together. Add sugar.
After melted, add corn and cook until hot.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix all together.
Serve with raw carrots, celery, cucumbers, cauliflower and radishes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine pepper, onion and cukes.
Sprinkle with salt and celery seed.
Let stand one hour in refrigerator, then drain. Pour vinegar and sugar mixture over cucumbers.
Place in containers.
Refrigerate.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in salt water until tender.
Drain and mash. Add cream cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper, mixing well.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with pats of butter.
Cover. Potatoes may be stored in refrigerator for several days.
Before baking, sprinkle with paprika and bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through.

title: spiced salmon
directions: Place in pan the liquid from the salmon with the butter, lemon juice, water and cloves.
When it begins to boil, add salmon (free from skin and bones).
Season with cayenne pepper and salt to taste.
Boil several minutes; serve on crackers.

title: frances wright's bread pudding
directions: Tear the bread into chunks.
Add enough milk to the eggs to make 2 cups liquid.
Add the vanilla to the milk mixture.
Add bread to milk mixture; soak well.
Place in greased casserole. Add fruit.
(Frances likes to use 2 or 3 fruits at a time; one favorite mixture is pears, raisins and apples.)
Dot with butter; sprinkle well with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for at least 30 minutes.

title: caramels
directions: Put sugar, butter (margarine), syrup and half of milk into pan. Allow it to come to a boil.
Add remaining milk slowly.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Takes about 1 hour slow cooking. (First samples in water.)
Done when sample clicks against rim of glass but is still soft inside.
When done, add 1 tablespoon of vanilla or walnut flavoring.
Pour into buttered pan.
Allow to set until firm.
Cut in pieces.

title: cheese balls
directions: Combine.
Roll in pecans.
Rolls best if chilled first. Freezes well.
Makes 3 small balls or 2 large ones.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cream chicken and place in soup pot.
Add water and allow to boil a few minutes.
Skim soup carefully.
Add vegetables and seasonings.
Lower heat and cook slowly, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Remove onion and serve with matzo balls.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts into small chunks or strips (which ever you prefer).
Brown meat in oil.
Add water; cover and simmer 2 minutes.
Add pineapple and vegetables; bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer approximately 3 to 5 minutes, until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Stir in combined preserves, cornstarch, vinegar and soy sauce.
Bring to a boil and mixture is slightly thickened. Serve over hot rice.
Garnish with a few sprigs of fresh parsley. Serves 4.

title: praline-n-cream pies
directions: Brown coconut, butter and pecans; divide into pie shells, saving small amount to garnish top of pies.
Mix cream cheese and can milk well; fold in Cool Whip.
Put in pie shells; top pie with sprinkling of coconut mixture and swirl butterscotch topping.

title: 1-2-3 cake
directions: Make sure eggs, butter and Crisco are at room temperature. Cream together until light and fluffy, then add salt, baking powder, flour and milk.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Mix together butter, sugar and egg; set aside. Sift together baking powder, salt, flour and nutmeg.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix together and add rhubarb last.
Put in unbaked pie shell.

title: mexico chiquito punch
directions: Mix ingredients in a 1 gallon jug; fill until almost full with water.

title: hamburger milk gravy hash
directions: In a large skillet, sprayed with vegetable oil (like Pam), brown meat, onion and garlic.
Add chopped potatoes and mushrooms. Mix well to combine.
Continue cooking until potatoes start to brown.

title: best pie crust
directions: In Bowl #1 (larger bowl):
Mix flour and pinch salt.
Remove 1/3 of this mixture and place in bowl #2.
Add shortening by cutting with cutting tool or fingers to the remaining flour in bowl #1.
Cut to a real fine consistency.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, and salt.
Bring to a light boil, the water, margarine and cocoa.
Add eggs, sour cream and baking soda.
Combine with the flour mixture and mix well.
Pour into a 10 1/2 X 18 X 1 inch cookie sheet and bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: hamburger goo
directions: Brown meat, celery and onions.
Add 1 tablespoon of fat if meat is lean.
Add all the other ingredients.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Serve between toasted, buttered bun halves.
This makes enough for 6.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Roll dates and nuts in 1/2 cup flour.
Sift soda and rest of flour.
Add alternately with milk, coconut, fruits, nuts and orange slice candy.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until done.

title: jubilee coffee cake
directions: In a small bowl, combine sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup mixture in greased Bundt pan.
Cut each biscuit in half and roll in balls.
Dip each ball in butter and layer biscuit balls, cinnamon mixture and 1/2 cup preserves in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Turn out on wire rack.
Top with remaining preserves.
Garnish with cherries.

title: cheesy cherry salad
directions: Chill this mixture overnight instead of freezing.

title: pecan balls
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and flour.
Add pecans.
Use 1 tablespoon of dough for each cookie and shape into balls.
Bake in a 300° oven for 45 minutes or until brown.
Roll in mixture of sugars as soon as taken from oven.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Bring sugar, turmeric powder, cloves, mustard seed, celery seed and vinegar to boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Drop cukes in hot syrup. Bring to a boiling point.
Put in hot sterilized jars.
Seal at once.
Place on a large board and cover with heavy towel until cool.
This helps them seal tight.

title: apple nut custard coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Beat baking mix, 1/4 cup sugar, the milk and vanilla with spoon.
Stir in pecans.
Spread in pan.
Mix apples, 3 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Spoon over batter (do not mix).
Beat whipping cream, eggs and 1/2 cup sugar just until smooth.
Pour over apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake about 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: honey-roasted apples
directions: Peel top third of apples and core, replacing 1/2-inch core in bottom.
Place apples in oiled baking dish.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions in water.
Season with salt and pepper to taste when potatoes and celery are tender.
If potatoes are too large, you may cut smaller.
Add milk and margarine.
Mix flour or cornstarch for thickening; stir constantly as you add this to your other ingredients until thickened.

title: three bean salad(serves 12)
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Cool while preparing other ingredients.
Combine cooled liquid and the remaining ingredients and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: peach crisp
directions: Place melted margarine in baking dish.
In small bowl mix the flour, sugar and milk.
Pour into baking dish with the margarine but do not stir.
Spoon fruit over batter evenly.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350°
until golden brown and dough rises to the top.

title: chicken dinner omelet
directions: Combine chicken and pimento.
Heat thoroughly.
In a 10-inch skillet, cook onion and celery in butter until tender. Add croutons. Toss lightly. Divide crust in halves.
Place vegetables in crusts and fold.
Bake until crust is done at 375°.
Pour chicken mixture over baked crust.

title: swedish birds nest cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar and blend.
Add egg yolk and blend. Stir in flour.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls, dip in egg white, roll in nuts, place on greased cookie sheet.
Lightly press into center of balls with tip of teaspoon to form small depression. Bake at 300° for 5 minutes, remove from oven and again press centers with teaspoon.
Bake 15 minutes more.
Cool, place jelly in centers.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: oven pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Put roast on foil, enough to wrap roast.
Put soup and onion soup mix on top of roast.
Mix it together and wrap in foil good and tight.
Put in oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: soup bean cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add beans, apples, raisins and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool.

title: old-fashioned tomato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, bring tomatoes to a boil.
Add baking soda, garlic salt, pepper and salt, as desired.
Reduce heat.
Add the milk and butter.
Heat through, but do not boil.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: patriotic biscuits
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender.
Add egg and milk.
Blend thoroughly.
Knead the dough on a lightly floured surface until smooth.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness and cut with biscuit cutter. Place on a greased baking sheet and brush with melted butter. Bake at 450° for about 7 minutes.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces (this will take about 2 months).
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene fire for about 4 weeks at 465°.
This will serve 1,972 people.
If more are expected, the two rabbits may be added, but do this only if necessary, as most people do not like to find hare in their stew!

title: spinach squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put butter in 13 x 9-inch pan and melt in oven.
Remove.
In large bowl, beat eggs well, then add flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add cheese, spinach and onion.
Mix well and spoon in pan.
Bake 35 minutes.
Remove and cool for 45 minutes.
Cut in squares.
Freezes well.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin well.
Add dry ingredients, mixing in a large bowl by hand with spoon.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: taco sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer five minutes.
Pack in jars.
Use all liquid.
Makes 3 pints.

title: forget me knots
directions: Beat egg whites and sugar until very stiff.
Fold in Rice Krispies and chocolate chips.
Place, by teaspoonfuls, on cookie sheets.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni noodles and drain.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Chill until served.
Serves 10.

title: creamy cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese with mixer until smooth; then add sugar and beat again.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in the Cool Whip and then spoon in your mixture into the pie crust.
Top the pie with your favorite fruit topping.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: chicken and sausage
directions: Take chicken and place in a big pot with salted water to cover.
Cook with lid on until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken, skin and bone.
Save broth.
Add 2 pounds hot sausage, shaped into small balls, to broth and cook until sausage is well done.
Remove sausage and thicken broth.
Mix flour and small amount of cold water to make smooth paste.
Stir into broth to make gravy, then add chicken and sausage.
Simmer about 15 minutes for flavors to blend.
Serve over split hot biscuits.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix with beans, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° until heated and cheese melts.

title: pork spareribs(costine di maiale)
directions: Place washed ribs
on
large
baking pan.
Sprinkle all over with poultry
seasoning,
salt,
pepper
and garlic salt. Add 1/2 cup water to
pan and cover with tinfoil.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes.
They will be very tender.
Heat barbecue grill until very hot.
Place slab of ribs on grill and brown about 6 to 7 minutes on
each
side.
Baste browned ribs with barbecue sauce and brown 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Place on cutting board and cut through to make nice single rib portions.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: lemon stuff
directions: Pour boiling water over jello and marshmallows.
Add the 1 cup cold water (thicken).
Add bananas and pineapple chunks.
Save the juice.
Chill.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and milk; add coconut and pecans.
Form into balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in top of double boiler.
Stick toothpicks into balls and dip in hot chocolate mixture.
Place on wax paper.
Cool.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In large pan, add the water and cranberries and bring to a boil. Add the soda and cook for 10 minutes. Add sugar, jello and marshmallows. Stir until dissolved. Let set until nearly thick; then add the apples, celery and the nut meats. Put in covered dish and refrigerate until served.

title: chocolate squares
directions: May add nuts if desired.

title: brandy fruit and nut cake
directions: Combine fruit and nuts.
Mix well.
Mix dry ingredients well. Add to fruit and nuts; coat well.
Beat eggs until frothy; add brandy.
Add to mixture; mix well.
Pour batter into 9 x 15-inch tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Cool in pan; remove from pan; wrap in cloth that has been dampened with 1/4 tablespoon brandy.
Wrap in foil; place in refrigerator a couple of days.
Unwrap; dampen cloth with water, no more brandy.
Rewrap and set in refrigerator at least a week.
Very very good.
Not too boozy.

title: 7-layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs evenly over butter.
Sprinkle coconut over the crumbs. Sprinkle chocolate bits over coconut.
Sprinkle butterscotch bits over chocolate bits and sprinkle chopped nuts over the butterscotch bits.
Pour over all the small can of sweetened condensed milk. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
Toast bran flakes in oven for 5 minutes; cool.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; mix well.
Stir in bran flakes.
Beat eggs at low speed; add brown sugar, then molasses.
Beat in milk and salad oil.
Add to dry ingredients.
Spoon into cups.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove immediately to wire rack.
Contain 150 calories each.

title: frosty mandarin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain oranges; reserve syrup and add water to make 1 cup.
Chill the mixture until slightly thickened.
Blend in oranges and sherbet; pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add all other ingredients and mix thoroughly. Put into unbaked 9 inch pie crust. Bake at 325 degrees for 45-55 minutes.

title: gladys mcqueen's old fashioned egg pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well.
Add buttermilk and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 300° until done.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 2 cups fruit juice from drained fruit to jello.
Take out 3/4 cup jello mixture and let gel separately.
Add fruit to remaining jello and chill until firm in 8 x 11-inch pan.
Whip the 3/4 cup jello.
Combine with Cool Whip and spread on top of salad and chill until ready to serve.
Add 1/4 cup pecans or walnuts over topping if desired.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers, onions and peppers in large dishpan, etc.
Add salt and cover with lots of ice.
Let stand for 3 hours, stirring occasionally so salt will be distributed evenly through cucumbers. In another large pot, combine vinegar, sugar and other spices. Bring to a boil.
Drain cucumbers and add them to the vinegar mixture.
Heat thoroughly but do not boil.
Pack in jars and seal at once.

title: light mocha pie
directions: Combine hot water, brownie mix, 1 teaspoon vanilla and egg whites; stir until blended well.
Pour into a 9-inch pie plate coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 22 minutes.
Let crust cool completely.

title: norman's apple pie
directions: Grease a pie plate. Fill the pie plate with the apples. Sprinkle 1 teaspoon sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon over the apples. In a separate bowl, mix the margarine, egg, sugar, flour and nuts. Spread this over the apples. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fiesta dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and picante sauce; beat at low speed with an electric mixer until smooth.
Garnish with sliced green onion. Serve with corn chips.
Yields 2 cups.

title: autumn soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add chopped onions and cook 5 minutes more.
Drain.
Add water, vegetables, salt, pepper, beef bouillon, bay leaves, basil and tomatoes.
Cook until vegetables are tender.

title: all-american hot dish(makes 6 servings)
directions: Cook and stir meat and onion in large skillet until meat is browned.
Drain off fat.
Stir in corn (with liquid), tomato sauce, olives, noodles, water, oregano, salt, pepper and cheese. Heat mixture to boiling.
Lower heat and simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes or until noodles are tender. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: delicious dessert
directions: Finely crush cookies and combine with butter.
Reserve 1 cup cookie mixture.
Spread remaining cookies in buttered 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Cover cookies with ice cream.
Spread with Cool Whip. Drizzle chocolate syrup over Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and remaining cookie crumbs.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer a few minutes before serving.
Serves 20.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Bring sugar, butter and milk to a boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips. Stir until smooth.
Pour over cake.

title: spiced walnuts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Finely chop mandarin peel.
Put mandarin juice in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Stir in mandarin peel, sugar, oil and red pepper sauce, and mix well.
Add nuts and toss to coat.

title: orange delight
directions: Gently fold cottage cheese, crushed pineapple and dry gelatin into whipped topping.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Spoon into dessert dishes.
If desired, garnish each serving with strawberry slices and mint sprigs.
Each serving 3/4 cup, 78 calories.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown and drain beef or turkey.
Add all other ingredients. (May add some water if you like soup to be more liquid.)
Simmer 1 hour.

title: punch
directions: Prepare the Kool-Aid as directed on package, adding 1 extra cup of sugar.
Mix all ingredients.
Place in freezer until it is slushy. Serve.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello in hot water.
Add oranges, sugar and cranberry sauce; mix well.
Let it set up partly and then add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into jello mold.
Let firmly set up.

title: corn flake treats
directions: Combine sugar and syrup.
Microwave for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter; return to microwave for 2 minutes.
Stir in the corn flakes.
Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into squares.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Put sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in a large pan. Bring to a boil. Cook only 1 minute and remove from heat.
Add oatmeal and peanut butter; mix well.
Add nuts, coconut and raisins.
Stir and drop on waxed paper quickly. Cool.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: broccoli timbales
directions: Finely chop broccoli; set aside.
Heat oven to 350°.
In one quart saucepan, over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook onion until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour until blended; cook 1 minute, stirring frequently.
Gradually stir in one cup half and half, cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened. Remove saucepan from heat.
Grease six (6-ounce) custard cups or 12 muffin tins.
In medium bowl with wire whisk or fork, mix eggs, bouillon, salt, pepper and remaining half and half.
Stir in onion mixture and broccoli.
Ladle egg mixture into custard cups.
Set cups in 13 x 9-inch baking pan; place pan on oven rack.
Pour boiling water in pan to come halfway up sides of cups.
Bake 35 minutes (for custard cups), 20 minutes (for muffin tins) or until knife inserted in center of mixture comes out clean.
Invert custard cups onto platter.

title: easy cake mix cookies
directions: May use 1/4 cup of oil in place of margarine.
Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 1 nut half on each cookie, if desired.
Bake in greased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil and melt in the peanut butter. Add corn flakes and stir well.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: jello salad
directions: Mash cranberry sauce.
Mix jello according to package, cutting water down 1/2 and using liquid off of pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: 3 flavor cake
directions: Cream
shortening, oleo and sugar together; add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each egg.
Sift flour, salt, and baking powder
together;
add with milk to cream mixture; add extracts. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Glaze.

title: rita's pound cake squares
directions: Mix together the pound cake, margarine and 2 eggs.
Mix until creamy, then spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook ground chuck until it separates.
Mix ingredients.
Bake in slow oven for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: In a large container, mix all ingredients and chill overnight. Yields 150 servings.

title: christmas rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° until rice is done.

title: company potatoes
directions: Mix hash browns, cheese, soup, sour cream, and onions together; pour in a casserole dish.
Mix butter and corn flakes; put on top of hash brown mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sweet little biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients, mixing well.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Shape dough into a ball and knead lightly 4 or 5 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Cut with a 1 3/4-inch biscuit cutter and place on ungreased baking sheet. Brush lightly with milk.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes. Yields 3 dozen.

title: spanish omelette sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, and simmer for 1/2 hour. Makes 3 pints.

title: spicy crab chowder
directions: In a 3 1/2-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat oil and cook potatoes, celery and onion until tender-crisp.
Stir in vegetable juice, crab and corn.
Heat to boiling, 10 to 15 minutes, stirring gently now and then.
Reduce heat to low. Simmer.
Serves 4.

title: elvis presley cake
directions: Cook cake as directed on box.
Mix sugar and pineapple together and cook until it comes to a boil.
Then pour this mixture over the cake when it is hot out of the oven.
Then, after this kind of soaks in, mix cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar together and spread over cake.
If the mixture is too thick, add 1 to 2 tablespoons of milk to it.
Then sprinkle chopped nuts on the top.

title: plum kuchen
directions: Cream butter or margarine with 1/2 cup of the sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add extracts.
Beat well.
Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Spoon into greased round 9-inch cake pan 2 inches deep.
Cut plums in half.
Arrange cut side down on top of batter.
Mix remaining 1/2 cup sugar with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Sprinkle over plums.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: mom's butter balls
directions: Cream butter and 1/2 cup confectioners sugar until fluffy. Blend in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and flour.
Stir in walnuts.
Chill.

title: fruited wild rice pilaf
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion and celery in butter until tender. Stir in the water, rice and bouillon; bringing to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 50-55 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender. Remove from the heat; fold in the apple, pecans and lemon peel if desired.

title: baked rice
directions: Mix ingredients in 3 quart casserole dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour or until liquid is absorbed.
Stir once during baking time.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: a good microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Spread over top, if desired, 2 tablespoons ketchup, steak sauce, barbecue sauce or chili sauce.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, beat eggs and brown sugar together until blended.
Add melted butter or margarine, corn syrup, salt, vanilla and chopped pecans and mix thoroughly; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake until filling is puffed and golden brown, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve pie slightly warm or cool and top with whipped cream.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Saute onions, pepper and celery until soft.
Layer bread, vegetables, krab (or crab) in large casserole dish, ending with bread. Combine eggs, milk, soup, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Pour over casserole mixture.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until browned and set.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tennessee-fried catfish
directions: Sprinkle catfish with salt and pepper on both sides.
Beat eggs with milk in shallow dish.
Dip catfish in egg mixture; roll in cornmeal.
Fry catfish in 1/8-inch hot shortening in heavy skillet.
Fry over medium heat until brown on both sides; drain on absorbent paper.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Clean and skin chicken breasts.
Place in shallow baking dish. Lightly mix together bread cubes, onion, 1/4 cup water, butter and poultry seasoning. Place mound of stuffing over each chicken breast.
Blend soup and 1/3 cup water.
Pour over chicken and dressing. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until tender. (We double the dressing mix.)

title: fudge topped brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine butter, sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, eggs, milk and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla.
Beat well. Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar, tartar, cold water and lemon extract in the top of a double
boiler;
beat 1 minute.
Set top of double boiler over boiling water.
Cook
for 7 minutes, beating constantly at high speed
until
stiff
peaks
form. Remove
from heat and fold in
coconut.
Frost
your
favorite cake.

title: whipping cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Alternate, adding flour and whipping cream, stirring frequently.
Add vanilla.
Start in cold oven.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Combine white wine, lemon juice and chopped garlic.
Pound thin about 1 pound chicken cutlets.
Coat with seasoned bread crumbs and saute chicken in olive oil until lightly browned and tender.
Add wine mixture and simmer uncovered a
few minutes until liquid is somewhat reduced.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: potato pizza
directions: Place sliced potatoes (parboiled and drained) in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place hamburger over potatoes.
Mix milk and cheese soup together (heat a little to mix), then pour over the hamburger.
Mix rest of ingredients together and pour over the soup.
Bake for 45 minutes in covered pan.
Uncover and sprinkle 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and slices of Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: banana pudding
directions: Over medium heat, combine sugar and egg yolks.
Gradually add Pet milk.
Cook until thickened.
Stir in vanilla.
Cool slightly. Layer wafers in a dish.
Layer bananas.
Pour 1/2 of filling over layers.
Repeat layering of wafers and bananas.
Pour remaining filling over layers.
Top with wafers.
Spread Cool Whip over wafers.

title: tofu balls
directions: Press water out of tofu, placing plates or weighted cutting board on top for 1/2 hour.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: In food processor, blend softened cream cheese, olives and jalapenos.
Spread mixture evenly on tortillas.
Roll and chill. Slice and serve.

title: ice cubes
directions: Melt sweet chocolate and semi-sweet chocolate chips in double boiler and let it cool down.
When cool, add 1/2 pint whipped whipping cream.
Mix well.
Add nuts now if you want, then pour it into a well-greased pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into cubes and enjoy.

title: karen's dessert
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar.
Pat half on bottom of buttered square baking dish. Reserve remaining crumbs for top layer of dessert.
Place marshmallows in top of double boiler over hot water.
Stir in milk and cook until marshmallows are melted.
Cool.

title: doughnuts
directions: Combine all ingredients. Roll out dough.
Cut with doughnut cutter and fry in hot oil.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Combine all other ingredients and cook until broccoli is tender.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently to prevent scorching.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes, onions and peppers.
Add other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Let cook for 1 hour or until thick.
Seal in sterile jars.

title: easy turkey pizza
directions: Unroll
and
separate
rolls;
arrange,
overlapping
a little, in a lightly oiled
11-inch pizza pan to form a crust. Pinch seams together well.
Brush
with
1/2 tablespoon of the oil.
Bake on the lowest shelf
of a preheated 425° oven for 8 to 10 minutes until edges brown lightly.
Remove from oven and spread with 2 tablespoons of the pizza sauce.
Meanwhile, heat remaining tablespoon of oil
in
skillet;
add turkey meat and brown lightly, stirring to
break up chunks.
Season with salt and basil.
Sprinkle meat
over
pizza
crust
and
top
with remaining pizza sauce.
Cover
with sliced cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan. Return to the
oven
and
bake
about
20 minutes, or until cheese
is
melted
and
edges well browned. Let stand 3 or 4 minutes,
then cut into wedges.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: country herb roasted chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, arrange chicken.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; brush on chicken.
Bake 45 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: butter crunch toffee
directions: Melt butter over low heat in a large heavy saucepan.
Remove from heat and add sugar.
Stir until blended. Return to low heat. Stir rapidly until mixed and bubbly. Remove from heat.
Add water and syrup.
Cook with thermometer over low heat, stirring frequently, about 20 minutes or until temperature reaches 290°. Remove at once.
Add nuts.
Pour on lightly greased cookie sheet. Cool.
Melt chocolate and pour over.
Smooth with knife.
Break into pieces when chocolate is firm.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-size pieces.
This will take about 2 months.
Cut vegetables into cubes (another 2 months).
Place meat in pan and cover with 1,000 gallons of brown gravy.
Simmer for 4 weeks.
Shovel in salt and pepper to taste.
When meat is tender, add vegetables.
Simmer slowly for 4 more weeks.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 38,000 people.
If more people drop in than expected, add the 2 rabbits.
This is not recommended, however, because few people like "hare" in their stew.

title: congealed chicken salad
directions: Heat cream of chicken soup and cream cheese until cheese is melted. Remove from heat and add gelatin, dissolved in cold water. Blend well. Blend in mayonnaise.
Pour into a square dish.
Place in the refrigerator to congeal.
Let stand at least 2 hours. Cut into squares and serve on lettuce.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Blend sugar, salt, spices, lemon rind and butter or margarine. Toss apples into mixture.
Arrange in pie shell.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Slice potatoes in bottom of large casserole dish.
Slice onions over this.
Add uncooked broken up hamburger.
Pour soup over top.
Do not stir.
Cover and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Serves 6.

title: no guess punch
directions: Squeeze oranges and lemons; add sugar, then add water.
Taste if sweet or tart to your taste.
Then add pineapple juice and chill.
Refreshing drink.

title: frances' crab meat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat in casserole about 15 minutes in a
300° oven.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: grape-nut pudding
directions: Warm the
milk
and pour over the Grape-Nuts in a bowl. Let stand
for
minutes.
Add beaten eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla, stirring to
mix
very
well.
Pour
into
a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking
pan
or dish.
Sprinkle nutmeg over top.
Place pan into a
larger
pan with 1 to 2-inches of hot water.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until the custard is set.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Pat into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, then cook for 5 minutes in oven until crust is set.
Cool. Cream together 2 sticks oleo and 2 cups powdered sugar.
Add eggs to oleo and sugar mixture and beat until very light, no less than 15 minutes.
Spread over graham cracker crust.
Drain well pineapple and spread over mixture.
Slice 3 to 4 bananas on top of pineapple.
Top with large container of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts and cherries on top.
Refrigerate.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Cut Twinkies lengthwise in half; layer cream side up in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding with milk, let stand 5 minutes.
Pour over Twinkies.
Slice bananas over pudding; top with Cool Whip. If desired, crunch a Heath bar and sprinkle over top.

title: mom's apple cake
directions: In a large bowl, let apples, sugar and oil set for 1 hour. Mix together dry ingredients and add to apples. Mix in eggs, vanilla and nuts. Bake in floured and greased Bundt pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes in 325° oven.

title: best dough
directions: Warm water in microwave for 40 to 50 seconds on High.
Pour into large bowl and add salt, sugar, yeast and 1 cup flour.
Mix well; add remaining flour.
When mixture is too thick to stir, pour onto heavily floured surface.
Dough will absorb flour but should remain "sticky."
Place back into bowl and cover with plastic or towel.
Let rise for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Knead on floured surface, it will be moist.
Keep surface heavily floured.
Roll out for pizza.
Bake pizza crust at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Use this recipe for French bread and dinner rolls too.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown beef in large skillet.
Drain and add remaining ingredients, except cheese and mix well.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Top with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 4 to 6.
Can make ahead, then top with cheese and bake.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together butter,
shortening
and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well
after each.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Bake in floured and greased 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Spread with chocolate frosting.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Put sugar and syrup in 3-quart saucepan and let mixture just start to bubble. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter. Add Rice Krispies. Spread into buttered 13 x 9 pan. Mix chips. Cook over low heat until melted. Spread over Rice Krispies.

title: chow chow
directions: Wash and prepare vegetables to be chopped in food processor or by hand.
Place in large pan.
Add salt and let stand 24 hours. Drain mixture, getting out all of the brine.
Add chopped cabbage to other vegetables.
In large pan, mix sugar, vinegar and spices.
Heat.
Add vegetables.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Boil fryer with celery stalk.
Allow to cool and take off the bone.
Melt oleo in pan.
Add the box of Stove Top stuffing.
Mix well.
Spread stuffing in bottom of an oblong dish, 9 x 12-inch. Place chicken pieces on top.
Mix in pan, soups with 2 cans of broth that chicken was cooked in.
Pour soup mixture over chicken and dressing.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: salt dough
directions: Knead dough on a lightly floured surface for about 5 to 10 minutes, until satiny smooth.
This prevents cracking and uneven baking.
After molding, bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Check often.
Apple color via a paste food coloring, brushed on with egg whites prior to baking for a golden brown finish.
Spray with a clear sealer (polyethylene or resin-based).

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese and spread over bottom of pie shells.
Top with layer of sliced bananas that have been dipped in lemon juice.
Add a layer of coconut then a layer of pie filling. Top with Cool Whip and chill.

title: mincemeat drops
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually and blend well.
Add egg; mix.
Add dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Fold in mincemeat; add vanilla and thoroughly mix.
(If dry mincemeat is used, add 1/2 cup water and cook until water is absorbed, about 8 minutes; cool.)
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart and bake at 400° from 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: easy hamburger macaroni
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onion.
Drain fat.
Stir in soup, spaghetti sauce, water, pepper and macaroni.
Heat through.

title: aminee's baked fruit
directions: Place peaches, pears and pineapple in baking dish.
In the center of each piece of fruit put 1/2 teaspoon brown sugar, 1/2 teaspoon vinegar, dab of butter and sprinkle of cinnamon.
Place cherry on each piece of fruit.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Serve hot.

title: cake flour icing
directions: In a mixing bowl, blend sugar, Crisco, vanilla, and butter. Mix well until sugar is dissolved.
In a medium saucepan, mix milk and flour and cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove sauce pan from heat and allow mixture to cool. When cool, blend milk and flour mixture with sugar mixture.
Whip at high speed for 8 to 10 minutes.
Icing will keep up to 3 weeks in the freezer.

title: one layer jam cake
directions: Mix egg, sugar and oil.
Mix together flour (save out 1/4 cup), soda, cloves, cinnamon and allspice.
Add salt.
Mix dry ingredients alternately with applesauce.
Add nuts and raisins which have been coated with the 1/4 cup flour.
Last, add jam. Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour, or until done.
Spread on caramel icing.

title: ham dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; dice onion and ham into small bits.
Add all ingredients together and serve on Ritz crackers.

title: beefy corn bread
directions: Brown ground beef and onion (drain). Mix corn meal, soda, salt, cream corn, eggs, milk. Pour half in greased 9 X 13 pan. Sprinkle cheese, ground beef and onion. Add remaining corn meal mixture. Bake as regular corn bread.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in blender.
While on medium speed, add the oil slowly.
Be careful not to add too much at once. Continue beating after oil is added until dressing is thick.
Add poppy seeds and stir.
Store in refrigerator, but do not freeze.

title: "one pot" dinner
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain off fat and put beef in crock-pot.
Brown bacon and onions; drain off fat.
Add bacon, onions and remaining ingredients to crock-pot.
Stir together well.
Cover and cook on low 5 to 9 hours (high 3 hours).

title: spicy baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken and remove skins. Place in bottom of baking pan bone side down. Lightly sprinkle chicken pieces with each of the spices above. Bake in a 350 oven for 40 minutes.

title: florey's barbecue sauce
directions: Heat the oil and saute the onion in a large stainless steel skillet over medium heat until it begins to brown.
Add all other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for thirty minutes.
Sauce may be used right away or placed in a covered glass jar.
Store in refrigeration for one month.
Great on chops, poultry and especially ribs.

title: orange refrigerator cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Into large bowl of mixer, place shortening, butter, sugars and egg.
Beat on #7 speed for 2 minutes.
Add juice, orange rind, lemon extract, pecans and the sifted dry ingredients.
Beat on #1 speed about 1 minute.
Scrape bowl while beating.
Shape into rolls and wrap in waxed paper. Chill several hours.
Slice thin with a sharp knife and bake on greased cookie sheet for 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.
I always double this recipe and freeze extra rolls for later.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: To the cooked pasta, add zucchini and cook for 2 more minutes.
Drain; rinse in cold water.
Shake.
In serving bowl, add pasta and zucchini, 1 tablespoon of oil, olives and green onions.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and chips or stuffing mix.
Toss lightly and spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spread cheese and chips on top and bake in 350° oven 25 minutes, or until heated throughout and browned on top.
Garnish with paprika and parsley.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Cut the chicken into bite size pieces.
Saute onion in butter until soft in a large skillet with a cover.
Stir in paprika and flour; cook, stirring constantly for 1 minute.
Stir in salt and tomato juice.
Add chicken, turning to coat pieces well; cover. Simmer 30 to 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: microwave mexican casserole
directions: In 12 x 8-inch glass casserole add butter and onion. Microwave (High) 3 minutes, stirring once.
Reserve 1 cup corn chips and 1 1/4 cups cheese.
Blend remaining chips, cheese, chili, beans and corn with onion.
Microwave (High) covered 8 to 9 minutes, rotating 1/4 turn halfway through cooking.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese.
(Microwave on High uncovered 3 minutes.)
"Ring" remaining corn chips around edge.
Rest 5 minutes before serving.

title: chilli
directions: Mix beef and onion in frying pan and heat well.
Put remaining ingredients in a pot and bring to a boil.
Add beef and onion; cook about 30 minutes or longer.

title: bachelor buttons
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients and add them alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Pour mixture into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: green chilies and rice
directions: Mix ingredients. Pour into buttered casserole and cover. Bake at 300° for 25 minutes or until hot. This is a wonderful dish to serve with ham, steak, meat loaf or just let your mind run wild with serving ideas. Serves 8.

title: lemon butter
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick.
Cool and serve.
Good with hamburgers, potato salad and sliced tomatoes for a summer picnic.

title: candy pecans
