directions: Beat egg white until a soft peak forms.
Gradually mix in brown sugar and vanilla flavoring.
Fold in pecan halves.
Grease cookie sheet well.
Place pecan halves 1/2-inch apart.
Bake at 250° for about 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix together.
Put in pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: low-calorie vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients to taste.
Simmer several hours.
Will make a lot.

title: nut stickies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Melt butter or oleo in 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Add brown sugar and nuts.
Top with cloverleaf, placed upside down.
Bake 25 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute.
Invert pan to remove rolls.

title: pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt and oil. Add 1 3/4 cups of the flour and stir well.
Turn onto a well-floured surface; knead until dough is no longer sticky, about 5 minutes.
Place dough on a greased cookie sheet and spread out, using fingertips.
Add sauce, cheese and other desired toppings. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: greek pilaff
directions: Fry onion until wilted.
Fry chopped lamb.
Add rice to fried onion and meat.
Fry it briefly.
(Cubed lamb should be stewed in stock, red wine and all herbs until tender.) Add stock with all herbs.
Reduce heat and cook for 20 minutes.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Pack sterilized quart jars with cucumbers.
Add to each jar alum, garlic, dill and red pepper.
Combine and boil vinegar, 1 cup salt and water.
Fill hot jars and seal.

title: bacon-cheese crackers
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; blend well.
Spread cheese mixture on each round.
Broil until mixture is hot and bubbly.
Serve hot or cold.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together apples and sugar and let stand 10 minutes.
Beat together oil, egg and vanilla and add to apple mix.
Sift together remaining ingredients, except raisins, and add to apple-oil mixture.
Stir in the raisins.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with a few chopped nuts.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken; debone. cook spaghetti in chicken broth; drain and rinse in hot water.
In skillet, melt margarine and saute celery, pimentos, bell pepper, and onion.
Cook slow until tender, then add soups and cheez whiz.
Do not add water to soups.
Combine chicken and all other ingredients (add some broth if dry).
Bake just until hot at 350 degrees for about 20 minutes.
Serves 10 - 12.
(You can add a little hot sauce for spice.)

title: hamburger and rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add onion and green pepper as desired.
Add tomatoes.
Add tomato sauce and let simmer.
While hamburger is browning, prepare rice as directed.
When rice is done, combine it with hamburger mixture still in skillet.
Add sugar, garlic salt, salt and pepper to taste.
Place mixture in Pyrex dish and let simmer in oven.
Be careful not to let it dry out.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat water and shortening until it boils hard.
Add all at once the flour; stir until it leaves sides of pan.
Cool.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased tin.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit slush(no fat)
directions: If you're an adult of average weight, here is what you accomplish in 24 hours:

title: chili dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat until bubbly.

title: french toast
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar together.
Add milk to beaten eggs. Whisk in cinnamon and sugar.
Dip bread into batter.
Melt margarine in skillet.
Brown bread on both sides.
Serve hot.

title: chinese chews
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together; mix with beaten eggs.
Roll into little balls, then roll in granulated sugar.
Place on floured cookie sheet and bake for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: In a medium bowl, combine butter, both sugars and spices; cream with mixer until light and fluffy.
Beat in softened ice cream and rum until smooth.
Turn into 4 cup freezer proof container.
Store ice cream mixture in freezer.
Mixture will not freeze solid.
To serve, place 1/4 cup mixture in a mug and add 1/2 cup boiling water; blend well.
Garnish with a cinnamon stick.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: floating pie crust
directions: Mix and pour in greased baking dish.
Pour fruit on top (make fruit juicy).
Add 1/2 cup sugar to peaches and apples.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Saute pecans in butter; set aside.
Soften cream cheese.
Add milk, garlic salt, sour cream and onion.
Stir until soft; add beef, tearing into small pieces.
Pour in an 8-inch dish.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Prepare pie crust following label directions; roll out.
Cut into 16 (4 1/2-inch) rounds.
Fit into 3 1/2-inch tart pans.
Beat butter and sugar in large bowl with electric mixer until creamy. Beat in corn syrup and honey, then eggs and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Place about 1/4 cup filling in each tart shell.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in a hot oven (400°) for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool before serving.
Decorate with whipped cream, if you wish.
Makes 16 tarts.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Break bread into 1/2-inch cubes.
Place in a greased 9 to 10-inch pan or dish.
Brown sausage; drain.
Put on top of bread. Put cheese on top of sausage or ham.
Beat eggs; add milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over other ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Heat chips,
milk and margarine until melted.
Pour over marshmallows and nuts.
Mix well and pour into a buttered dish. Chill in refrigerator about 4 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, celery and mustard seed in large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Drain tomatoes and onions; rinse in cold water.
Add to vinegar mixture; let simmer until hot.
Do not boil.
Pack in hot, sterilized jars and seal.
Makes about 5 pints.

title: rice salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except for the cream in a large bowl. Mix together well.
Stir in gradually the whipped cream until all is gone.
Gently stir for 2 minutes.
Chill for at least 1 hour and then serve.
Serves 6.

title: low-fat pinto bean casserole
directions: Saute ground turkey and onion together.
In a large bowl, mix together the tomatoes, beans, steak sauce, chili powder and barbecue sauce.
Pour into a large baking pan.
Mix corn bread as directed on package.
Pour over bean mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Put cake mix, oil, margarine, eggs and sour cream in a mixing bowl.
Heat 2 minutes at high speed.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour half of mixture in pan.
Mix raisins, brown sugar and cinnamon together.
Sprinkle over batter in pan.
Add rest of batter.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour or until done.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving 1/3 cup liquid.
In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in reserved liquid, vinegar and butter.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly.
Add beets and cook until warm.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Pour cherries and juice in saucepan.
Heat to a boil, then add sugar and jello.
Stir until sugar and jello dissolve.
Remove from heat.
Chill partially, then add pineapple and nuts.

title: che-broom dip
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; drain and cool.
Add broccoli to soup, cheese and mushrooms in medium bowl.
Serve at room temperature.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender. Process until smooth. Store in refrigerator until ready to use. Yields about 1 1/4 cups.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Add one can of icing. Mix until well blended. Pour into a greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake according to box directions; cool. Frost with second can of icing.

title: baked seafood platter
directions: Saute catfish in shortening just long enough to keep it from falling apart.
Place fish in a 12 x 18-inch baking dish.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix beans, peas, asparagus and soup thoroughly.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs mixed with butter.
Sprinkle with cheese over top.
Bake at 375° until it bubbles.
Serve hot from casserole.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all of the ingredients well.
Shape this mixture into cakes.
Dip the cakes in another beaten egg and then dip cakes into more bread crumbs.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: whipped strawberry drink
directions: Put strawberries, milk and eggs into blender.
Process until frothy.
Pour into tall glasses.
Garnish with fresh whole strawberries or mint sprigs.
Serves 2.

title: broccoli and noodles supreme
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, prepare noodles according to package directions.
Add broccoli for last 5 minutes of cooking time. Drain in colander.
In same saucepan, combine soup, sour cream, cheese and black pepper; add noodles and broccoli.
Over low heat, heat through, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with diced carrot and red pepper, if desired.
Preparation time:
5 minutes; cook time:
20 minutes.

title: apple duff
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Peel and core apples. Stuff the centers with mixture of brown sugar, raisins and cinnamon.
Roll out pastry and cut into 4 circles approximately 8 inches in diameter, depending on size of the apples.
Place an apple in the center of pastry circle and brush the edge with beaten egg.
Draw up pastry to enfold the apple, pressing edge to seal.
Brush tops of pastry with remaining egg.
Bake in shallow dish for 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: sugar free strawberry pie
directions: Mix pudding mix and water in a boiler and bring to a boil; cook until thick.
Remove from the heat and add Jello, stir until dissolved; add strawberries and Equal and stir. Pour into pie crust and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Top with cool whip.

title: graham cracker fluff
directions: Soak gelatin in water; set aside.
Mix sugar, milk and egg yolks; cook for one minute, stirring all the time.
Remove from heat; add gelatin and vanilla.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Then add stiffly beaten egg whites and whipped cream. Melt butter; mix brown sugar, butter and graham cracker crumbs together.
Line bottom of a dish with 1/2 of crumbs.
Pour in pudding; put remaining crumbs on top.
Chill.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix pineapple juice with water according to directions on Jello.
Let cool.
Grind cranberries and add one cup of sugar and mix.
Combine all ingredients with Jello liquid and place in a mold (or tube pan). Refrigerate to jell.
To remove from mold, dip in hot water.

title: tortilla soup(large recipe)
directions: Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes. Serve with grated Cheddar cheese, sour cream, black olives, chopped tomatoes or garnish how you choose. Also serve with corn chips or our favorite flour tortillas fried on griddle.

title: emerald isle mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add pineapple with syrup and creme de menthe.
Chill until thickened, stirring often.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix all other ingredients separately. Shape dough into rolls and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Cut into cookies and cook on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° until brown.

title: marinated pork chops
directions: Place the pork chops in mixture of the cola, soy sauce and garlic overnight.
Grill over charcoal or broil in oven.

title: braised beef
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions and peppers.
Add puree.
Cook at 375° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: bunstick coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then add 4 cups flour and knead. Let raise until double in size.
Roll out dough on floured board and place on greased cookie sheet.
Let double in size.
Put the topping on and bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Cool.

title: angel's lasagna
directions: Mix spices and tomatoes together in a large saucepan.
Simmer for 1 hour. Sauce is best if made one day ahead of time to use for lasagna.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Drain
pineapple.
Mix water with juice to equal 1 cup. Mix vinegar, soy sauce, cornstarch and brown sugar; cook until thick and
clear.
Add pineapple and bell peppers.
Add meatballs and simmer 15 minutes.

title: casserole italiano
directions: Brown beef with onion, garlic, salt and oregano in a skillet, stirring frequently.
Add the soup, water and boiled noodles. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and place cheese around edges.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Place cupcake papers in cupcake tin and add one vanilla wafer to each cup.
Mix the cream cheese, eggs, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice with mixer.
The batter will be lumpy.
Pour the batter into cupcake liners (3/4 full).
Bake at 350° for 15-20 minutes.
Do NOT overbake!

title: tomato casserole
directions: Butter a 10 x 10 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Place layer of saltine crackers in bottom of dish.
Pour one can of tomatoes over crackers (chop tomatoes into pieces).
Sprinkle 1/2 cup onions over tomatoes.
Sprinkle 1/2 cheese over onions.
Repeat layers, ending with crumbled crackers on top.
Dot with margarine.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes, or until golden brown and bubbly in center.
Serve with meat.
Especially good with fish.

title: excellent hash brown casserole
directions: Put hash browns in a buttered large roaster or casserole. Top with beef and onions. Sprinkle with peas. Combine soups and sour cream and spread over peas; sprinkle with cheese. Top with onion rings. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or more.

title: dill dip
directions: Blend together.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Better if left overnight.

title: applesauce bread baked in a jar
directions: Cream the shortening and 2 2/3 cups sugar together.
Beat in eggs, 2/3 cup sugar and applesauce.
Sift together and blend into first mixture the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into well-greased pint jars (wide mouth with no neck), filling half full.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.
Remove 1 jar at a time from oven; wipe the sealing edge clean.
Put on lid and ring and screw tight.
Jar will seal as bread cools.
Store as you would regular canned goods.
Delicious!
Enjoy!

title: cranberry and apple relish
directions: Grind fruit in food chopper.
Add sugar and chill a few hours before serving.
This keeps well.

title: quick chicken or pork chops
directions: Roll in flour, salt and pepper; brown in frying pan.

title: zucchini and onions with mozzarella
directions: In 10-inch skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add remaining ingredients except tomato and cheese.
Continue cooking until zucchini is crisp-tender (7 to 10 minutes).
Add tomato; sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and let stand 2 or 3 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: butter pecan brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray pan with cooking spray.
Mix first 3 ingredients together and spread mixture into pan.
Press down.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over layer in pan.
Cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour until top is golden brown.

title: meatballs and wieners
directions: Combine hamburger meat, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper. Form into balls.
Brown in a skillet.
Boil tomato sauce, lemon juice and brown sugar.
Add meatballs and wieners.
Simmer for about 8 minutes or until the wieners are heated.

title: oatmeal macaroons
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add and beat well, eggs and vanilla.
Add and mix in sifted flour and dry ingredients.
Mix in oatmeal and nuts.
Roll in balls.
Bake on greased sheet 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt bark and chocolate chips in double boiler or in microwave.
When completely melted, add nuts and stir.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix together Bisquick, baking powder, yellow corn meal and sugar.
Add melted margarine, milk and eggs.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then at 325° for 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: guacamole
directions: Combine mashed avocado, onion, garlic and seasonings in a small bowl.
Spread top
with mayonnaise, sealing to the edges of the bowl.
Chill.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil all ingredients except popcorn and soda.
Mix well.
Stir for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Stir fast.
Pour over popcorn and mix well.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all canned fruits and mix with the pudding mix (omit the cherry juice).
Place the drained fruit and raisins into a salad bowl of choice (size depends on the number to be served).
Cook pudding over medium heat, stirring continuously (to avoid sticking) until it begins to thicken and turns clear (fruit color).
Pour the cooked syrup over the fruit afterward adding the cherries last.
Mix the pudding well with the fruit and allow it to chill at least 1 hour before serving.
May be altered for sugar free (low sugar) by using sugar free fruits.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Crust:
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan in oven.
Remove. Add flour and nuts.
Mix.
Pat in pan and return to oven.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove and cool.

title: honey herb chicken
directions: Grill or preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine all ingredients except chicken.
Brush sauce over chicken.
Grill or bake until well done and tender, basting every 5 minutes with sauce.
If baking, the chicken pieces may be placed in a baking dish and the sauce may be poured into the baking dish.
Basting is then done with a spoon at 10 minute intervals.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crawfish fettuccine
directions: Cook 15 minutes; add 1 package fettuccine pasta (cook accordingly).

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Saute onion, pepper, celery and margarine.
Heat soup and Cheez Whiz until melted.
Add rice, soup and broccoli into mixture.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: choc-o-lite
directions: I melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan that I am making crust in. Add crust ingredients and spread over bottom of pan (it takes time to spread it out).
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let crust cool.

title: crabmeat in shells
directions: Melt butter. Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Flake crabmeat and add to sauce with parsley and eggs. Blend thoroughly.
Fill greased baking shells.
Sprinkle crumbs on top and bake in oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: yeast waffles
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in large bowl.
Add milk, sugar and salt.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in oil and flour.
Allow batter to rise in a warm place about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir batter down and place in refrigerator overnight or when needed.
Stir batter down again and bake in a preheated waffle iron.

title: shrimp dip for bugles
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat over low heat until creamy.
Serve warm with Bugles.

title: nellie's spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all together in large container and toss.
Cover and refrigerate 4 to 6 hours or overnight.

title: linguini with thai chicken
directions: For sauce, combine and blend broth, wine, soy, cornstarch, peanut butter and pepper in a bowl and reserve.
Preheat large skillet over high heat.
Add oil.
Stir-fry garlic and ginger 15 seconds.
Add onion; stir-fry 3 minutes.
Remove and reserve vegetables.
Add chicken and stir-fry until done.
Make a well by pushing chicken to sides and stir in sauce in the center.
Cook, stirring until sauce is thickened and bubbly.
Cook 2 more minutes.
Add vegetables until coated and hot.
Serve over noodles with green onions on top and cilantro as additional garnish.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion in a 10-inch skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix (dry).
Spread in pie plate; sprinkle with chilies.
Beat milk, eggs and baking mix 15 seconds in blender, 1 minute with wire whisk or hand beater or until smooth.
Pour over chilies.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomato and cheese.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Crush crackers to semi-fine grind.
Add and mix all ingredients to soft pasty consistency.
Remove mushroom stems. Mound stuffing in caps.
Place on buttered pie pan in preheated 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix pineapple and jello together and bring to a boil.
Let cool 10 minutes, then add ingredients.
Let chill four hours and serve.
Add a few drops of red or green food coloring for Christmas.

title: pickles
directions: Select a bowl or jar large enough to hold all of the above ingredients.
This will be your "pickle barrel."

title: sweet-sour pork chops
directions: Trim fat from pork chops.
Brown chops on both sides in small amount of oil.
Drain juice from pineapple.
Mix cornstarch and vinegar until smooth.
Add soy sauce, sugar and juice (add water if not enough).
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Pour sauce over pork chops and cook until tender, about 30 minutes.
Add green pepper and pineapple; cook about 10 minutes more.

title: beef 'n bean pot
directions: Brown beef and bacon together and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Cook at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine Raisin Bran, sugar and flour.
Add buttermilk, oil,
eggs and raisins.
Stir well.
Pour into well-greased muffin pans.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. This mixture will keep refrigerated for 5 to 6 weeks and can be baked as needed.

title: hamburger steak
directions: Mix well and shape into patties.
Saute slowly, about 30 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Add 1/3 cup cooking oil and 2 tablespoons flour to drippings to make a gravy.
Pour in mushroom soup.
Heat and stir until thickened.
Pour over hamburger patties.

title: nut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Roll chopped nuts in flour and fold into batter. Bake in Bundt pan at 375° for 50-60 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over cake to serve.

title: caramels
directions: Boil sugar, cream and syrup rapidly for 2 minutes.
Slowly add butter so boiling does not stop.

title: pork chops
directions: Dredge the pork chops in flour, salt and pepper.
Place in baking dish. Cover with the chopped onions.
Mix the ketchup, soy sauce, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, sugar and water and pour over chops.
Bake 3 hours, covered, at 300°.
After 2 1/2 hours, uncover and let brown. Enjoy.

title: chinese stir-fry vegetables
directions: (May substitute your own vegetables as desired.)
Chop mushrooms, broccoli, zucchini, carrots, Chinese cabbage and bok choy in equal amounts.
Chop up whole onion and green and red peppers.
Heat Chinese wok on medium flame.
Saute garlic about 30 seconds.
Add onion and saute about 1 minute or until slightly translucent.
Add broccoli, zucchini, carrots and peppers.
Cook and stir frequently.
You may need to add about 1/2 cup of water for moisture.
Cook for 2 to 4 minutes or until vegetables are slightly soft.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown meat in frying pan, breaking up any lumps.
Add next four ingredients.
Bring to boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
In small mixing bowl, mix Ricotta or cottage cheese, egg and Parmesan cheese.
Put a little of the meat sauce in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, then start alternating layers as follows:
layer of raw noodles, 1/3 meat sauce, 1/2 of cheese mixture, repeat and then top with last of 1/3 of meat sauce.

title: pork chop and onion rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chops in single layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Brown in oven (or brown in skillet). Remove chops and pour off fat.
Spread rice evenly in bottom of baking dish and sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid, and distribute mushrooms evenly over rice.
Add hot water to reserved mushroom liquid to total 3 cups.
Pour over rice.
Arrange browned chops on top and cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until all liquid is absorbed.

title: butter cream frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Recipe yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: dan chingwa's stuff on stuff sauce
directions: Saute onions and green pepper in butter in a large deep frying pan. Add beef, salt and pepper; fry until brown. Drain off fat. Add soy sauce, beef bouillon, Kitchen Bouquet and Worcestershire sauce to beef mixture; mix well.
Then add water and bring to a boil.
Shake water and flour in a covered jar. Stir flour mixture slowly into pan, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil. Cover and put on a low burner until you are ready to serve.

title: ann jillian's turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl by hand.
Pack into a 9-inch greased loaf pan (glass preferred).
Cook at 350° to 375° for 55 minutes.
Leave out of oven for 3 minutes.
Slice and serve.
Serve with real mashed potatoes, creamed corn and early baby peas.
Gravy from meat loaf is just right on potatoes.

title: aunt pila's "ganotchers"
directions: Cook black beans with salt and a little onion until soft and most of the liquid is gone (3 hours).
Cool to room temperature.

title: chocolate fluff(frosting)
directions: Mix well and whip until thick.
Chill.

title: supper on a bread slice
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cut 1 loaf French bread in half lengthwise.
Spread meat mixture over top of bread.
Wrap aluminum foil around crust side of bread.
Leave top uncovered.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Garnish with strips of cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Cut slices and serve.

title: vegetable juice v-8
directions: To all ingredients except tomatoes add 2 cup water and simmer 1 hour or until vegetables are soft.
Add washed and quartered tomatoes and cook until soft.
Strain can.
Add sugar and salt to taste.
Reheat, either boil and put in jars or cool and freeze in Ziploc freezer bags.

title: hummingbird cupcakes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat! Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spray cupcake pans or use cupcake papers.
Fill 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen cupcakes.
May be made into layers also and iced with cream cheese frosting.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix cake as directed except use sour cream instead of water. Mix sugar, nuts and cinnamon and pour half on batter in pan. Layer apples and sugar mixture.
Add the rest of batter and bake as directed on mix.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: twinkle cake
directions: Bake cake mix in 4 thin layers.
Let cool.
Bring flour and milk to a boil.
Cool in refrigerator.
Cream until fluffy margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar, gradually.
Add flour and milk mixture.
Add vanilla and beat until fluffy, 5 to 10 minutes. Put between layers and on top of cake.

title: quick cranberry pie
directions: Grease a 10-inch quiche or pie plate.
Spread cranberries in bottom of dish.
Sprinkle with 1 cup sugar and the pecans.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add remaining sugar and beat until blended.
At low speed beat in flour, shortening and butter.
Pour batter evenly over cranberries and nuts.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: delaware water gap
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill and serve!

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Sprinkle crumbled bacon in pie crust.
In a bowl, beat eggs, half and half, salt and nutmeg.
Stir in cheese.
Pour into crust. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cube cheese.
Melt butter, then add flour; mix well.
Add milk and pieces of cheese.
Make sure all cheese is melted.
Mix cooked macaroni and cheese in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Garnish with paprika if desired.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt.
Beat until shortening is melted.
Cool to lukewarm and add eggs. Dissolve yeast in 1 cup of warm water.
Add to mixture and mix well.
Add flour.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cut out and let rise 2 hours.
Bake.

title: broccoli corn bake
directions: Combine all ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Blend cracker crumbs and butter; sprinkle on top.
Can put some cracker crumbs in casserole and 1/4 cup on top.
Bake in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fritos chili pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, bring chili to a boil.
Mix in Tabasco sauce.
In baking pan, place a layer of corn chips.
Sprinkle 1/3 of onion on chips.
Sprinkle 1/3 of cheese onto onion.
Cover with 1/3 of chili.
Repeat process of layering 3 times.
Top with corn chips.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: old-fashioned baked beans
directions: In 2-quart casserole, stir together first 5 ingredients.
Top with bacon. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 cups or 12 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter to soften.
Add sugar gradually and cream until fluffy.
Add syrup and salt; beat well.
Add eggs (one at a time), beating thoroughly after each.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean; cool.

title: saucy chicken bake
directions: Dredge chicken in flour and brown in oil.
Transfer to greased shallow baking dish.
Set aside.
Combine next 6 ingredients in skillet and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes. Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes until tender.
Garnish with orange slices and parsley.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Cool and cut into small chunks.
Mix all ingredients (except sour cream) with chicken.
Add sour cream. Mix well.
Pat in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tortilla chips
directions: With a pastry brush, paint one side of each tortilla with a light coating of oil.
Stack tortillas, oiled side up, in an even pile.
Cut stacks into eighths.
Separate the pieces and place, oil side up, on lightly greased baking sheets.
Toast at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Watch carefully!

title: nut rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm milk and pour over 5 tablespoons sugar and beaten egg yolks.
Add butter; mix well.
Add flour; mix well. Cover with a dry towel.
Set in refrigerator overnight.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Drain fruit cocktail until dry. Discard juice.
Add to the mixture, then add the cherries (cut up) and some of the juice for color and the cup of marshmallows (cut up).
Fold in large quart size Cool Whip.
Mix all together. Place in dish easy for cutting and serving.
Freeze.
Keep frozen.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Arrange potatoes in a greased pan.
Dot with butter.
Arrange chops over potatoes. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour milk over chops. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown and chops are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: red chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, shortening and eggs, beating after each addition.
Add soda to milk.
Add milk and flour alternately to mixture, then add boiling water and vanilla.
Bake in loaf pan about 9 x 13-inches.

title: country butter
directions: Soften margarine.
Add oil and buttermilk. Whip with mixer until well beaten.

title: swiss 'n chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except walnuts.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crab meat mousse
directions: Heat the first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Add lime juice. Dissolve gelatine in 1/8 cup water.
Add gelatine to hot mixture and stir until completely dissolved.
Add mayonnaise, celery and crab meat.
Put in mold and refrigerate.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Combine chopped nuts and cracker crumbs. Beat egg whites (as if you were making meringue), add sugar and baking powder. Fold into nut mixture and add vanilla. Pour into a 9 inch pie pan and bake in a slow oven 250 - 300 degrees for about 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool and top with Cool Whip. This pie may be made a day ahead of time. It's also great with ice cream on top instead of Cool Whip.

title: pineapple delight cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as usual in round cake pans; cool.
Cut layers in two.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Beat egg and vinegar. Add water.
Gradually add to dry ingredients.
Mix until you can handle.
Chill before rolling out.
Makes 5 to 6 crusts.
May be frozen.

title: rabbit stew
directions: Cover
rabbit pieces with cold salted water in a saucepan (2 to	3
tablespoons of salt to 6 to 8 cups water).
Let stand about 1 hour.

title: fried squash and potatoes
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes, squash and onion.
Coat with cornmeal, salt and pepper and drop into hot grease.
Fry until tender.
Turn fire up when done and brown.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Combine chocolate, oil and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add to chocolate mixture, mixing well. Chill several hours or overnight.

title: breakfast fruit cup
directions: Heat water and add sugar until dissolved.
Remove from heat and cool.
Pour over fresh fruit and freeze.
When ready to use, thaw until slushy.
Add a slice of banana and top with a strawberry.

title: sausage balls
directions: Crumble sausage in bowl.
Add cheese, shredded.
Blend biscuit mix in.
Make balls walnut size. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 9 dozen.
Can be frozen.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; work in shortening.
Add sweet potatoes; cut into dough.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: blue cheese coleslaw
directions: In a large bowl toss cabbage and Blue cheese.
Chill 1 hour (covered).
Mix all other ingredients except oil.
Add oil in a stream, whisking until emulsified.
Chill 1 hour.
Pour dressing over cabbage; mix well.

title: white chocolate crunch delight
directions: Melt white bark.
Combine other ingredients in large bowl. Pour chocolate over mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.

title: chicken stew
directions: Rinse chicken.
Combine with water to cover in 12-quart stockpot.
Cook until tender; cool.
Bone and chop chicken. Chill chicken and broth in separate containers.
Skim broth. Combine broth, chicken, corn, potatoes, onion, tomatoes, evaporated milk, soup, salt and pepper in 12-quart stockpot; mix well.
Simmer for 2 hours or to desired consistency.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored. Gradually add sugar, slowly stirring in brandy and rum.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites, whipped cream and milk.
More milk can be added if you care to have a very thin eggnog.
Sprinkle with nutmeg just before serving.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and oranges; add sugar and hot water and boil 2 minutes.
Add gelatin dissolved in cold water.
Cool.
Add nuts and celery and let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: french stew
directions: Mix.
Put in oven, covered, at 250° and cook for at least 6 to 7 hours.
Takes about 25 minutes to prepare ingredients. Trim fat from meat. Do not open while cooking.
Serve over wild rice or noodles. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions thin, pour salt over them and let stand 3 hours.
Drain off all the liquid.
Mix sugar, vinegar, mustard seed, turmeric and celery seed.
Bring to a boil.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Heat to a boiling point but do not boil. Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together flour, baking soda and cinnamon. Beat the sugars and butter together until light and fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla. At low speed, beat in flour mixture until blended. Fold in chocolate chips and oats. Cover. Chill for 1 hour. Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place on greased baking sheets 2-inches apart. Flatten slightly. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until browned around the edges. Cool on pans slightly. Transfer to racks to cool. Makes 4 dozen.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 9-inch pan. Spread brown sugar evenly on top. Arrange pineapple slices on sugar. Fill spaces with nuts, if desired. Mix flour, baking powder and salt. Beat egg yolks until light and add sugar gradually. Add pineapple juice and flour mix. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour batter over pineapple. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes. Turn upside down on cake plate.

title: cookie factory chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugars. Add the eggs and vanilla. In another bowl, mix flour, powdered oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Fold the 2 mixtures together, blending well. Add the chocolate chips, grated Hershey bar and the nuts and mix until well blended. Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet. Make golf ball sized cookies placed 2-inches apart. Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Break or cut lettuce into 4 qt. corning ware or pyrex dish. Layer onion, pepper, and frozen peas as listed.
Whip mayonnaise and spread on top of peas.
Sprinkle cheese over the mayonnaise. Crumble bacon strips and sprinkle on top of the salad. Cover and refrigerate.
Best if made the night before.

title: sabrina's diet dessert
directions: Mix in a 4-quart bowl and chill in refrigerator.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Mix together.
Roll into balls and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes or less, until light brown.

title: scandinavian salad
directions: In large bowl, mix vinegar, sugar, oil, water and salt.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Drain and serve (save juice).
What is left can be put back in juice and stored in refrigerator.
Keeps well.

title: peabody cheese cake
directions: Whip cream cheese by itself at a high speed to get as smooth as possible, without any lumps.
Then mix at slow speed for a few minutes to avoid air bubbles.
Mix in sour cream; add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into a graham cracker crust.
Bake in a hot water bath in a 325° oven for one hour and ten minutes.
Let cake cool in oven until it is slightly warm. Transfer to refrigerator to finish cooling.
Serve cold with desired sauce.

title: jalopies
directions: Layer ingredients in order given.
(It is easier if you mix the soup and the sour cream together.)
Be sure to have the grated cheese as your final layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: broccoli quesadilla
directions: Steam, boil or microwave broccoli until crisp-tender. Coarsely chop and set aside.
In a large nonstick frypan, heat 1 teaspoon oil.
Add onion; saute for 3 to 4 minutes to soften.
Add garlic, cumin, chili powder and cinnamon; cook 1 minute.
Add broccoli, peppers and tomatoes.
Stir well and saute for 3 to 4 minutes.
Put in a bowl and stir in cilantro.
Set aside.

title: texas candy
directions: Mix and stir on low fire for 10 minutes.
Remove from fire and add 20 regular size marshmallows and remaining ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop onto waxed paper.

title: broccoli casserole #2
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package, but do not overcook.
Drain off liquid.
Stir in cheese while broccoli is hot.
Cover and let stand until cheese melts.
Place in casserole and cover with topping made of crushed crackers mixed with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: tate's own stuffed beef roll
directions: Take 1 round steak; sprinkle with meat tenderizer.
Pound steak until 1/2-inch in thickness.
Mix stuffing mix according to directions; cover steak with stuffing mix.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Clip with toothpicks.
Make brown gravy according to directions.
Add to it the envelope of onion soup mix; mix well. Pour over steak that has been placed in a casserole or bread pan. Cover with foil.
Bake until steak is tender, 1 1/2 to 2 hours, at medium heat (about 350°).
Cut into rounds about 1 1/2 inches to serve.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 50 minutes.
Bake in Bundt pan.

title: diana's pineapple banana cake
directions: Measure the dry ingredients and sift them together.
Dice the bananas; measure the quantity and add them to the dry ingredients, along with the oil, vanilla, eggs and crushed pineapple and juice. Stir to blend but do not beat.
Pour into greased 9-inch tube pan and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Set aside to cool on a rack without removing from pan.
This cake is served without frosting.

title: beef stroganoff dip
directions: In large frying pan, brown chuck with onion, seasoned salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Pour off grease.
Add cream cheese, tomato sauce, ketchup, picante sauce and oregano, mixing well. Heat slowly and stir until mixture is well blended.
Serve in chafing dish with chips.
May be prepared ahead.
Serves 8.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Chop onion; saute onion in butter.
Add flour and milk; stir constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat; add chopped chicken.
Chill 2 hours.
Beat water and egg in bowl.
Divide chicken mixture into 8 equal portions.
Shape into croquettes. Roll each one in crumbs.
Coat with egg mixture and roll in crumbs again.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Deep fry in 375° oil until deep golden brown, about 2 or 3 minutes; drain on paper towels and serve with warm sauce.
Fresh mushroom sauce is a good choice.

title: new york cheesecake
directions: Mix and press in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside. Preheat oven to 300°.

title: chocolate passion dessert
directions: Cook fudge brownies as directed on box.
Cut brownies into 1/2-inch cubes.
Layer in 3-quart serving bowl.
Layer only 1/2 of brownies, 1 cup of strawberries, then 1 sliced banana and 1 tub of Cool Whip (your choice).
Then repeat layer starting with brownies. Cover with whole strawberries.
Serves 16.

title: italian cheese bread
directions: Cover each half of the French bread with the Mozzarella cheese. Pour enough Italian dressing on each half to cover the bread.
Broil long enough for your cheese to melt and brown. Makes a great side dish with spaghetti.

title: pecan catfish
directions: *For a real kick, add 1/4 teaspoon red pepper to the pecans.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix soup, water, rice together. Put chicken in greased casserole and cover with soup mixture. Cover with foil and bake at 375 degrees for 2 - 2 1/2 hours.

title: reuben chicken
directions: Lightly grease 9 1/2 x 11 baking pan.
Place chicken in the pan and cover with sauerkraut.
Cover sauerkraut with cheese slices and cover cheese with dressing.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours at 350 degrees.
Start checking meat with fork
at 45 minutes, if tender it's ready to eat.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Brown bacon; remove from drippings and crumble. Combine sugar and flour. Add egg, salt, vinegar and water, mixing until smooth. Pour into bacon drippings and heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens. Serve warm as a salad dressing or over boiled cut-up cabbage, braised lettuce or (Pennsylvania Dutch style) dandelion greens! You might want to try it with collard greens.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Drain oranges.
Combine pineapple, oranges, grapes, marshmallows, coconut and nuts.
Mix sour cream and sugar. Stir into fruit mixture.
Chill.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Salt and pepper to taste. Put in a greased pan.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in baking dish.
Combine flour, sugar and milk.
Mix well.
Pour into pan with melted oleo.
Pour peaches on top of mixture and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine butter with sugar, salt, flour and pepper.
Add beaten eggs
and
milk;
add
corn.
Bake
in buttered dish at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes well. Bake at 325° uncovered for 30 minutes. Bake in shallow 2-quart Corning Ware dish or 9-inch glass pie plate.
Dip with Bagel chips or crackers.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning.
Before serving, layer with lettuce, tomatoes, grated cheese and black olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: california honey punch
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over the tea bags; cover.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags and cool tea at room temperature. Dissolve gelatin dessert in 1 cup boiled water.
Stir in honey, then cold water; add to cooled tea.
At serving time, combine mixture with grapefruit juice, orange juice, lemonade, ginger ale, pink champagne or wine.
Put a block of ice in punch bowl and pour punch over it.

title: southern sunshine
directions: Mix orange
juice,
ReaLemon and sugar together.
Last add lemon lime soda.
Serve over ice.
Makes about 7 cups.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix mayo, water and soup.
Add remaining ingredients.
Fold in 3 sliced, hard-boiled eggs.
Put in greased casserole.
Sprinkle with crushed chips or cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: tangy barbecued pork chops
directions: Combine
first 11 ingredients in small saucepan.
Bring to boil;
reduce
heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Grill chops over medium
coals
for
10 minutes on each side.
Baste with sauce and
grill an additional 15 to 20 minutes or to desired degree
of doneness, basting frequently with sauce and turning meat occasionally.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: cherry fudge bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large saucepan, cook pudding as directed on the package.
Blend cake mix (dry) thoroughly into hot pudding, by hand or with electric mixer, for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add cherries.
Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate pieces.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes 40.

title: water chestnut dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Best if made day before serving.

title: slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, onion and pepper.
On top, sprinkle sugar.
Do not stir.
Bring to boil the oil, vinegar, celery seed, mustard and salt.
While hot, pour over cabbage mixture.
Put in a closed container and refrigerate.
This slaw keeps indefinitely.

title: mexicorn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Mix cooked rice, soup, corn and oleo.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 325° until bubbly, about 10 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake for 5 more minutes.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add and cream well brown sugar and white sugar.
Beat in 1 egg and then another.
Add pineapple (undrained).
Sift together and add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add chopped nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: frosting (for brownies)
directions: Combine all above ingredients, except Sugar.
Boil 2 minutes, then add sugar.

title: sweet and sour chicken(mrs. gilbert's favorite food)
directions: Cut the chicken into bite-size pieces and stir-fry in a frypan.
Boil rice until boiled completely.
Add pineapple, sweet and sour sauce and rice to the chicken.
Serves 4.
Fat grams:

title: chocolate praline cake
directions: Combine oleo, cream and brown sugar in small heavy saucepan. Heat just until oleo is melted.
Pour into 2 round cake pans and sprinkle nuts evenly.
Mix cake according to directions on the box; pour into cake pans.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from pans, placing praline side up; cool completely and spread whipped cream on 1 layer and top with other layer and top with whipped cream.
Garnish with whole nuts and chocolate curls.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Saut onion and garlic in olive oil. When onion is tender (yellow), pour in can of beans and bring to a boil on medium heat. Simmer for 10 minutes. Pour in vinegar and serve over rice.

title: baked beans
directions: Wash and soak beans overnight.	Next morning, put on to boil in same
water
with
the soda.
You may have to add more cold water to cover.
Boil until skins crack. Drain off water.

title: teriyaki walnuts
directions: In 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan, mix well sugar, ginger and garlic salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl with fork, beat egg whites with teriyaki sauce until blended.
With rubber spatula, stir in walnuts until well coated.
Transfer to jelly roll pan.
Stir with spatula until nuts are coated with sugar mixture.
Bake in preheated 250° oven.
Stir occasionally until coating is dry. Store airtight for up to 3 weeks.
Makes 2 cups.

title: egg bread
directions: Mix corn meal, salt and cold water and boil for a few minutes, stirring constantly, until it becomes thick.
Stir in milk, melted butter and egg and pour into well-greased pan or dish and bake for about 40 minutes at 400°.

title: herbed mayonnaise
directions: Blend all ingredients in small bowl.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour to blend flavors.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer until thick. Serve. Will keep in refrigerator. Excellent on pork or chicken.

title: brownies
directions: Mix ingredients together thoroughly and cook in 2 small square pans.
Bake
in 325° oven about 30 or 35 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: green tomato catsup
directions: Grind tomatoes and add salt.
Put into a cloth bag; let drain overnight.
Grind onions and peppers and drain in a separate bag. Place spices in another cloth bag in a large kettle.
Add vinegar, sugar and spices and bring to a boil.
Add drained vegetables and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir to keep from sticking.
Pack in jars and seal while hot.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: In bowl, combine pie filling with rhubarb, sugar and cornstarch. Mix well. Pour filling into 9-inch crust. Cover with top crust. Bake at 375° for 35 or more minutes or until golden brown.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Chill 1 hour.
Make dough into balls about the size of a walnut.
Roll in mixture of 2 teaspoons cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Do not flatten.
Bake at 350° about 10 to 12 minutes, until just lightly browned.

title: bill's turkey chili with beans
directions: Simmer 1 hour or until somewhat thickened.
To thicken, use flour.
Make a paste with 3 tablespoons and add slowly.
Hotter? Add 4 ounce can diced Ortega green chilies.

title: creamed cucumbers
directions: Mix the salad dressing or mayonnaise, sugar, sour cream and salt and pepper.
Put a layer of cucumbers and a layer of dressing mix twice.
Garnish with paprika or dill seed.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Cube beef and place in large saucepan with next 7 ingredients. Cook until beef is well done (about 2 hours).
Add potatoes and cook about 1/2 hour longer.
Add mixed vegetables 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add melted butter.
For best results, mix at first with spoon, then use your hands.
Then make 1-inch balls and use your thumb to indent center of each cookie. Regular cookie sheet will hold 30 cookies.
Put on cookie sheet (no butter).
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Pick up with spatula and place on cookie rack to cool.
But first put 1/2 teaspoon of fruit preserves into indentation.
Let cool 25 to 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes(the way my mother used to make them)
directions: Mix flour and soda in bowl.
Make hole in flour and add 1 egg, sugar, 1/3 cup buttermilk, vanilla and shortening.
Mix with your hands until stiff; knead well.
Roll out on cutting board 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Sprinkle with sugar. Place on greased cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
(Add more buttermilk, if needed.)
Bake at 375° until brown.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: italian sausage bread
directions: Saute onions until clear.
Cook cubed sausage in a 350° oven until done.
Drain off grease.
Follow directions on box of hot roll mix for preparing dough.
Let dough stand 5 minutes.
Break dough into 3 even loaves.
Roll out dough to size of a large pizza.
Make 3.
Mix onions and sausage and spread evenly over dough to edges.
Spread 1/3 cheese, 1/3 cayenne, 1/3 olives and 1/3 jalapenos for each one.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Place on cookie sheet seam down. Bake at 350° until golden.
Slice as desired.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Place garlic in bottom of each of 6 pint jars; add pepper. Pack tomatoes in jars.
Pour 1 teaspoon dill seed in each jar. Boil vinegar, water and salt for 5 minutes.
Pour over tomatoes. Seal jars.
Let stand for 6 weeks.
One sliced carrot may be added in each jar between tomatoes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread roll mix in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Mix together and spread on crust the sour cream, dressing mix and dill weed. Top with raw vegetables, cut up fine. Chill.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onions.
Drain well.
Add all ingredients together.
Bring to a boil.
Line serving platter with Tostitos chips.
Add mixture.
Top with grated cheese and serve.

title: apple rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add buttermilk, melted butter, 6 tablespoons sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, egg and whole wheat flour.
Stir to blend.
All all-purpose flour.
Knead dough until smooth and elastic.
Let rise in a warm place for about 40 minutes.
Punch down.
On floured board, knead dough until satiny. Divide into 3 parts.
Roll each into a rectangle.
Cut rectangle into 10 squares.
Place an apple wedge in the middle of each square.
Combine remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apple wedge.
Fold dough over apples to cover completely.
Brush with beaten egg.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes, then increase oven to 425° and bake 4 more minutes.

title: peanut muffins
directions: Mix and bake in muffin tins in moderate oven.
When cool dip muffins in thin icing made with confection sugar and milk.
Then dip in ground peanuts.

title: ropa vieja(old clothes)
directions: Cook meat in a pressure cooker with water and salt for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into 2-inch slices, then shred.
Save broth for Vermicelli Soup.
Fry in olive oil the onion, garlic, green pepper, bay leaves and oregano.
Add whole tomatoes, tomato sauce, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add shredded meat to sauce.
Serve over rice.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in sugar, salt, shortening, eggs and potatoes.
Mix in flour with hands until dough is easy to handle.
Knead on lightly floured board until smooth and elastic.
Place greased side up in greased bowl.
Cover with damp cloth and place in refrigerator.

title: baked penne
directions: Brown beef and boil pasta to package directions.
Drain both. Drain mushrooms.
Mix all ingredients and put in 9 x 9-inch pan and top with more Mozzarella.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Serves 6.

title: creamy spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in 1 tablespoon oil in water.
Mix cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, green pepper and onion. Alternate layers of spaghetti and cheese mixture. Saute ground beef.
Put over spaghetti.
Pour tomato sauce over top. Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Spaghetti sauce can also be used.
Tomato sauce gives a different flavor.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix all except 1/4 cup soup and milk together.
Fill 8 to 10 flour tortillas with mixture.
Roll seam side down in a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased.
Mix soup and milk and pour on top.
Cover pan and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Top with cheese and bake 10 to 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: dip
directions: Soak onions in sherry or water for a few minutes.
Mix ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Combine caramels and 1/2 cup of the condensed milk and melt in microwave or in double boiler.
Set aside.

title: louise's sausage casserole
directions: Tear up bread and place in a 2 1/2-quart Pyrex dish.
Brown 1 pound bulk sausage and drain off fat.
Sprinkle over bread. Spread cheese over sausage.
Beat eggs and add milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over bread and sausage and cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: brick oven casserole
directions: Melt butter or margarine in frying pan.
Cook onion and green pepper until tender.
Add ham and brown lightly.
Remove from heat and stir in mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Place dry rice in buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with tomatoes and ham mixture.
Cover with corn.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese on top. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in large mixer bowl, then beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan and cool on rack.
Split into 3 layers.
Spread about 1 cup of frosting between layers; spoon rest into center.
Chill.
Garnish with chopped nuts.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring brown sugar, butter and Karo syrup to boil in microwave. Remove and immediately add baking soda and stir.
Place popcorn and peanuts in large roasting pan.
Pour syrup over popcorn and peanuts; mix well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
When baked, put into grocery bag and shake well. Continue shaking occasionally.
Store in plastic bags or containers.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix together everything except the catsup, brown sugar, onion powder and liquid smoke.
Shape into balls using an ice cream scoop.
Place in a flat pan in one layer.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Transfer meatballs from drippings to clean pan.
In small bowl combine the catsup, brown sugar, onion powder and liquid smoke.
Pour over meatballs and bake 30 minutes.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion, celery and mushrooms in butter.
Melt cheese in top of double boiler.
Add everything and heat thoroughly.

title: tom thumb cookie bars
directions: Combine the 1/2 cup shortening, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 cup brown sugar and cream thoroughly.
Blend in the cup of sifted flour.
Spread mixture in a greased 8 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes or until delicately browned.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Thaw frozen broccoli and drain excess liquid. Mix broccoli and all other ingredients together. Pour into pan and bake at 350° until golden brown on top. Cool before slicing.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add milk, sugar, egg yolks and vanilla.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes or until thick.
Add coconut and pecans.

title: orange fruit cake
directions: Sweeten juice and pour slowly over cake after it is baked and still hot.

title: new orleans school of cooking pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bring to soft ball stage (238° to 240°). Remove from heat and stir until mixture cools and thickens. Spoon onto buttered wax paper or aluminum foil.

title: calico bean pot
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for at least 1 hour.
May also be done in crock-pot.

title: aunt sue's mexican chicken casserole(club member: laine)
directions: Mix 1/2 pound cheese with chicken, cream of chicken soup and the chilies; heat. Mix Doritos in bottom of casserole dish. Put a layer of chicken mixture. Sprinkle another layer of Doritos until both are used up. Add the remaining cheese on top. Bake at 300° for 15 minutes. This is hot with peppers. Use only 2 green peppers for milder taste.

title: brownies
directions: Start heating oven to 350°.
Place all ingredients in bowl. Stir until blended.
Turn into greased 8 x 8 x2-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cut into 2-inch squares while warm.
Makes 16.

title: hot cranberry cider
directions: In a saucepan, bring ingredients to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes.
Remove spices.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add sauce and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients except noodles.
Pour 1 cup sauce in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Layer 3 pieces of uncooked noodles over sauce.
Cover with 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Spread 1/2 of cheese mixture over sauce.
Repeat layers of noodles, 1 1/2 cups sauce and rest of cheese filling; top with lasagne noodles and then the rest of the sauce.
Cover with foil.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and bake another 10 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: mushroom-lima bake
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in oil.
Add limas.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake in 375° oven 30 minutes.

title: apple butter
directions: You will need a brass kettle.

title: marshmallow pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients; refrigerate.

title: cake without frosting
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
After mixing cake, add chocolate chips and fold in.
Pour in cake pan.
Bake according to directions on box.
Cool about 10 minutes.
Invert cake onto plate.

title: fantastic lemon cake
directions: Generously butter a 9-inch (12 cup) turk's head mold, 9-inch tube pan or 12-cup Bundt pan. Dust lightly with 2 tablespoons flour, tapping out excess. In a medium bowl combine remaining 2 3/4 cups flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for 60 minutes or, if cupcakes, for 20 minutes.

title: herb corn bread
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, onion salt, salt and sugar. Stir cornmeal and herbs into dry ingredients. Combine egg, milk and melted butter. Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir until dry ingredients are well moistened but still lumpy.
Pour into well-greased 8-inch square baking pan, muffin pan or cornstick pan. Bake at 425° for 25 to 35 minutes until top is golden brown. Serve hot.

title: clety's special
directions: Saute onion and pepper.
Brown ground meat.
Add all ingredients.
Put into casserole and season.
Add cheese on top and bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: fluffy oven eggs and bacon
directions: Grease a casserole.
Cut up bacon and fry until crisp.
Add onion and cook.
Drain.
Spread in bottom of casserole dish.
Beat Bisquick, eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over bacon.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes, uncovered, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Form into walnut-sized balls.
Place on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam and flatten with fork or fingers.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until done. Store in airtight container when cooled.

title: cheerio bars
directions: Heat the sugar and syrup to melt the sugar, but do not boil. Make sure sugar is dissolved.
Take off stove.
Add peanut butter and pour over the Cheerios which are in a large bowl.
Mix well and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan (buttered).
Pack down and let cool. Cut into bars.
Can put on frosting when cooled.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over cooled bars.

title: chicken-broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli.
Arrange broccoli in a greased shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Combine cream cheese, milk and garlic salt in a saucepan.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Pour about half the sauce over broccoli.
Top with 1 pound sliced, cooked chicken or turkey and remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; then broil until lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: linguine puttanesca
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil for the linguine.

While the water is heating, place 2 tablespoons of olive oil in a large skillet, add the garlic and cook over low heat for 5 minutes, until the garlic softens and becomes fragrant but does not brown. Add the tomatoes.
Increase heat to medium-high and cook for 10 minutes or until the tomatoes give off their juices and the sauce begins to thicken.
Add the anchovies, capers, olives and red pepper flakes.
Lower heat to medium and cook about 5 minutes longer.
As soon as the water comes to a boil, add the linguine and cook it until it is al dente.
Drain and place in a warm serving bowl.
Add the basil, parsley and remaining teaspoon of olive oil to the sauce.
Taste it and add a pinch of salt if necessary.
Spoon the sauce over the pasta; toss it well and serve at once.
Yields 4 servings.

title: dave's mushroom soup
directions: No salt needed in soup. Broth and bouillon have plenty.

title: cereal killer cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream sugars and margarine.
Add eggs; blend until smooth.
Add vanilla; cream.
Mix all dry ingredients and blend with mixture.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire racks.

title: low-fat bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon in large bowl.
Mix cereal, milk and sugar in another bowl; let stand five minutes.
Stir in egg and applesauce.
Add to flour mixture; stir just until moistened (batter will be lumpy). Spoon batter into muffin pan sprayed with no stick cooking spray, filling each cup 2/3 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or golden brown. Serve warm or may be frozen and heated in microwave.
Serves 12.

title: classic french silk pie
directions: Bake pie shell; cool.
Beat granulated sugar and butter in 1 1/2-quart bowl until light and fluffy.
Stir in vanilla, cream of tartar and chocolate.
Beat in eggs until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate until set, 3 to 4 hours.
Or cover with plastic wrap and freeze at least 8 hours.

title: easter egg nest cookies
directions: In large bowl, break up shredded wheat biscuits until quite fine.
Set aside. Melt the chocolate chips and peanut butter until smooth.
Pour over shredded wheat biscuits and mix well.
Drop by spoons onto wax paper.
Shape each mound into a circle and form a small hole in the center.
Cookies take quite long to set up so you have time to shape them to look like nests.
Put 3 jelly beans in the center of each cookie. Let set several hours or overnight to firm.
You can use a teaspoon and then shape them with the small end of a melon baller.

title: tressia's tamale pie
directions: Brown ground chuck, onion and green pepper in skillet.
Add chili powder, salt, sugar and garlic.
Mix in the olives, corn and cheese.
Put in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix corn bread mix according to box directions; pour over top.
Bake until corn bread is done, approximately 20 to 30 minutes, at 400°.

title: chicken and rice #1
directions: Brown chicken for 10 minutes.
Cover the bottom of pan with rice.
Put chicken on top.
Cover with cream of chicken soup.
Add enough water to cover chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef stew(crock-pot)
directions: Place meat in crock-pot.
Mix flour, salt and pepper and pour over meat; stir to coat meat with flour.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to mix well.
Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours (high 5 to 6 hours).
Stir stew thoroughly before serving.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Stir yogurt, mixing the fruit. Pour into a bowl. Add the Cool Whip and mix well. Put into the pie crust. Cover and refrigerate. Best if chilled overnight.

title: rolled pizza
directions: Allow pizza dough to rise several hours.

title: kentucky burgoo
directions: Simmer meat until well done.
Defat liquid and separate meat from bones.
Add remaining ingredients and cook very slowly for at least 4 hours.
The mixture should be very thick.
Add water from time to time to keep from sticking.
Season to taste.
Makes about 36 cups.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together.
Put in 350° preheated oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberries romanoff
directions: Clean and hull 2 quarts of strawberries.
Sweeten with sugar. Whip vanilla ice cream and fold in cream (whipped).
Add the juice of 1 lemon, rum and Cointreau.
Pour cream over strawberries.
Serves 8.

title: potluck chicken
directions: Mix oleo with stuffing.
Put half in bottom of pan.
Put chicken next, then soup and broth.
Pour rest of stuffing on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and fold into Miracle Whip salad dressing.
Chill.

title: corn bread
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in all other ingredients and stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Bone the chicken and soak in water for 30 minutes.
Flour lightly and brown in 1-inch oil. Arrange in a layer in a shallow casserole. Cover with Sauce.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, cooking oil and vinegar.
Sift flour and soda together. Add flour to mixture.
Add milk slowly.
Add flavoring and cake coloring.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 layers.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl and add eggs and oil.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, undrained pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove and cool completely. Spread frosting between layers, on top and sides.
Sprinkle with 1 cup nuts.

title: cheese and corn chowder
directions: Simmer the water, potatoes, carrots, celery, salt and pepper for 10 minutes.
Add the corn and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in the milk and cheese and heat but do not boil.

title: jambalaya
directions: Other meats or red beans may be substituted.

title: shrimp with lobster sauce
directions: Saute onions or scallions with Italian sausage meat (cut up in small pieces).
Add shrimp.
Cook about 3 minutes.
Then add soup stock (College Inn, etc.).
Mash in small piece of garlic. Thicken with cornstarch.
Then fold in egg without beating.
Serve on rice.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, put the cherry pie filling; spread evenly.
Dump dry cake mix onto the cherry layer.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle pecans or walnuts over the cake mix.
Put 1 stick of butter cut in thin slices over the top.
Bake for 50 minutes in a 325° oven to a golden brown.
Serve cooled with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Mix water with pickling salt and boil.
Let cool.
Slice cucumbers into gallon jar.
Pour water over cucumbers and let sit 14 days.
Drain and rinse.
Cover with cold water to which alum is added.
Let set 24 hours.
Drain water and cover with white vinegar.
Put pickling spice in a bag and add to jar.
Let set 24 hours.
Drain vinegar.
Add 3 cups sugar.
Stir well.
Repeat sugar for a total of 3 days.
They make their own juice. May be left in jar or put in smaller jars. They do not need to be sealed.

title: better-than-sex-cake
directions: Bake the cake in a 13 x 9 pan according to package directions.
Let cake cool for about 20 minutes.
Spread the pineapple over the cake with the juice.

title: leek and potato soup(this recipe is about 125 years old)
directions: Split leeks or scallions in half and cut in small pieces.
Cut up potatoes.
In water, put potatoes, salt and barley and let come to a boil; cook about 1 hour.
Mash the potatoes.
Thin out soup with a cup of milk, more if needed.
Again let it come to a boiling point, turn off heat and add 4 tablespoons of butter (no substitute or it won't give same flavor).

title: brown onion sauce
directions: Fry the onions in butter and a dash of sugar to a nice brown; thicken a little with flour and add enough strong beef broth to make a thick sauce.
Season with cayenne or black pepper and rub through a sieve.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine and set aside dry ingredients.
In large bowl, beat the brown sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Stir in flour mixture; beat until well blended.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured pans (9 x 13-inch, two 9-inch or Bundt pan).
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or frost.

title: double boiler bread pudding
directions: Prepare bread.
Remove crust and butter.
Stack all slices and cut into cubes (4 to 6 cubes).
Put sugar in boiler add cubed bread, milk and light brown sugar.
Pour on top of 4 eggs, well beaten.
Do not stir.
Cover and cook about 1 1/4 hours on medium heat.
Do not uncover until ready to serve.
Top with whip cream. Can be warmed if any left in double boiler.

title: cherry-almond coffee cake squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Mix sour cream, water and eggs in large bowl. Stir in cake mix (dry) until moistened.
(Batter will be slightly lumpy.)
Spread in pan.
Drop pie filling by generous spoonfuls onto batter.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until cake springs back when touched lightly; cool.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Drizzle with glaze.
Makes 15 servings.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Alternately add the rest of the dry and wet ingredients.
Beat all ingredients at least 2 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Mix all ingredients in skillet. Cook 20 minutes or until meat is done, stirring often. Add water if necessary. Serve on warmed or toasted buns.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix the ingredients in the order listed.
Put in 9 x 13-inch floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream.

title: sugared sour cream nuts
directions: With a wooden spoon, mix together sour cream and sugar.
Cook on medium heat to 223°, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla extract and English walnuts.
Stir until completely coated.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.
When cool, store nuts in airtight container.
Can be stored up to 3 months.

title: old time gingerbread
directions: Pour
boiling water over shortening.
Add sugar, molasses
and beaten egg.
Beat thoroughly. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix until smooth. Pour into greased 8-inch square cake pan. Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for about 35 minutes.	Serve alone or with a frosting.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix all together.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sugar-free frozen punch mix
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sugar substitute to taste.
Cool.
Add lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Mix well. Bag and freeze.
Thaw until mushy and add 2 to 3 quarts diet 7-Up per bag.
Makes 4 bags.

title: pork chops and spanish rice
directions: Cook
pork
chops
in small amount of oil until lightly browned.
Place
in deep baking pan.
On each pork chop, place 1 tablespoon	uncooked
rice	(or more), 1 onion ring, 1 bell pepper ring and a tomato.	Chop celery about in the pan.
Mash the tomato a little to cover the other vegetables better.
Put a
little catsup
on	top
of each tomato.
Season with salt, pepper, Worcestershire
sauce, garlic powder or other seasonings
to taste.
Pour tomato juice in pan and enough water to cover rice. Cover tightly with foil.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour
and
15 minutes or until liquid is dissolved and rice is done.
Each
pork chop
makes
1 serving and is practically a meal in itself.
(I like to add some extra rice.)

title: omelet squares
directions: Place cheese slices on the bottom of a greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Cut bacon into bite size pieces and layer over cheese.
Sprinkle mushrooms, green pepper and onion on top.
In a medium bowl, beat eggs, salt and pepper together with a fork.
Pour over ingredients in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: dirty rice(for a crowd!)
directions: In a large roaster, separate ground meat with a cup of water; then brown.
Add chopped onions, bell peppers, celery and shallots.
Cover
and cook
until all liquid has disappeared.
Add 2 cans of soup and a little water.
Add Kitchen Bouquet for color. Cook 4 cups of rice; add to meat mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 20 people.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix fruit cocktail, sugar, soda, salt, flour and eggs, mixing well for about 2 minutes.
Add 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar and serve with whipping cream or ice cream, if desired.
Use 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: apple pie in bag
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients with fork in pie pan.
Press in bottom and on side.
Use a deep 10-inch pie dish.
Mix the sugar, 3 tablespoons flour and cinnamon with sliced apples.
Put into crust.
Make crumb mixture with 1 cup flour, 1/2 cup sugar and soft margarine.
Put on top of apples.
Add a little cinnamon on top (optional).
Slide into paper bag and fold under.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix flour, milk, sugar, nutmeg, salt and cinnamon in small bowl.
Mix with a fork until crumbly.
Add soft margarine. Sprinkle crumb mixture on top of apple mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Will serve six.

title: chicken tinola(chicken stew)
directions: Saute garlic, onions, ginger and chicken.
Season with salt and ground pepper.
Simmer over moderate heat for 10 minutes.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 25 minutes.
Add green spinach leaves and cook for 2 minutes.
Add yellow chilies and cook for 3 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain corn and mix all ingredients together. Cover and refrigerate about 2 hours before serving.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate.

title: french vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix and pour into an ice cream freezer.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: chicken and broccoli with mushrooms
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Mix margarine and flour together in saucepan.
Cook briefly over medium heat. Blend in chicken broth, stirring constantly, until thickened and smooth.
Stir in mushrooms and their liquid.

title: shallalai
directions: Brown green peppers and onions in heavy skillet with just enough Crisco to cook.
When tender, add ground beef and cook on medium heat until meat is browned.
Add soup and pimentos and cook on low for about 10 minutes.
When ready to serve, open 1 or 2 cans of Chinese noodles and pour over top of Shallalai.
Serves 6.

title: cauliflower mustard pickles
directions: Divide large head of cauliflower into pieces and boil with a dozen white button onions, until about half done.
Drain and add a dozen dill pickles, cut in pieces, to 2-quarts of vinegar, 2 cups sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Bring to a boil.
Mix together flour, ground mustard, turmeric powder and cold water to mix.
Add this to boiling vinegar and continue to boil for 5 minutes longer.
Pour boiling mixture over pickles and seal in jars.
Makes about 4-quarts.

title: sausage and cheese appetizer
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain.
Add lemon juice.
Saute onions, parsley and bell pepper.
Add soup and cheese.
After sauces are well blended, pour over broccoli (in casserole).
Top with crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: orange jello fluff
