directions: Mix the orange jello and the boiling water together; cool. Add the orange sherbet and beat with mixer or eggbeater.
Fold in whipped cream substitute.
Add the drained mandarin orange slices and crushed pineapple.
Mix, pour in mold and refrigerate until firm.

title: mary's potato casserole
directions: Cover bottom of casserole dish (9 x 13 x 2-inch) with 2 pounds of hash browns.
Sprinkle with small chopped onions.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Melt 2 sticks margarine and pour over potatoes (saving some for top).
Heat and mix 1 (10 ounce) can cream of chicken soup, 16 ounce sour cream and 1 (16 ounce) Cheez Whiz. Pour on potatoes.
Mix remaining margarine with 2 cups crushed corn flakes.
Spread on top of casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit pudding
directions: For dieters, use lite fruit and pudding.

title: frozen punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Combine sugar and cold water and bring to a boil.
Add sugar mixture to jello mix.
Add lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Put in containers and freeze.
Bring out of freezer 3 hours before time to use.
Place in punch bowl and pour ginger ale in and stir.
Serve.

title: puffed turkey sandwiches
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spread bread with cranberry sauce.
Place slices on baking sheet; top each slice with turkey.
Beat egg whites and mustard until stiff; fold in mayonnaise.
Spread mixture evenly over turkey.
Bake for about 10 minutes, or until topping is golden brown.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: candy bar cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed and reserve one layer for later use at a later date. Cool cake and frost sides and top with a thin layer of cream.
Put rest of cream on top in lattice design with a border around the edge. Spoon strawberry pie filling into every other section. Spoon peach filling into remaining sections. Sprinkle almonds on top.
Break candy bars into thirds, making 15 squares.
Arrange smooth sides out with edges overlapping. Chill until serving time.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream butter, shortening, oleo and sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Sift all dry ingredients except cinnamon and sugar; add to egg mixture. Mix thoroughly and put in the refrigerator overnight. Roll into balls the size of a walnut; roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture. Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Let stand a minute before removing from cookie sheet. Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: kim's fancy fast chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Top each piece with slice of Swiss cheese.
If using mushrooms, lay them over the Swiss cheese.
Mix the soup with wine and pour over the chicken.
Spread stuffing mix over top and drizzle melted butter over the top. Bake in preheated oven for 45 to 55 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, Cool Whip and egg.
Make into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
(You may want to use two spoons to handle dough, as it is very sticky.)
Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach - mix all ingredients. Heat in microwave until melted. Stir, serve with crackers or bread.

title: steakhouse london broil
directions: In large plastic food bag or 13 x 9 inch glass baking dish, blend recipe mix, oil and vinegar.
Add steak, turning to coat. Close bag, or cover, and marinate in refrigerator 30 minutes to 3 hours.
Remove meat from marinade, discarding marinade.
Grill or broil, turning occasionally, until desired doneness.
Slice meat thinly across the grain.

title: shrimp cocktail sauce
directions: Place all ingredients together in a jar and shake until blended.
Chill in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans until tender, drain well.
Melt Velveeta cheese in mushroom soup.
In baking dish, mix green beans with soup mixture.
Top with French fried onion rings.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes, until cheese mixture is bubbling.

title: peach alaska pie
directions: Soften 1-quart ice cream until it can be stirred easily.
Peel peaches, slice thin and stir into ice cream.
Spread mixture into cooled pie shell and freeze until firm.

title: marinated kraut
directions: Heat white vinegar, wine vinegar and sugar together.
Mix together sauerkraut, onion, bell pepper and pimiento.
Pour vinegar mixture over vegetables.
Chill for several hours.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix wafers, orange concentrate, coconut and nuts; make into small balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
For smoother balls, blend coconuts and nuts in blender.

title: chocolate chip chilled dessert
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler; add egg yolks and mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add sugar and vanilla.
Add nuts and fold in whipped cream.
Break cake into pieces.
Put 1/2 of cake pieces in 9 X 13 pan and pour 1/2 of chocolate mixture over.
Put remainder of cake pieces
on top, then remainder of chocolate mixture.
Chill 6 to 8 hours.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube pan.
In a large bowl cream together the shortening, butter and sugar.
Add the eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift the flour and baking powder together and add the mixture to the creamed mixture alternately with the milk and extracts.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Let the cake cool in the pan for about 15 minutes. Serves 8.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Fry the bacon and remove from pan. Brown the onion in the bacon grease. Add the beans, mustard, sugar, catsup and crumbled bacon. Mix well and pour into a casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 hour.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil; add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add flavorings, then nuts and prunes.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: the ultimate potato soup for 8
directions: Melt shortening and saute the washed potatoes, parsley and onions. Cook, covered, on low heat for 15 to 20 minutes; do not add liquid. Add the stock and continue cooking; add salt, pepper and bay leaf. Whisk the cream and flour together and slowly add to boiling stock. Simmer for at least 30 minutes; remove bay leaf and serve. For added flavor, add a dollop of sour cream just before serving.

title: chili
directions: Chop onion and green pepper. Crumble beef into heated frypan. Add onion and pepper and cook until tender. Drain off fat. Stir in rest of ingredients. Boil gently 45 minutes until thickens. Yields 6 servings.

title: creamsicle cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in 9 x 13-inch pan. When done, make holes in cake with a wooden spoon. Mix Jell-O with 1/2 cup hot water and 1/2 cup cold water. Pour over cake, making sure it goes into holes. Refrigerate for 20 minutes.

title: baked rice custard
directions: Scald milk in the top of a double boiler.
Slightly beat eggs and combine with sugar and salt in a 1 1/2 quart casserole. Gradually stir in scalded milk, add cooked rice, raisins and vanilla. Sprinkle with nutmeg and place in oven.
Bake at 325 until set, about 50-60 minutes.
Makes 6-1/2 cup servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain well.
Mix in rice, Cheez Whiz, chestnuts and soup. Put in large casserole and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: brownie sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix together sugar, flour and soda. Set aside.
In a saucepan, mix together oleo, Crisco, cocoa and water.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Pour the boiling mixture over the dry ingredients and mix well.
Add the buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: can't fail fudge
directions: Combine margarine, milk and sugar in large boiler.
Bring to a boil and boil for 8 minutes exactly.
Remove from heat; add chocolate chips and marshmallow cream. Stir or beat just a while to melt everything.
Add vanilla and mix in.
Add nuts and pour into dish greased with margarine.

title: butterhorns
directions: Rub together
yeast
and sugar until syrupy.
Add lukewarm milk with shortening.
Add beaten eggs and 1/2 cup sugar. Sift together and
add 4 cups flour and 1 teaspoon salt.
Stir until thoroughly	mixed.	Let
rise
until
light
hours). Divide into 2
sections and roll out like pie.
Cut each "pie" like pie into 16 wedges after buttering generously with melted butter
or margarine.	Roll
from
outside
in
and
place
in greased baking sheet 2-inches apart.
Let rise until double in size, 1 hour. Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: sausage cake
directions: Combine sugar, sausage and hot coffee.
Take a little hot coffee out and dissolve soda.
Combine all dry ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 275° to 300° for 1 hour or until done.
May be stored as a fruit cake.

title: venison marinade
directions: Sprinkle venison roast with lemon pepper marinade.
Rub it into the meat with the hands.
Place strips of thin salt pork over the top of meat; wrap with foil and place in preheated oven (400°).
Get meat hot, about 5 to 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325°.
Medium roasts should be ready in 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: oriental sauteed rice
directions: In large skillet, melt oleo and saute onion and pepper.
Add rice, water chestnuts and parsley.
Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.
Stir in grated cheese and continue cooking 5 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: tuna cucumber cups
directions: Make the cucumber cup: Wash and peel, using a vegetable peeler. Cut cucumbers into 3/4-inch round pieces. Remove seed centers.

title: chew bread
directions: Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan, greased but not floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can also use coconut or chocolate chips.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients in heavy saucepan until color is almost that of finished product (light golden brown).
Add the butter, baking soda and peanuts.
Stir and pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Cool and crack.

title: baked lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and add salt and oregano.
Add this to sauce in 2 (8 x 8-inch) or 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan.
Spread thick layer of sauce on bottom.
Layer on noodles.
Layer Ricotta, Mozzarella, meat sauce, etc.
Put Parmesan cheese on top.
May be frozen.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp or crab bisque
directions: Make a roux of flour and butter. Slowly add milk, stirring constantly.
Add wine, half and half, lemon juice and seafood. Add cayenne, salt and pepper to taste,
Stir until thickened.
Serve with oyster crackers.

title: tea room waffles
directions: Mix and sift pastry flour, salt and sugar.
Beat 3 egg yolks until light and lemon-colored.
Add sour cream and beat into the sifted dry ingredients.
Fold in 3 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake on hot waffle irons.
Serve hot with chicken a la king or creamed chicken.

title: quick french onion soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon in boiling water.
Add Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve in warmed bowls with 1 Melba toast and 1 1/2 teaspoons of Parmesan cheese sprinkled on top of each.

title: santa fe salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl; stir well.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Yield: 3 1/2 cups, 0 gram of fat.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, bananas and sour cream; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix until all flour is dampened. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
This is a very moist bread.

title: arros con pollo(rice with chicken)
directions: Brown the chicken, add onions, green pepper, bay leaf, garlic, salt, vinegar, tomato sauce, olive oil (unless used to brown chicken), cumin and some wine or beer.
Cover to cook for 15 to 20 minutes on low heat.
Add rice and bijol or saffron.
Add rest of wine or beer, peas and asparagus.
Cover and put in oven at 325° or finish cooking on top of the stove for 30 minutes.
Check, if rice is not fully cooked, add more wine or beer until rice is tender.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together well.
Chill at least overnight.
Best if chilled for 24 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased baking dish. Sprinkle top with additional 1 1/2 cups herb stuffing.
Bake for 40 minutes at 375°.
Serves 10.

title: stromboli
directions: Break bread dough in half; roll out half in a little flour, stretching as you roll in shape of a rectangle.
Lengthwise put a layer of salami, layer of pepperoni, layer of cheese and layer of ham.
Fold ends in and sides together to form a loaf.
Press seam down.
Take beaten egg and brush on top.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Repeat second half.
Bake at 350°
for 25 minutes. Let set 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: mom's strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix everything.
Makes 2 dozen cupcakes or 1 loaf cake.
Bake cupcakes at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Bake loaf at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: dried fruit candy
directions: Put all ingredients except coconut in food grinder or processor.
Process until well mixed.
Press into buttered 8-inch square baking dish. Chill well. Cut into squares and roll in coconut.
Store in airtight tins.

title: spinach dip
directions: * Spinach takes about 6 hours to thaw in refrigerator.
Make dip 24 hours in advance.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place half of bread cubes in buttered 9 x 14-inch pan.
Cover with ham and cheese.
Then with remaining bread cubes.
Combine eggs, milk and salt.
Beat and pour over bread.
Drizzle melted oleo on top.
Refrigerate at least 12 to 24 hours.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes, uncover and bake 15 minutes longer until done.

title: low-fat festive crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Serve with assorted fresh vegetables or crackers.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onions in 1/4 cup butter or margarine.
Mix in flour. Blend in chicken broth, clam juice, white wine, cream and oregano. Simmer 3 minutes.
Stir in 1/4 cup Parmesan and set aside.
Melt remaining 1/4 cup butter.
Add chopped garlic and mushrooms and cook quickly.
Set aside.
Cook vermicelli according to package directions.
Combine chicken broth mixture, mushrooms and cooked vermicelli with the shrimp.
Pour into casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with remaining Parmesan.
Bake uncovered at 375° until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bacon stuffed mushrooms
directions: Fry bacon; drain and crumble.
Blend with mayonnaise, onion, cheese and seasoned salt.
Fill mushroom caps with cheese mixture and place on greased baking sheet.
Cover and bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.
May be prepared ahead.
Serves 16.

title: carrot bulghur quickie
directions: Pour the boiling water over the bulghur and let stand for 10 minutes.
Heat the oil in frying pan and stir the carrots around in it for 3 minutes.
Drain the bulghur and stir it into carrots. Add the chopped eggs and most of the parsley.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Continue cooking for 2 to 3 minutes; stir in remaining parsley and serve.

title: cheesy chicken broccoli bake
directions: Combine all ingredients (except shredded cheese) into a medium pan. Top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 50 minutes. Let set 15 minutes before serving.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Add spaghetti and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Crumble browned hamburger on top.
Sprinkle with onion and garlic salt.
Layer pepperoni.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix cornmeal with flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add egg and milk; blend in melted shortening.
Mix well.
Dip wieners in batter.
Fry in deep fat.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Mix meat and spaghetti sauce together.
In a 11 x 14-inch pan, layer ingredients starting with spaghetti sauce mixture, then noodles (uncooked), cottage cheese, Mozzarella and then Parmesan cheese.
Continue to layer.
Save 1 cup of sauce.
Cover and bake for 90 minutes at 350°.
Check after 30 minutes.
If dry, add sauce.
If not, save sauce and serve as a dipping sauce for French bread.

title: oatmeal waffles
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together flour, oats, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
In small bowl, mix eggs, milk, butter and brown sugar together.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir to blend.
Pour batter onto preheated grids of greased waffle iron. (Amount of batter will vary with size of waffle iron.)
Close lid quickly.
Do not open during baking.
Use fork to remove baked waffle.
Top with fresh fruit, yogurt or syrup.
Yields 12 (4-inch) square waffles.

title: hamburger-broccoli bake
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Mix together the other ingredients. Place in oiled baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: my mother-in-law's blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 3 cups hot water.
Add other juice and all. Pour into long dish and congeal.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan.
In large bowl, sift flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add other ingredients and stir until mixed (hand mix only).
Pour into pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Blend ingredients and pour into a graham cracker crust.
Store in refrigerator until chilled.

title: layer cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch pan melt butter.
Pour in crumbs.
Pour Eagle Brand milk on crumbs.
Top evenly with chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Press down.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Cool before cutting into squares.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix margarine and vanilla wafer crumbs well and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat powdered sugar, eggs and whipped margarine with mixer for 8 minutes.
Pour over crust and spread evenly.
Slice bananas over whipped mixture in pan.
Spread pineapple over bananas.
Spread 1 large container of softened Cool Whip over pineapple.
Garnish with chopped nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Set aside.
Mix broccoli, cauliflower, bacon, onion and raisins.
Mix with mayonnaise mixture and chill.

title: seafood and wild rice casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms, celery, onion and pepper.
Add pimiento and soup.
Prepare rice according to package directions.
Add whole shrimp and crabmeat to cooked rice.
Moisten with milk to medium consistency.
Spoon into casserole and bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: praline candy
directions: Cook all ingredients except pecans on medium heat, stirring frequently. At softball stage, remove from heat and whip with spoon for 1 minute. Stir in pecans and drop by spoonfuls onto buttered tray.

title: easy oriental soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer until vegetables and tortellini are tender. Serve with egg rolls or other favorite Oriental dishes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add flavoring; stir in coconut.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Place in a cold oven.
Set the temperature at 350°.
Bake for one hour and 15 minutes, or until done.

title: gibb's favorite side dish(wild rice)
directions: Cook rice as in basic recipe (washed and boiled for 45 minutes).
Fry bacon crisp and drain.
Saute onions and celery in butter, add mushrooms and seasonings.
When cooked, mix with wild rice and serve as side dish.
This is ample serving for 4.

title: brandon's taco pie
directions: Drain, then mash beans.
Roll out bean dough like a pie crust. Cut into 4 or 5 saucer sized crusts.
Fry in hot oil; set aside. Put chili on half the crust.
Fold to make a half moon.
Sprinkle with onion and cheese.
Bake at 325° until cheese melts.

title: curried tuna
directions: Finely chop and peel apples.
Cook apples and onion in oleo until tender.
Blend in flour, curry powder and salt.
Add milk. Cook, stirring constantly until thick.
Drain and break tuna into large pieces.
Add tuna, ginger and lemon juice.
Mix carefully. Heat and serve over rice or noodles.

title: best big-batch tomato sauce
directions: In an 8-quart Dutch oven over medium heat in hot salad oil, cook onions, carrots, green peppers and garlic until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes and remaining ingredients. Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium-low. Partially cover Dutch oven and cook 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Makes about 9 pints.
(Each pint is enough to serve over one 8 ounce package of spaghetti, cooked.
Or use sauce in Swiss steak, pizza, lasagna or Eggplant Parmigiana.
Freezes well.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add eggs one at a time. Beat well, add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and vanilla. Mix well and add to combined fruit, nuts and coconut. Bake at 300 degrees for one hour. test if not done, cook 10 or 15 mins. more.

title: easy new england clam chowder(microwave)
directions: Place onion and butter in 4-quart casserole.
Cook on High for 5 minutes or until onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper as desired.
Cook on High for 15 minutes or until heated through.
Stir 1 or 2 times during cooking.

title: pineapple carrot cake
directions: Sift together the flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice, cloves and salt. Beat together the sugar and oil until well blended and adding one egg at a time.
Add vanilla. Gradually add dry ingredients, beating well after each addition. Combine nuts with 1 teaspoon flour. Stir in nuts, carrots and pineapple. Pour into greased and floured sheet pan.
Bake at 370° for 20 minutes. Cool on rack. Best frosted with cream cheese icing.

title: crawfish etouffe
directions: Saut chopped seasoning in butter until clear.
Add in crawfish tails and simmer.
In a mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add to crawfish mixture and simmer until warm. Serve over steamed rice for etouffe.

title: ham and cheese breakfast "quiche"
directions: In a 9 x 9-inch pan (spray bottom lightly with Pam), layer bread and ham.
Mix eggs, milk and pepper.
Pour over bread and ham.
Top with cheese and pats of butter.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until set.
(My family's traditional Christmas breakfast.)

title: vegetable stuffed halibut
directions: Thaw halibut.
Simmer onion, celery, mushrooms and carrot in covered pan with butter and water, 5 minutes.
Add parsley, lemon juice, 1/2 teaspoon salt and rosemary.
Mix thoroughly.
Season steaks with salt and pepper.
Place one steak in oiled baking pan. Cover with vegetable stuffing.
Put the second steak on top. Sprinkle with chopped bacon.
Bake at 375° for approximately 20 to 25 minutes or until halibut flakes when tested with a fork. Garnish with parsley and lemon slices.
Serves 6.

title: oyster stew
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine the undrained oysters and salt. Cook over medium heat about 5 minutes or until oysters curl around the edges.
Stir in milk, cream and hot pepper sauce.
Heat through.
Season to taste.
Sprinkle each serving with paprika; if desired, top with a pat of margarine or butter.
Makes 4 main-dish servings.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Saute beef, onion and bell pepper, then add other ingredients in order.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add vegetables; simmer another 15 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Slice stem ends from peppers; scoop out seeds.
Blanch in boiling salted water 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine ground beef, onions, rice, steak sauce and ketchup.
Stuff peppers.
Arrange in greased baking dish.
Top with extra sauce, if desired.
Bake in 350° oven 45 to 50 minutes or until meat is cooked.

title: quick root beer
directions: Dissolve sugar in water, then add the extract.
Mix well and place in a gallon jug.
Jug should only be 3/4 of the way full. Stand without lid for 6 hours in a warm place.
Fill with water, put lid on and cool.
Will be ready in about 2 or 3 days.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: *May substitute 1 pound cooked and drained ground beef for sausage.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Put chicken, bread cubes, celery salt, pepper and onion mixed together in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook flour, butter and broth until thick.
Pour over beaten eggs.
Mix and pour over chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick punch
directions: Scoop 1 quart sherbet (any flavor) into punch bowl.
Carefully add three 1 pint (12 ounce) bottles lemon-lime carbonated beverage.
Ladle into punch cups.
Makes 25 to 30 (4 ounce) servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Blend flour and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, mixing remaining ingredients and put in raw shell.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes. It may be too long, so take out before cooking dries pie.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs until well blended.
Add vanilla, vinegar and meal.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Cook in 300° oven 35 minutes.
One-half cup of coconut may be added if desired or 1 teaspoon lemon flavoring.
Makes 2 pies.

title: lill's gingersnaps
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg, molasses and vanilla; mix.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mix.
Chill mixture.
Roll in balls in hands.
Dip in sugar.
Flatten on cookie sheet and bake at 325° until done.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Crumble into mixture the yeast; stir until yeast is dissolved.
Stir in egg.
Add shortening; mix in flour, half at a time.
Round up dough, kneading is unnecessary.
Place in greased bowl and rub surface of dough with soft shortening.
Cover tightly with wax paper, then with damp cloth.
Place in refrigerator until ready to use.
Dampen cloth occasionally and as it rises, punch down dough.
When fresh rolls are desired, remove dough from refrigerator; cut off amount needed and return remaining dough to refrigerator.
Shape into rolls and place in greased baking pan; cover with damp cloth and let rise until impression remains when dough is touched gently with finger (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Bake in 350° to 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: white clam sauce
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil.
Stir in flour, salt, white pepper, oregano and parsley.
Stir constantly until mixture boils.
Add enough dairy cream to reserved clam juice to make 2 cups of liquid.
Slowly add liquid to flour mixture, stirring constantly, until it boils.
Stir in clams.
Keep warm until ready to serve. Use with any kind of spaghetti.

title: chicken stuffed shells
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients with stuffing. Stuff shells. Combine soups and water and sour cream. Spray dish with Pam (dish big enough to hold 25-30 shells). Put some soup in bottom of dish. Lay shells in single layer and top with remaining soup. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
Mix remaining four ingredients.
In glass 9 x 13-inch dish, put 1/2 of cracker mixture in bottom of dish.
Cover with soup mixture.
Put remaining crackers on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: butter bean bake
directions: Saute bacon and onion; drain and crumble bacon.
Mix beans, onion and bacon and cover with tomato soup and 1 cup brown sugar mixed together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed mushroom appetizer
directions: Clean the mushrooms. Remove stems and chop fine. Saute chopped stems with butter or margarine. Add garlic, onion powder and 1 tablespoon wine.
Add crumbs and cheese.
Add 1 cup broth and simmer.
If mixture is too dry, add a little water.
Stuff the mushroom caps.
Place caps into casserole pan. Add 1 cup broth and 1 cup white wine to bottom of pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Dip chicken in spread.
Coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in prepared pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: granny's easy risotto
directions: Place chicken in a large pot with margarine.
Fry until slightly tan.
Add celery and onions.
Cook until translucent. Add 4 cups of water and salt. Cook until tender.
Remove chicken. Cool.
Cut into small chunks.

title: currant venison roast
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Wash and pat dry the venison roast. Using a knife, make a half-dozen 2-inch long by 2-inch deep slices in the roast.
Deeply insert a rolled bacon rasher into each 2-inch deep slice.
Salt and pepper the roast and place into a roasting pan.
Place roast, uncovered, into the 450° oven for 15 minutes to sear and seal in juices.

title: baked pork chops with apples
directions: Wipe chops with a damp cloth.
Brown slowly, but well on both sides in a hot greased skillet.
Sprinkle with salt.
Core and slice unpared apples 1-inch thick.
Arrange on top of pork chops. Add water and sprinkle lightly with sugar.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until chops are tender.

title: oyster pie
directions: Put 1/2 of oysters in pie dish.
Cover with a layer of oysterettes.
Dot with butter.
Cover with sweet milk.
Put another layer oysters, oysterettes, butter and milk.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: whole wheat rolls(for bread machine)
directions: Place ingredients in bread machine. Select the dough cycle. When finished, punch down dough.
Separate dough into approximately 20 pieces.

title: strawberry glace pie
directions: Wash, drain and hull 1 quart strawberries.
Arrange 3 cups of berries in baked pie shell.
Simmer remaining berries and 2/3 cup water about 3 minutes.
Blend and add to boiling mixture sugar, cornstarch and 1/3 cup water.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Cool and pour over berries in shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix vegetables and sprinkle with sugar. Boil remaining ingredients for 3 minutes. Pour over cabbage and mix well. Cover and refrigerate. Stir before serving. This will keep up to three weeks.

title: bloat buster
directions: Heat oil in saucepan over medium heat.
Add onions and celery; cover and cook, stirring until tender, 5 minutes.
Stir in garlic; cook 30 seconds.
Add beans, squash, carrots, chicken broth, water, lemon peel, pepper and thyme.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and boil gently, uncovered, until vegetables are tender, 20 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Boil cabbage about 5 minutes.
Brown meat with onion, salt and pepper.
Drain both.
Mix together and place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: In a large pot, brown beef, onion and pepper until lightly sauteed.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining
ingredients, except cheese. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with cheese to sprinkle on top.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli and onion together.
Drain.
In a separate bowl, mix together cream of mushroom soup, mayonnaise, eggs, 3/4 cup cheese, salt and pepper.
Add broccoli and onions to the soup mixture and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle 1/2 cup grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: miniature nut rolls
directions: Blend 1 pound butter and cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add flour.
Blend until bowl comes clean.
Refrigerate until firm, usually overnight.
Roll dough out in 10x sugar, not flour, and cut into 4 pieces.
Mix last 4 ingredients to make nut mixture.
(Dough should be divided into about 33 balls before cutting each into 4 pieces.)
Spread nut mixture on widest part of the pie slice.
Turn in edges and back, then roll so the tip is on the bottom of the cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° about 15 to 17 minutes until lightly brown.
Check during baking.
Roll in 10x sugar.

title: nut squares
directions: Mix the brown sugar, 1/3 cup margarine, vanilla and egg yolk with a fork in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir in Bisquick (will be crumbly).
Press into pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven, or until light brown.
Cool.
Melt together the corn syrup, 2 tablespoons margarine and chips; cool.
Spread over baked crust.
Sprinkle with nuts; press in lightly.
Refrigerate until firm.
Can be frozen.

title: microwave brown rice
directions: Melt margarine in casserole in microwave for about 1 minute. Add rice, soup mix and water.
Stir until mixed.
Microwave 8 minutes.
Stir with fork.
Cover with Saran Wrap and microwave for 8 more minutes.
Stir with fork just enough to fluff and check for softness.
Microwave another minute or two until rice is done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients with 1/2 cup nuts.
Cover with remaining nuts.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Melt
margarine in skillet and saute onions and celery. Pour over bread crumbs in very large mixing bowl.
Add seasoning
and toss together well.
Pour in enough broth to moisten. Add
eggs and
mix well.
Pack lightly into crock-pot.
Cover and
set
to high for 45 minutes.
Then reduce to low to cook for 4 to 8 hours.

title: angel cookies
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift flour and other dry ingredients together.
Stir into mixture.
Roll into small balls.
Dip half of balls in plain or colored sugar.
Flatten on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: swiss onion dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump (or spread) in order listed, pouring butter over all the ingredients.
Bake in 325° oven in 9 x 12-inch pan for 1 hour.

title: pecan balls
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in order given and form into small balls or crescents.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar when cool enough to handle.

title: pear cheese salad
directions: Mix gelatin and cream cheese together.
Add boiling water; blend with rotary beater.
Chill until thickened.
Beat pears with rotary beater.
Add pears and nuts to gelatin mixture.
Chill.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in unbaked pie crust. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies in food processor or blender.
Mix pudding like it says on box. Add Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar.
Spread a layer of cookies, then a layer of cream cheese and another layer of cookies. End with cookies. Chill overnight. Delicious.

title: homemade soup
directions: Put all ingredients in big pot.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until potatoes are done.

title: quick cobbler pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Melt oleo in baking dish and pour flour mixture into dish.
Add fruit with juice to mixture. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown. Crust will rise to top of pie.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add taco sauce and seasoning.
Mix and let simmer.
Heat tomatoes to boiling.
Lower heat.
On plate put chips, then on top of that put lettuce, then meat mixture, cheese on top of meat and hot tomatoes on top and serve.

title: abe's crayfish etouffee
directions: Wash thoroughly and cull crayfish.
To approximately 10 gallons of boiling water, add crayfish and scald for 5 minutes or until half cooked.
This is very important!
If they are not scalded long enough, they will break up and become mealy.
Cook and peel, separating fat from the tails.
Heat oil in pot.
Add minced onions, green onion tops, green pepper and parsley.
Saute.
Add crayfish fat or butter and cook over low heat until fat comes to the top, stirring constantly.
Add tails, cayenne pepper, salt and Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Add a small amount of hot water until etouffee is of desired consistency.
Simmer 30 minutes. Serve over hot rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl (by hand).
Mixture will be sticky.
Roll into 1/2-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until slightly brown.

title: company meat loaf
directions: Add bell pepper, garlic, onions, celery and bread crumbs to ground meat.
Work in eggs and milk, along with salt and pepper. Shape and put in loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Mix soup, Worcestershire sauce, horseradish and catsup; put on top of loaf.
Bake 30 minutes longer.
Serves 8.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla together.
Add zucchini, flour, baking powder, soda and nuts together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.

title: crispy cobb salad
directions: Arrange greens, turkey, tomatoes, eggs, avocado and bacon in rows on large serving platter.
Serve with dressing; sprinkle with Blue cheese if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cream cheese pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, mix at medium speed, beat together until smooth the cream cheese, 1 egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread over the bottom of the pastry shell.
Sprinkle with the pecans.
In a large clean bowl, beat 3 eggs on medium speed until frothy.
Add the corn syrup, 1/4 cup sugar, salt and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Gently pour the mixture over the pecans.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven until a knife inserted halfway between the center and edge comes out clean, 40 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack before cutting.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cook, stirring constantly, until clear and thickened.
Add gelatin.
Cool.
Place strawberries in pie shell.
Pour in gelatin mixture.
Chill.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Blend 1 cup of flour, margarine and powdered sugar.
Press mixture into a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: all-time favorite barbecue sauce
directions: In small bowl, combine soup, vinegar, oil, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and hot sauce; set aside.
Use sauce to baste ribs, chicken, hamburgers or steak during broiling or grilling.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Melt first 6 ounces butter or margarine.
Add white sugar, egg and 1/2 cup milk.
Bring to a boil and boil one minute.
Remove from heat and add walnuts, coconut and graham cracker crumbs.
Spread over graham crackers.
Put another layer of whole graham crackers over top and chill.

title: baby pizza
directions: Combine tomato paste, garlic salt and oregano.
Spread on crackers.
Top with cheese and meat cubes.
Sprinkle with oregano. Bake at 400° for 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve hot.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: chopped chicken livers
directions: In large skillet, saute onion in oil until tender; add livers and saute until just barely pink inside when cut slightly with a knife, about 10 minutes.
Cool a little.
Chop livers and eggs finely; stir in mayonnaise.
Serves 4.

title: reunion dip
directions: Blend cocktail sauce with cream cheese.
Spread mixture in a thin layer on a serving platter.
Layer remaining ingredients in the order listed.
Chill.
Serve with Tostitos chips.

title: crab dip
directions: Butter pie plate.
Mix all ingredients; spoon mixture into prepared pie plate.
Bake at 375° to 400° until it bubbles. Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with plain white crackers.
Yummy!

title: spinach salad
directions: Toss ingredients together gently.
Just before serving, toss with dressing made of following ingredients.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables in microwave for about 10 minutes. Then mix other ingredients with vegetables.
Sprinkle cheese on top and cook in conventional oven for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix the minced garlic, bell pepper, onion and parsley together with the seasonings.
Clean fryer well.
Rub inside and outside with salt and peppers.
Make slits in meaty sections with sharp knife and stuff minced seasoning mixture into slits, as you would a roast.
Dot with butter.
Place in baking dish or pan and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove foil and bake another half hour to brown.

title: corn pudding
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add salt, Accent and milk. Stir in corn. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until pudding is firm. Serves 6.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain corn.
Add celery, pepper, onion and pimento.
Mix mustard, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over corn mixture and cover. Let stand overnight for best flavor.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix the pulp, eggs and milk.
Add the dry ingredients.
Stir in the melted margarine last.
Pour this into a greased pan and bake about 1 hour at 325°.

title: cauliflower with mushroom and cheese sauce
directions: Clean cauliflower, leave on some of the green to make it look pretty.
Steam in a shallow amount of water.
While steaming, make any white sauce to make 2 cups worth and add 1 cup grated cheese, then mushrooms.
Drain cauliflower and place on serving dish and pour sauce over top.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: rice cooking directions
directions: For 3 to 12 cups cooked rice or seven 1/2 cup servings.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough 1/4-inch thick; place close together on pizza pan.
Bake according to package directions.
Let cool.
Beat together cream cheese and sugar over dough.
Slice bananas and strawberries; mix with pineapple.
Arrange fruit mixture on baked cookie dough.
Prepare glaze; pour over fruit.
Top with whipped cream.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Drain pineapple chunks. Place in 2-quart casserole dish. Mix sugar, flour and Cheddar cheese. Sprinkle over pineapple chunks. Mix crumbs and melted butter. Sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger with diced onion and ground garlic; drain. Add Ragu sauce and simmer for 10 minutes.
Cook lasagna noodles as directed on box.
Shred cheese.
Use a 3-quart casserole.
Start with meat sauce on bottom, the lasagna, then cheese, then repeat until all is used and meat sauce is on top.
Cook 1 hour at 350° or microwave for 25 minutes on medium heat.
If using microwave, top with Parmesan cheese after cooking.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and spices. Alternate flour and oil. Pour nuts and apples into this mixture and mix. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brush chicken with mayonnaise.
Coat with combined crumbs and cheese.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 1 hour or until tender. Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Heat consomme to boiling point.
Beat eggs until very light. Stir soup rapidly with fork and pour egg slowly into boiling soup until egg is shredded and cooked in long strings.
Serve into warmed bowls. Makes 2 or 3 servings.

title: chicken waldorf salad
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended. Serve on lettuce leaf. Makes 4 servings.

title: microwave chex mix
directions: In a small bowl, combine seasoned salt, Worcestershire sauce and margarine.
Pour cereal into a large bowl.
Pour mixture over ingredients.
Microwave on High about 5 to 6 minutes.
Stir every 2 minutes.
Spread onto a cookie sheet to cool.
Place into airtight containers.
Makes 9 cups of mix.

title: pork chops and noodles
directions: Brown pork chops and drain off fat.
Leave in skillet.
Add sauce.
Simmer with top on until chops are tender.
Add water, if necessary.
This amount of sauce for 4 chops.
Cook noodles and serve with sauce.
Add tossed salads and hot bread and you have a delicious meal.

title: creamy lime salad
directions: Add enough water to reserve pineapple liquid to measure 1 1/2 cups; heat to boiling.
Pour boiling liquid into gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Refrigerate until gelatin is slightly thickened, but not set.
Beat softened cream cheese into slightly thick jello until mixture is fluffy and cheese is in tiny pieces.
Place in mixer and beat at low speed.
Mix pineapple and whipped topping into jello/cheese mixture.
Pour into 4-cup mold and chill until firm.
